user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ayla Panini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiwtVIpBtKGTSIlPRlXWoQjHmNImwpsGr8ajO3tXx2uHueUqE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"W deal, W service, W food. I came to use my $5 off birthday voucher and I got a mini byob for just under $10! Service was excellent and very fast, and the portion was perfect and filling. The poke scoop recommended by the guy serving me, spicy tuna, was as delicious as he said! Would definitely go again :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5edVch4DjYxWTXzuzRzQtc_Tmid0kZNIxkrLH&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Selina Zhou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdh_K07G_35WE1XQolPePKtbRPCS7etPd4GO37eQJrOR8PInDd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The place is packed during lunches, but everyone is still quite attentive if you ordered pick-up. The portions are quite generous, and even the mini bowl is enough to make sure you’re not hungry.

The salmon is my go-to pick, the shoyu is a must hahaha.

There is not much seating near the place itself, so definitely just sit on some bench if it’s not raining.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUL3NqhZUds1uCJFHjqiEfzEWo0vnCvKMwPjhe&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Nicole Villalon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvX-NXEAvIz9hfeDmCLJbpqDwAUM7ozgrgH4vZTSomKf59ULGv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"STEVE’S POKE DOES IT AGAIN!!!
I’ve eaten here 4 times so far and every single time the service has been phenomenal. Today’s experience, however, absolutely takes the cake.

I ordered a mini BYOB with one scoop of poke online, coming up to ~$15 after tax and tips. The people at checkout were very attentive and made sure to check in and let me know my order was being prepared, and would be ready in a couple minutes. And then, the girl preparing my poke misread my order… and accidentally made me a large instead of a mini BYOB!!! She apologized multiple times, but how could I complain? More poke! And when I let it slip my birthday had been a week ago, the staff offered to throw in an iced tea, free of charge!

The poke was delicious, the service was stellar, and staff’s kindness absolutely made my day. I’ll be happy to visit Steve’s Poke again very soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmSF-4CMT-TmWd3-H-5XYvs2169hWwMLVwRpNj&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Tresa Horney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlCxWd5ESmqb9bOtTVn1nxYHpHQadHnSQ3MsNKRjtwrjVvD0jPDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Easy to order, friendly service, and a great meal. Pleased to have a vegetarian option. I’ll return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPy2Vjy3vWoV_UVTxuZk8COaNosX0DfibJOIhOD&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"$20 for this poke bowl, comes with 4 different choices of fish/poke, and any number of free “toppings”. The rice is “regular” white rice, not really flavored with mirin or anything. The fish come with sauce, but I should have asked for extra sauce on it because it had either dried up a bit or soaked into the rice. Considering the other choices around UBC, this is probably pretty good value for money.

I ordered takeout, but they have a few seats inside and outside if you prefer. The street currently has a bunch of (summer) construction, though.

They frequently have promo discounts on their site, but if you order on their online platform, there’s a mandatory $0.25 bag fee.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMG5oLw7BBFbNinAOxoTystwMC33r4z7vTCasRg&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Hari haran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIiG04_8rXv0XFEGQSVtxLwFR51JdEUoQ099gTHIIYGUB0FAw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Edit: just picked up a poke bowl and it seems the folks at the store have overdone it with soy sauce (???) this is not good. See picture attached

People are less responsive for pickup orders. Not sure why.

But mostly, Some of the best poke you can eat in Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5Fa39-wPyW-gxFrFm-dQJx5a5nADo4V_MO6ES&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Vitalie Veclici","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVn8kycEuyvgu8wcx5Mpwijp97INeeCs7xxytZNIaEQ_HzZHS2yeg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Steve’s Poke Bar delivers delicious, fresh poke bowls with a variety of high-quality ingredients and customizable options. The staff is friendly and attentive, ensuring a pleasant experience from start to finish. While the food is top-notch, the interior could benefit from some updates to enhance the overall dining atmosphere. With a bit more attention to the ambiance, Steve’s has the potential to become one of the top poke spots in Vancouver. Still, a fantastic choice for poke enthusiasts looking for great service and tasty bowls.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Erika W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXk-zmliLlm5bIplSxpmOCgffchZEiqu1WLJ9rhI9Bc-N96TAwesQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food quality is fantastic and the portions are extremely satisfying. The staff were super friendly and patient as I chose my ingredients for my bowl. Not from Vancouver but when I do come back, I’m going to be sure to revisit this place because it is a stand out even among the fancy dine in places I went to. Thank you so much and until next time all the best.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Selina Zhou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdh_K07G_35WE1XQolPePKtbRPCS7etPd4GO37eQJrOR8PInDd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Mercante is a great place to visit, and I urge you to, especially for their pizzas. However, as great as it tastes, it is clear that over the two years I have been going there, the amount of arugula they have been adding has decreased drastically.

Maybe it is just shrinkflation, or maybe nobody likes arugula, but regardless, that is disappointing nonetheless.

Stick to the pizzas with pesto or tomato sauce, they are absolutely amazing, the ones without are quite bland.

The crust is some of the best you’ll ever taste, or maybe all my years of never trying pizza this fresh ruined my tastebuds.

If I were to recommend a particular pizza, it’d definitely be the pesto pollo! It’s simple, pesto with chicken and mushrooms but it is a joy to eat.

The pizza is quite fast, cooked in around 10 minutes, and there are plenty of seating as well.

I tried the pasta once when it first came out… and it was basically just reheated in a shoddy take-out container. Incredibly disappointing compared to the pizzas.

The mini caprese salad has the best sauce I’ve ever eaten, so even if the price is a bit steep, worth it imo.

Anyways, please visit! And enjoy some of the pizza pictures I’ve taken over the years.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8dRluJ1Y1QIiw864urKWtZC0j-aWF2bSdF9bd&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"B W (Battery)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2VcTxYkMGGx4jwVvZYc_zLzH45KC5E2wcm69COre1h2Q43jQG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The pricing for the pizzas increase further and further BUT the quality and portion size of each pizza decreases. The flavour of the pizza is decent (not justifiable for the price). Compared to in 2021 the toppings added have been less and less (You can see in the photos below, One with less arugula is recently taken)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOEaFBwrMdmz38q6u4vdNNgNito6eNO4ARACcrh&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"charles bai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVivIWOvTOamsgiucoqI5EKukhiOsZqTk7nog1iV-Y1Xav6PIczow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pizzas were ok. The dough is most as chewy as I’d like. The underside was a bit too charred for my liking. But other than that, it tastes like you would expect an Italian pizza to taste.

But what is that $7 for such a small slice of tiramisu…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyDKLlV2mlf_ToQxfsaQiVcIBUIa9jTyxTTki9&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"JuChul Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBl2ZXIT6h1ADZaXOEj0qdwPy-q7Gry2PxCal1RfLk4LIaRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow, a hidden treasure inside UBC~
The coffee was a bit disappointing, but the pizza was the best. Since it's not a coffee shop, it would be perfect to just have it with coke^^","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLPEGB-CaG0qEI3Tio6TacurZsxD_EtFBBO-5W&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Ryan Tsang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVH174LmUPGzeC52GF3Com64V8GOYDH3Xrkt6Q91uXjQsUYZcmm4g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"If you look at the menu someone else posted here, you can see that they have increased the price per pizza by $4 over 8 months. I paid $17 for this pizza bianca and I’m not even full. My friend did recommend the prosciutto tho. Just want to point out that you can get so much more pizza at fatih for the same price

Edit: went back to try the prosciutto, it’s a good, honest pizza on its own. It’s just that you can get more at other places for the same price","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPp8saw9uH9ksnbeKVj66TlamGY5BnRRiu2byMD&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2022-10-17"},{"Name":"Jane Shi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFWHgQId1z1gpOQAZDnSRuOfaVawcViBKqphYyzzEF887Ye7SC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I really like the pesto pollo pizza, however, it's price has gone from $13 4 years ago, to $19.45 now🥲 also it sometimes gets overcooked","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODyyebpBbceGXMlNKDmaaFIc4DVQsrJKSrXt05&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Aihua Jiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiIXew8o1uyfdMhPFiSNro9u7WkSI3CgBfNp4g3MiTBjo4SQPa=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kids said that this was the best pizza they ever had! People here were super nice too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOM3ppLtWgktr3TfhuELY8yq_Y6r7Nppem_rQVI&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-7-11"},{"Name":"Tanisha K Johnson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLWKo2zP2bT5gefRcCNDXbo6jtsCNqEJZkafWXJiSZYIcvJbw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food itself is good, but the young Asian server at the front desk treats my friend madly. so rude! I felt disappointed since I am no stranger to the shop. Will reduce visits.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Cindy Ly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIzge4iM_AthUe2Y8lEMYg2Y2ExA0fMxlIza7QeGpuo6ooWkw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came for their Happy Hour menu which I thought was the most affordable. I tried almost all their items. Their chicken wings are a showstopper...definitely a must have. I liked their chicken burger but not the side salad. Ambience was comfortable and staff were attentive.  Will definitely go back again if I'm ever in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPH91GTRSzk1oTMM9p1IO53xs2WIKdEM3AxtjvG&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Stephanie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBV5KRG75WlxmWo1wuDhWSQhlZCOao4V2_9kFkOn0OqRNe45TP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We came on a Saturday during happy hour. The restaurant was pretty empty. I love how it's laid out and the number of tables they have.

Our server was knowledgeable and friendly. Happy hour wildlight drinks get $2 off

Inverted dude - was a coffee based drink. I didn't really like it. I wouldn't get it again

Negroni - strong and delicious

Mussels and fries (16) - plentiful and well seasoned. Loved the sauce. The French fries were crispy and addictive. Would recommend

Chicken wings 10 pieces (12) - pretty standard. Crispy on the outside. On the sweeter side.

Overall would come back to try their other items. Prices during happy hour are a steal","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDxXa1iPMIaDUb3dYUzqDVP3M8rux0dOeqzQqE&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"Crabby Ermine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7ghzWacgyIAQrG2Lk7qt0s7V3r_adVAnu6EbLXS1Ck1zLBRgjvA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"10/10 experience. Great service. Great atmosphere. Great food.  Parking is free underground and register with check in. Loved all the dishes we had today.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaJa3xW-fN0TaVwqmoUrrmVKfqPIH5GB-Ezcgu&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Ray Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3wj8Ne3ngI4eg9ouEU6zPmvERlQuudbckz4ma4Vg6pfYrsWM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful service in a nicely appointed dining room with a fun and trendy atmosphere. The location is particularly convenient for parents who are looking for more upscale dining options while visiting their kids studying at the nearby university.  The seafood chowder, seafood linguine, and duck breast were particularly good. We went on “Wine Wed” where select bottles were 50% off offering good value. Portions were just adequate but not what you would consider large, but that just means you get to leave room to try their yummy desserts (I particularly liked the Stawberry Fraisier, and the Basque Cheesecake with red wine reduction).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4tLmOOTAsLJvn5WtbD1OyzUmHRy-gI1MFkAD8&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Riley Taylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ-9EcAoNHnhEH_CEFhkVuk3VNbTy11CmDBZ6MWN5FAekK6Cw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"TOP TIER. Premium EVERYTHING.

Quite literally one of the best dining experiences that we have ever had. From the second we walked in, we were approached by GM Margot who made us feel the warmth and excitement to host us for supper. Victor, our bartender didn’t miss a beat with suggestions and promptness of beverage top ups! Food…. Don’t get me started!!! I’m salivating a day later writing this review thinking about how beautifully curated each dish was designed. Chef Chow is a total artist and a master of his craft. A few musts include the Tuna Tartar, Oyster Motoyaki, Beet and Burrata salad, duck, the scallops OMG, sable fish… DOUBLE OMG and an array of desserts that the pastry team had skillfully curated to reflect British Columbia’s nature and environment.

From the bottom of our hearts- HUGE thanks to the entire team for the special hospitality and delicacies. You all truly outdid yourselves.

Thank you!!
Riley and Anna","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8Z8XjNkHyhAvJM342-p_KpqBWYsIkY1rwLmYe&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuLCrwKa9NLpGvoI7KXeamb10EWAoAmRoPxgdu96hyYHG6mtPkhg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came the other day as a solo diner for lunch. Had the smoked sable fish chowder and the harvest green salad. The chowder was the best I've ever had. Very nice atmosphere. My server Mel was also welcoming, attentive, and came across as a genuinely very lovely person.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfJygC171kXxCcNsSJo3-wLP0SQ2Uyt1Mnw7Sc&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-9-26"},{"Name":"Alex Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIuPG0P_xvSAHjLq3lehdcGbMVx_kB14iyd4zXzj-7VOUEMAw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First and foremost, a huge thank you to our server Naomi for making our evening at Wildlight truly special. She was an absolute joy, incredibly sweet, and very attentive and informative throughout our meal.

We split the pescatarian board and mushroom gnocchi, had the strawberry frasier for dessert, and finished with the complimentary shortbread.

Everything was absolutely wonderful.

The pescatarian board showcased a fantastic mix of seafood and pickled vegetables and was a true pleasure to explore.

The mushroom gnocchi was the epitome of comfort food with some great textures.

The strawberry frasier was incredibly refreshing and had the best ripe strawberry flavor in several forms.

The shortbread was a lovely surprise and sweet treat to end the meal before we left!

My partner and I each had two cocktails (Awesome Blossom and Pacific Vesper in the picture) and were thoroughly tempted to try more! Each cocktail was delicious, well balanced, and complimentary to the food.

Wildlight was a lovely experience from start to finish. Both my partner and I would strongly recommend an evening here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORrSSDOzpPYS1WvgEYc9nnBneuVG28DZxfzgy3&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Mary Proulx","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEhEtou551etajvQPOzB4dygQrXePqTCHvPLlyMk3uMrquxnRA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love gnocchi - the mixed mushroom stroganoff gnocchi here is the most fresh and flavourful ever. Half price bottle of wine Wednesday a wonderful surprise. Dessert is beautiful and enough to share. A fabulous lunch with friends; food, location and space and great service - thanks to Brandon","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTKSTnTBH98HWxtMSpyf0Dq2J26QKkVW-G2ebL&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-10-23"}]

[{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best places at UBC to hang out! Lovely staff and wonderful vibe. Tried the grilled chicken ramen and it was generously filled, almost couldn’t finish the whole meal. Other friends of mine ordered burgers and they said they were fantastic. Prices aren’t cheap, so it’s a place to go for a celebration once in a while.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCAcUJj4YsDoBohcTlkfqkVoKoS5nD30m0xhBk&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"M J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKuOygw8Aep3D50DIY1TUyT5-BADbHqefvUMdU3qf0JomdEvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great selection of food and craft beer, good place to hang out for a few drinks. The small nachos was enough for us to share between 4-5 people, loved the roast beef sandwich too. Deep fried Mac and cheese was nicely cooked and the tomato sauce helps with the heaviness of the Mac and cheese. Ordered the IPA and loved it - crisp and had a nice aroma. The service was fast and attentive although it was busy at the time of visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXcjzjGRoyy6vduMIRbCuk6WLqez6jCJo-pmrv&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Dylan Magierek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0kVFJpnKEbseG6UEIeqqL4lraFc9x941pplBP3I-C35nxYYtP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was a nice sojourn from a long day of driving and walking around the UBC campus moving my son into the dorms.  The food was very good: especially the fries, chicken sandwich, side salad and burgers.  The French Dip was just pretty good.  I wouldn’t recommend it.  It didn’t have enough meat to balance out the kinda hard roll it came on.  Lots of beer choices and I enjoyed the Pilsner.  Expensive for a brewery/sorta pub!  But good service and atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9A45j3pzrU9X5vPV34VvyOZ59GJCSIADcF_aQ&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Anthony Le","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIC22IEsZIbsu-lUm5EyMjgm7JYJbJkRjU13-W8XkZYXAuixkB6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice place for a sit-down, fancy-ish meal. The drinks were pretty good, and the food is delicious; definitely a nice place for a formal meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOE7MmrhhKXG2H5sjxLe8eW9H0WqnR-Tuz2xtla&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Vanessa Becker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjP-M2atXZC7s46eJ4wd5XC-RHr2pn3fRoPwoLQqghdxSrQBA9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Browns is a nice pub type spot. We got seated quickly for lunch and our server was friendly and attentive. Drinks and food came out at decent times.
My sister has celiacs disease and had heard Browns has gluten free options. They were able to make modifications on a meal and she enjoyed it, Blackened chicken Caesar with no croutons.
I got a cheeseburger with Caesar salad.
There’s a ramp and accessible entrance and chairs can be moved to fit wheelchairs.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgyStbHqW6IqBgmoutJLEDmIuxPuu1FMQBsNe6&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-5-19"},{"Name":"Maria N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvvSp5rMnSOuZlWMjCChnc3kIAvhaXhf7fzSVxvOmtGCdirlnS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty food and quick service. There were barely any customers when we came in on Saturday afternoon.
We got a chicken burger with a side of fries and a salad with a chicken breast (came a bit late.) Both tasted good.
Very decent place to grab a bite around UBC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMh6lhWfsmLChgTOHHA4RM65-xzqYFv7EYhpgf5&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Biggie Sandhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJXTSWG9GRBzr7s-0VIl70S37U8PyPayiekKKBiKbK7ygPFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had our work Christmas Dinner here. Great workers great food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMIthBnLk1en1HwdUUDWZ3GIt9z3pNtalz6zAt&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Zibiah Sandhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIV7J0QaWpaOWLAzK9jqKBW9H-FOCY6ViMt-aqG3Okqi6IgVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am following up from my previous review that I had left a few weeks ago. Despite having a negative experience, the staff at Browns Crafthouse went above and beyond to make sure that my friends and I had a good experience to make up for what had initially happened. The manager Matt reached out and was very kind and generous, and offered to make the experience better for us. They accommodated drinks and many appetizers for our large group, and were super sweet the entire time. I cannot remember our servers name, but she was a tall caucasian woman. She provided excellent service and took my friend's gluten allergy very seriously. It was some of the best customer experiences I had. Matt himself had come out and greeted us, apologized for the previous experience, and made sure we had a great time. They went above and beyond to make sure that we had a good experience, and it was really appreciated!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Jeff Downer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXl3HQ-1C4N-_a7ykvhIi5aM883AB-cDQVYb1xeenCY7zekayvZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! This is good. One of the LARGEST wraps I’ve ever had, must have weighed several pounds. The quality and balance of meat and vegetables is perfect. I will eat these all the time. I ordered a mix wrap, chicken, beef and lamb and all three are cooked perfect and not dry.
The counter service was so nice and accommodating. Upstairs was clean and a generally great place for lunch!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPm2KQDyO2c1CL0fzUMucqmbPUMgqg47YuRE_9v&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"FARZAM ameri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUC2df7lOXeiqMsnPi2htms2568VuOUkmExj9MZ8kkh6j2hvhus=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered Loghmeh kebab, and I have to say optimistically under 40% of that kebab contains actual Meat. The food was tasteless and It was just waste of money. I STRONGLY suggest you not to go there.
Staff was really polite and friendly though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoCVXxYvNnPrU6RCsUdI-VTH87WanqMj-btLQ2&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Extremely delicious and huge portion size (tho the size might vary some days, I have put the two pics for comparison). First time I went, the portion size was quite small for the price but the second time I went, they gave me a huge portion which lasted for 2 meals in total. I love the Vaziri meal that they have!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPih8L_Q2wK2QfkznE7CiefGaptLdidvJ3Bpds5&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-4-16"},{"Name":"Mariena Bui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6Nw1jeBXne8haJacgZytBHrMEqU2gmOMAF3l5QWK0CwO3rXPJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the saffron chicken with zeresht rice and I was satisfied with how the food taste and how filling it was, that I even had leftovers. My husband ordered khoreshte ghayme and he said that this place made this dish very well. For dessert we got sholeh shard and I love how it this place didn’t make this dessert to sweet! Next time I’m in UBC I will probably go to this place again ☺️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCCrILJyF2kem_vb-iTitmN7-tSH1WfxWLBmab&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-2-29"},{"Name":"Negin Rahimi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4DUUoCWRf2VeIHKqwIhVGBDp6aPH06WL8KyLGIL_eC6FWBXb5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I recently visited the UBC branch of this restaurant near closing time. Unfortunately, the two jooje kabab (chicken) dishes we ordered were not warm. When I asked for a replacement and for them to be warmed up, they simply reheated the same plate, which did not resolve the issue and took a long time. The taste of the food was also disappointing, and the chicken was not cooked well. We ended up requesting a refund, but since it was late at night (around 11 pm), we couldn't find another place to eat. I have had a great experience at their other branch, but I cannot recommend this particular branch due to the poor service and quality that fell short of my expectations for Sahel Restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7yKfp8eM4dYI6zdmfXa1F0jAkoq40k9-j-8vc&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-5-23"},{"Name":"Miyuki Food","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIefbmBJIFd8vluRG1CtvO_cHUxsRdwtm3bVobO6E-icLpG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So good!! I got the lamb and beef donair and the meat and everything was tasty, and the service was great. There is also a nice upstairs area with seating and a tv","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFpW22RVhCzjq0t8O64yMaiiDBQ5d2EBHb_Nw&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-4-9"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"New branch of Sahel at UBC featuring donair and Persian food. The ordering counter is downstairs with a seating area upstairs. It wasn't particularly clean: some tables had crumbs and there was trash on the floor under some tables, which weirdly is carpeted. The furniture, however, is in good condition and comfortable.
FIRST VISIT: I had a felafel plate and a rice pudding. The food was average quality. The sauces they use are a little different than the typical sauces: the white sauce was thicker and tangier and the red sauce had a hint of heat but mostly tasted like a zestier and thinner version of ketchup (this is maybe not the most appealing way of describing it - it was good, like a cross between hot sauce and ketchup). I liked the different flavours and the rice was actually pretty good, but I was indifferent about the felafel and hummus. The felafels were like the puck-shaped ones you can buy at the grocery store. The rice pudding had a nice flavour but was almost gelatinous in consistency, which I can't decide how I feel about.
Second visit: I wanted to see if the more distinctly Persian dishes would be better, so I tried the eggplant stew, the one veg stew on the menu. The “broth” that the eggplant and tomato were stewed in was straight oil, which I did not like. Again the rice was great, but they give so much with the stew that I didn’t know what to do with it all.
The prices ($17 for the plate and stew w/ rice, $5 for the rice pudding) are fair for the amount of food you get, which is pretty generous. I finished the whole felafel plate but was very hungry, so if you have a smaller appetite you will have leftovers. Two people could easily split a rice pudding.
The staff seems very nice, but I just can’t see myself coming back for the food. I’d get the felafel again if it was the ONLY place to get felafel in town, but it is very much not.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNY72ngJ2ZaAwXFb3jb_xOhzFGMNLItp0KiPLjO&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-1-12"},{"Name":"Abdullah K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaOLs3U1NGAh-EH96OS0WG3dhkXXnjYtovUMs7UYINOdg16mA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my go-to place to eat on and around campus! With the limited halal options at UBC, this is a lifesaver. Good food, phenomenal portions, and fresh! If I had to suggest one thing on the menu, it would be the soltani meal. The steak is really well cooked and tender. I’m so happy Sahel opened at UBC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9Y519rm1k_jiyVqRKLtV2JmvAIaOwnipoGyUb&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2023-12-8"}]

[{"Name":"Alex Zhang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhM8_i0FgjcMWn1pe2iCTPCulYiJ6ZdM-BxEPPrbNCZswmBhAC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We got the 12.99 specials that come with the free strawberry tea. Food was good but portion sizes were amazing - way more than what we would expect for the price point. Would come back again, please don't come when I'm here though because I don't want to wait in like to get in.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwGUffMCid9mYoOZnoUamdNb5OEGSphWqcE3J4&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Grace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpyR6lW9JHiyXGuG73lo5A19PTb1WXFzVLCnrO84Gv3hfeDE5c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A new restaurant on campus serving Japanese and Chinese cuisine! I got the corn croquette set for $12.99, with a small bowl of udon added on for $3.50. The set came with a melon smoothie. The corn croquette was delicious, crispy on the outside and creamy on the inside. It came with curry sauce and katsu sauce. It also came with a big portion of rice (the rice was well-made, which was a relief since I’ve had mushy rice at other restaurants before). The miso soup was salty, but paired perfectly with the rice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP24-dj3EKzX1h2q3vosOg1MLmiGK8BW9sRxAVJ&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Madeline Kam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpk6Vux-KZ276SHSgtsoa9YbbByLpXdFWBO-biQ8KXP9MZVJYZxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The staff and atmosphere were great, but the food was a bit bland. I ordered the combo which included miso soup and drink of the day and I believe it was 10.99 which is a pretty good price. However, the food did not have much flavor and included scarce amounts of protein (in this case chicken). The drink was a winter melon slushy which was a bit icy and crunchy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0eJ6zfyWxK9NGBkvDlyPP7AyjsetQVWVPollW&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Anouk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX030nN0Ds_sauo0gxWlayfH_7n_wMK-lQfODkscyR8xTr0EynOFg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Place is bright and clean. We both ordered the Shanghai thick noodles and the dishes took 25 min to arrive. Taste was unbelievably mediocre and the soup was too sour - neither of us finished. The opening deals on the menu are affordable though, especially for UBC, and maybe they taste better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWiirhGWCywKk_4pWuAI7dmTssCBUA1V0fb4Cd&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"Isabelle lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKeqOC4yQmaYwP6NpsFegJJEZXL9yVwbsvUjxB7-j-CAgqz2g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service - all the servers were super attentive and even the store manager was helping with clearing, wiping down tables and serving food.

Food is decent, generous portions and very reasonable price. You won’t find anything cheaper than this these days.

I got the 3 fried prawns, 2 fried scallops,  2 pieces of fried yam + bowl of rice and miso soup for $14 only.

Highly recommend this place. Give it a try (:","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNz-ZmsmRszrSY1eFYJM1K72lNbvdcZnF6Ubyzo&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Sophia H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJj7J89gHLVylfj7eNtEAHc3P50FouTDBLmVYxgTpUzNqmzNA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came here today for lunch with one of my friends and were pleasantly surprised by Beyond BBQ!! We both got the pork loin katsu ($17) and they had a special on where if you get any katsu you also get a free drink, so I got a supreme mango tea and my friend got the passion fruit tea. Everything was so delicious, and they gave us a TON of food for the price!!! The pork had an amazingly crispy breading and was flavourful without being dry, the miso soup came out hot (which I was very impressed by), and there was the perfect amount of rice. The sauces were good also and added a delicious pop of flavour!! Not to mention that the fruit tea was so flavourful and fresh!! The staff and servers were also lovely and did an incredible job, especially with giving recommendations. I would definitely come back!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4_goCkK_8lX1VMTr-7haXCj-Lb_pjZnBWZzOc&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Justina He","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJX5XpjJlDr-QcyrWD78qxzdGiJ3dWfMQkYELeI3EDDwTRmpES=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is an affordable new restaurant on campus that people should NOT go to. They serve horrible versions of Asian cuisine that not only are insults to the original recipes but are disgusting. Ordered a class mung bean noodle dish that took half an hour to be served despite being a COLD dish but what is supposed to be salty and spicy noodles in a sesame paste was grossly sweet and soggy with random vegetables. Friends got the croquette and udon dishes that had undercooked rice and just a pile of raw cabbage as a "salad", stale kimchi and noodles with no flavour.
TLDR: DO NOT be fooled by the cheap deals because they are too good to be true and you can get much better food for a similar price. Service was mid at best, with food taking too long to be served but the food itself was disgusting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzVrAc1rEc5JYNxc7W5m9l-YXkA8S25-YuqHcQ&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Big portion size, pretty tasty and great customer service! The food came pretty fast given that this is deep fried food. I liked the unlimited salad and rice servings! I wish the sauce was bigger in portion size too to dip the katsu in. Overall, the price seems reasonable for the portion size and taste that you receive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOz5ZRWgqek5cZ591Gbo4WglK7khxYCB4szBSK&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-5-22"}]

I asked him to make something special for me and he as I was hungry and everything on the menu looked great and he made this!!! 😍😋

Truly made me happy 🙏","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmczE1V5tZ3s5jhaBMo5muCLC3QYQmEsmc7dZT&fid=0x0:0xfb8dec509effaf79"],"When":"2024-12-23"},{"Name":"Mike Lapenna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFIvBa0AGMBL5-B8OS4f3WOp-gipDoffwdpfbukNi-vL6h9rwvJQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"For a fast food joint, this place really excelled. Plentiful indoor seating and a nice patio outside but I didn't see any umbrellas.  The wraps and bowls were so generous you could probably skip your next meal.  And for creativity, they had a hibiscus lemonade drink at the counter.  Nice treat.  Tasty and fresh meal.  I love the sauces.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcB_kfbjDKR1HShQ8gO3AdBIUSHqxUJoe-aySR&fid=0x0:0xfb8dec509effaf79"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Kimia Abtahi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ2CE2uN5zYA5-Ne2mDlfB8HQlAxJSeFJKc2I3kIPxW8BoK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I ordered the chicken shawarma bowl, and the portion size was more than satisfying. It came with a nice balance of half salad, half rice, along with hummus and garlic sauce. The chicken was fresh, juicy, and flavorful, making it a great combination with the sides.

Overall, it’s a solid choice for lunch if you’re looking for something tasty and filling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5tMhBUnSfYx0Cr-8VqZlMAnbMAitYLg05A3k&fid=0x0:0xfb8dec509effaf79"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Shim YoLo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9XiPT_KaiLFykPP5HSZvMvML6zZQZeEGREDSKbtc8Bydct1U4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"had a fantastic dining experience at jam-jar . The authentic Lebanese dishes were bursting with flavor, from the creamy hummus. The rice bowl platter was a highlight, and the freshly baked. The employees were welcoming and attentive, making the experience even more enjoyable. If you’re looking for delicious, authentic Lebanese cuisine, it is a must-try! I’ll definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnJYdz6JnkHPDDMw6y_sTqX0CEM-Jrnc_zgW7c&fid=0x0:0xfb8dec509effaf79"],"When":"2024-10-24"},{"Name":"Johnny Fansher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWG34f6YSi84gg3JANp3FyD1uZ_GsH9Yb1lFgk5CMGvn43qQ2J3=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love the food here and the staff are really great at Customer Service. Even though I eat meat, it’s really tempting to choose the veggie items because they’re so flavourful. Try the cauliflower- it’s incredible. Wish they’d bring back the spinach. It was amazing. The new beef option is very tasty too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPGvnkdl0HFrl-pb0NzOOsM1QrWVag5QwNIG_1&fid=0x0:0xfb8dec509effaf79"],"When":"2024-6-28"},{"Name":"alisha kansal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZFHEBGxDSCUAtm1heLmCmdHlRcTtsx3hB7a0Qzut6tn1RZD579w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am a big fan of jamjar bowls, their quantities and the freshness of the chicken they serve. I went in to grab dinner tonight and the staff was so friendly and interactive. There were two people working, a girl and a guy wearing spectacles.. he provided exceptional service and was welcoming. It feel nice to be greeted with warmth when grabbing food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQm64vLitHt25cadzV4WLtHV7SUAIBjVVvKDOR&fid=0x0:0xfb8dec509effaf79"],"When":"2024-12-3"},{"Name":"Michael Carlon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV6cVvTpa16_EmiiPiUCrcIGqzT_hc2Ni8h3jpc_TOjUKi0id0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m working near the UBC location, Jam Jar is the best tasting, healthiest lunch you can get in my opinion. [{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved my experience at the Gallery. Ordered burgers with salads and my friends also ordered some chicken wraps and fries. Everything was pretty tasty and well seasoned. Beers were fantastic. Prices a little bit on the high side, especially for a restaurant inside campus, but it’s definitely worth trying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOs1KGPNL5W9iWl4zIgcxQSrnJ2fRONlu24N4UE&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Anthony Le","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIC22IEsZIbsu-lUm5EyMjgm7JYJbJkRjU13-W8XkZYXAuixkB6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pretty good place for a nice meal for ubc students. There wasn’t necessarily any service, but nonetheless the food was pretty good. Definitely would go here for a drink it I was a ubc student","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9K99fN-Zftq2MUemombIFm2bz26P8kglKa8XA&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Randal Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-rLwNvZI_YNkKUeSaM-3PNFSDfyyf9aevvVnQDsEtEwj3jDdP=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The dining room is spacious and has lots of natural light making it a good spot for lunch. During lunchtime there was no loud music playing so I could have a conversation with a friend. You order food and drinks at the bar, but I got both pretty quickly. I had a red sangria which seemed reasonably good. I had a citrus and beet salad which was also good but not very filling if you're expecting it to be a meal. The service from the staff serving the food and clearing the table seemed reasonably good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I like this place. I wouldn't go here as a night out, but at the right times, it's a chill hang. The atmosphere varies wildly depending on the day. On some nights it's louder and is in line with what you'd expect a university bar to be like, and sometimes it's very relaxed, and you can even find some people using it as a study spot (not something I would consider or really recommend, but you do you as long as it's not busy and no one needs the table). Sometimes it's somewhere in between or a weird mix of both. It's not always predictable, but I've found that to hit the quieter days that I prefer, early evening during exam season at school is best, and summer in general are chiller than the main academic year.
The food is good, often surprisingly good. The menu items are well thought-out and tasty, and nicely presented. It's not a veg-centric establishment but there's lots of choice for vegans! Off the current menu, I've had the Power Punch Salad, the Vegan Pulled Jackfruit, the Vegan Burger, Vegan Chick'n Caesar Wrap, and the Tempeh Teriyaki. I wasn't particularly impressed by the Caesar wrap - it wasn't awful, I just didn't feel like it was worth $19.5, but everything else was a delight. I'm glad their vegan burger is a (seemingly) housemade, minimally processed black bean patty instead of beyond meat or similar! I usually won't order a salad as my meal, but the Power Punch is substantial! The side salad that comes with the sandwich orders is actually pretty nice too.
They make good cocktails and have a long list of local draft beers on tap which I haven't really had a chance to dip into, but I got the "Green Bird" for fun on St. Patrick's Day, which is just a version of their house "T-Bird" lager that's been coloured green (maybe naturally, judging by the grassy notes I got from it, but I don't know for sure). It was actually a good lager though!
Sometimes the staff is nice enough, sometimes I get the vibe that they're too cool to be serving me or something, but because the only interactions you have with them are when you order and pay at the bar and when they bring your food out, an unenthusiastic bartender doesn't ruin the whole experience. Because of this service style, you can expect to be in and out of here faster than you would at a full table service restaurant, but it's not fast food, so dishes still take as much time to prep as they would at a "regular" sit-down place. It's also pricier than typical counter service food, but very reasonably priced compared to off-campus restaurants that serve food of this quality, and there's no obligation to tip 20%. To me, the service model, fair prices, and high quality are a combination of the best elements of counter service and full service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQwEdJ88aXsSlarpRs-9jcRwBTBo0B-hIa3KfE&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2021-4-19"},{"Name":"Steve Morgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmgrmzSyB3CC_qWamR3pXmaZna6-RxfqDluiFzTGNrypDReGc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very large service area. Games. Foosball table. Big patio. Not the least bit crowded for lunch in summertime. They have a limited menu but it has decent variety. Quality of the food is good for a university joint. Beer list contains a good number of local, craft beers. Kids can dine here but no kids menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPovaBoxIJBbbrqqo0D1-7ZOWCRu2vS1WYswiw&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2019-7-10"},{"Name":"N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIY4v8Faubu_Z2iYv4KPw3dI0PsoX4C2vKMs2dyC6KeQw7f0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Almost no service (walk up to bar to order) and any service you do get is most often unfriendly. Like the type of attitude you would think takes more effort than being nice. They are not making a case for autogratuities in general because I think this is one of the reasons this place gets away with such unpleasant staff. The other reasons include that there just isn't that much choice on campus and the food is basic but decent here. The view is nice if you're out on the patio. And there's a lot of space. It's very sad that the sit-down nice restaurant didn't make it because that's exactly what the area needs. They just didn't promote it and since this is the top floor, no one discovers this space by walking by. The service at the Gallery when it was in the old sub was never this sad. Have pride in whatever you do. Just making people happy and not disappointed is a reward in itself. Or fake it. Whatever. Just don't make people more down than when they came in.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jade","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyJzoLeWrDhvC2NhSPJXZCJklxu-S39z3hI0-Hrrv9m9AA5ZkKQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is my first review below 5 stars.
They automatically charge a tip without telling their customers (I didn't notice any signage). This makes their prices misleading. Also, since I wasn't with a group and I ordered at the register auto-grat does not seem reasonable. I will happily change my review and return as a customer when they are more forthcoming about their prices.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Haleh Magnus","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZGl2rvHWlqbzuuFKZ9pHQfQXwlTmRHH4ep4A1K4mjlsDM4dQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went there for a light food, beer and to listen to good #jazzmusic from amazing musician of UBC Jazz Club. The space was bright , spacious. I found it busy and big line up. The Jazz performance are on Wednesday 6pm to 9pm by UBC Jazz Club.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPIUZZN56p20ZRBTeW6npihhigzi31LzbVDTis&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2022-9-22"}]

Good service in general, nothing crazy.

Servings are also a little small, up sized it and realised it looked more like normal serving. Probably better to serve more to cater to the student population.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxr74lRM_hjEQIzAYwZSCD6IvxA1XlUaqvyE-A&fid=0x0:0x52216304f25772e2"],"When":"2023-8-9"},{"Name":"Rico C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJSPs7IwE2pPBNxNqoF9AWcF7glNi-GV2crXAnc0vJ62CxPEebCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good portions though soup ramen could use some more soup. Most of my friends got Zenbu which was better with meat oil but still it is very dry… I think undon noodle must be much better with tautly texture. I got the mentaiko cream mazesoba and it was very tasty! The chilli powder was super good!! You can get any size for same price but it's the same amount of noodles and toppings (it's just more soup). My friend says the original ramen was average.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHjn9o9NH4BtH9gzNPuscVipBcJepA6cMCIPU&fid=0x0:0x52216304f25772e2"],"When":"2023-11-21"}]

[{"Name":"Lucas Carvalho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3Y5swxK5t-70Gy8Xk2HfBl2d0Kp1d5aI2hfbI1RYPe5ETgbk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently ordered from Pizza Garden and was thoroughly impressed. I had no idea that a franchise could make such a good Neapolitan-style pizza. The crust was perfect, and the toppings were fresh and flavorful. The standout, however, was the service. Serdar, who handled my order, was incredibly helpful and friendly. He ensured everything was accurate and delivered on time. Highly recommend Pizza Garden for a fantastic takeout experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoWwnrdza1eRDt2mkSGkIMSp2JBHRPFqiCP1si&fid=0x0:0xbbb6ed7ce318b358"],"When":"2024-7-15"},{"Name":"Alex D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1AiUQzb9xl_LWZO8zrudqnEF7MFlpJwIR41eeS_FpkOjPDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great pizza. Great people. Great atmosphere.

Best midnight snack on campus by far.

The staff here are exceptional- nothing but good things to say. I will be back to eat at the garden soon, mark my words.

Sincerely,
Alex","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"white MinK_유학생 흰밍크","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMdtH-XRii0erNS64dI6X46Y7qAH_4JVNXmd6wau4U9fTI9ow=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've ordered a few times, but  I ordered today was really nice and made with good ingredients.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWBtkGymeIwFSHxYn6zNhb-rE3BcWQ3S0QlA1n&fid=0x0:0xbbb6ed7ce318b358"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Thomas Dafinger","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVgRxfBp6VMIHfTWsantiboN_3wV3cKgrdCUr_knYj_-dXSrU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I ate a 10“ Pizza Caprese in here and I was not completely satisfied with it. I was missing spices and flavor. The tomato sauce was almost tasteless, unfortunately… And the pizza has little to do with neapolitan style as it is advertised.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMRB2lJIEX7bDPk11BcVyhptdf-G4QrNFbldX0&fid=0x0:0xbbb6ed7ce318b358"],"When":"2023-6-23"},{"Name":"Hasan Alezzi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocILiQqYpJ9Ad59Uw0Aw-8zFH3ehk6FJ0H4o8h-5DSWGuMf08w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has one of the best pizzas I have ever eaten. With a great deal of flavours, reasonable prices, and the great conversations I have with the staff who have many years in the pizza making industry (Serdar) this place has my heart. The days serdar works, the endless conversations I have with him truly make me feel appreciated not as a customer but as a person, and a friend. To all the pizza lovers, give this one a try!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sue McC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW06TagF1DBLI_AqSSOqwgpsIGwW0BIgdFbzbBu_C2VdtEyRU7N=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best, most delicious pizza! No where else compares to their genuine Italian flavour and perfect crust. Love U.B.C Pizza Garden. Sooo good!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"邱小峰","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLoTyUGOsKWbYXmDQE449thtUo6RvukmTHpOmRD68VDu-AOZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I live at UBC and had the chance to try it this Sunday for the first time. The pizza was really amazing. I asked a lot of questions while choosing my pizza, and the person who made it patiently answered all of them. The staff are great ！","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Callum Greene","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjih0-5fz2ont2vKOSI63GqVkhOR2CFeB97Ctb2WFiyv3dkQbG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I come in here multiple times per week, and I can't help but notice how friendly and kind everyone is. Serdar has been especially friendly, and I love coming here to eat. Highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""}]

The portion size is really big which was nice. service was ok. Their boba/ drinks menu is really good and worth checking out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCuCuRwLK5nl8Rf8uS_79T2EAGV1yo0FwSFhF6\u0026fid=0x0:0xb106d2d499f21350"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"Jonathan Tin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW--tm4xws8wH-RGwfFJsn6JJV78S1w-uWlu-Vb1VMH9K-MLh1f=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"What a lovely and innovative restaurant for the younger generations. Generous portion sizes that I could barley finish (for only $13.99, what a blessing for students), high quality soup and broth that is not filled with MSG and oil, and friendly staffs :) The ordering process was so simple, scan the QR code, add the items to cart, and confirm - No need to wave for attention! When I was there, if you order their rice noodles, you can order unlimited noodles refills as long as you are eating in store. Check out their menu and see for yourself!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkYlxvXEUw1k97OiKgGtjvr7phGR_GkhWSaBzk\u0026fid=0x0:0xb106d2d499f21350"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place slaps hard! The brown sugar mochi is very very good, and I also highly recommend their rice noodle with spicy sauce :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOHI5oCwjSI80nYvF8YnUS5Wwg6eMs3MG9jh2jT\u0026fid=0x0:0xb106d2d499f21350"],"When":"2023-6-30"},{"Name":"Hunter Lin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI34kPhtu-7rTv3BQRn-vQfVeWaOZClfgiB9-oYADKh-tzY3MZv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food is ok but the environment is so noisy with bubble tea machine working around. The taste is ok, I will say for the price you’re paying is worth it due to the big servings. There’s also an unlimited refill of noodles too but they took quite a long time to get us the refill.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXcVBk2g-9yOr6PQYYSSXdPC7yCRnvzMfML6dA\u0026fid=0x0:0xb106d2d499f21350"],"When":"2023-8-15"},{"Name":"Adison Zhang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJUHVKg_GuRcd0GLUjYbIBqjNX1GBuhBeVgfya2PM_BI6NlqQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I have been a regular for 2+ years. Best food but worst customer service, and they have mixed up my orders over 5+ times on Uber Eats. This time I was really annoyed because I only eat the noodles really spicy and I selected the spiciest option, but they barely gave me any spice. (I know how much spice they usually put in the noodles) I complained about it on Uber and they gave me a $5 credit when the noodles were $28 and I threw away the noodles. Another time they gave me some weird vinegar noodles instead of what i ordered and almost threw up because of how disgusting it was. DID NOT GIVE ME A REFUND OR REPLACEMENT. I don't even know why I keep ordering from this place their food is just too good 😞😞","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bottom line: it’s a great pizza for an affordable price (they often have promotions) on campus.

I got the “grab n go”: any small pizza and a pop for $10.99+tax. The Deluxe pizza was decent: crust was crispy, toppings filled the pizza, beautifully melted/charred in their XLT speed oven. And around the outer edge of the pizza is a heavy sprinkling of sesame seeds, which lends a texture like crunchy pizza dough. Kind of nice.

The online ordering platform tells you the order will take minimum 20 minutes, which was spot-on for my order. They also sell pizza by the slice for $2.38+tax in-store.

Best thing: they give you your takeout pizza in a cardboard box, so there’s no $0.25 bag fee!

The restaurant itself has probably 10 small tables—some inside, some outside—for eating there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDOuHiDIZTmdoXWax2rwLSqlNZvYhweoWLQ0nu&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Uncle Fatih's Pizza is one of the best pizza experiences I've had in Vancouver. When comparing price and taste, it's honestly way better than other chain pizza places. We ordered a medium Meat Lovers and a medium Eggplant Artichoke, and enjoyed both of them. The chipotle dip was a nice addition, though it's not very spicy. The pizza itself is juicy and full of flavors.

If you were to compare it to an authentic Italian restaurant in Downtown, I can't say for sure how it would hold up—I haven't tried that yet. But this place serves great pizzas with good quality. As long as the quality stays consistent, it will always be one of my favorite pizza places.

[Update, July 1, 2024]
We ordered an extra-large half-and-half pizza. One half was Sweet & Spicy Lovers, and the other was Eggplant Artichoke. We enjoyed both. The Sweet & Spicy Lovers pizza has pineapple slices, so if you enjoy the sweetness of pineapple on your pizza, it could be really nice. The spiciness comes from banana peppers, which are quite intense—I’d rate the spicy level 9/10 and usually avoid the banana peppers with the last pieces. The meat on the pizza was very nice, though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3LNwcz4Mhb2_rAOeKq6HQ2yu9c_abTPsvF_gY&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome bang for the buck – 20th anniversary deal was any slice for $2.38 plus taxes. Slice was of a regular size and adequately filled. Ingredientes were good quality and the cheese was pretty tasty. Service was friendly, but I guess overwhelmed because there were only two people working at the whole restaurant. Maybe this setup will only last during the summer vacations, but there were some people waiting to make their order on the line even then.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNr_x3LSgypONBL59pcXxllJnkv_odePZ2Iyp46&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Gurleen Mann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiPUG0uS2mNXBduiVsY6PVMjHnfxQ7NkDQyzxiXX7WnB_qcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m really glad I stopped here with my family for lunch. The staff were helpful and answered all my questions. We ordered a small garlic chicken pizza, small spicy chicken pizza and veggie lovers (gluten free small pizza). The entire order was made quickly and tasted very good with fresh ingredients and a soft dough. They also had some dipping sauces on the side. Would have been awesome if they had small containers to place them in, but that wasn’t a deal breaker. All in all one of the best pizza places I’ve had in a very long time!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jessy James","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYtH31UTkbDUolpuvM8YhvZp6aRqCRrozjZhpKhJHwBksolrRrhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went in as they were closing (which nobody likes I know! 🙈) but we had no where else that was opened so we gave it a shot!

The last 8-10 slices all assorted and they charged full price for everything. Almost $36 after tip for end of the night pizza was a little crazy IMO. However they did their best to give us a deal anyways, so we left a tip as much as we could.

The pizza was tasty, I would personally recommend the ham and pineapple! The others were great too but not as traditional in taste as they were a little more complicated in ingredients. Not a bad thing, I just like my pizza simple 🥰

Otherwise felt the food was very tasty and would return if they had better prices, maybe some Italian style/thinner/cheaper made slices could help things as a recommendation? I love my Italian traditional pizza style myself, but I know this place is more westernized and that's also okay.

Otherwise a good experience, just think end of the night slices are typically sold at a reduced rate. They did give us 8 slices and the 9th free, but I feel it could have been half off. Maybe I'm picky, idk 😆.

Overall good stuff! 🍕 Thanks!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"YVR Duke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbrjJ5U6gKw7Gn1zE_GlxhUndims9WHlh7sVaHLXVrjOFlYd_B=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I missed the old Pi[e]r² Pizza.
This is the closest we can get on campus.  Freshslice is ok but it just lacks a character.

Recommended for pizza lovers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOU3FmBdtQ7LMg_cBIVovU8hZILP6gYcvSoICF2&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Zay R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrcv0nbceihjzzaPr2LIIin5v_Tj9YhzMv8cvDTNxNVU0GSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I always order from them via Ubereats. Sometimes they do have good offers ‘buy 1 get 1 free’ on selected pizzas which is definitely better and cheaper, their prices are a bit pricey without the offer.
As for their crusts, they were always well cooked, soft and very tasty. I like their thin crust more.
Their pizzas are freshly made. I tried couple of veggie pizzas, they were all delicious. However, their bbq sauce is not the best (barely taste it)
This time I got pesto chicken pizza and it was good.My favorite is Garlic Lover Pizza!
Also I appreciate the fact they offer Halal chicken :)
Overall very good Pizza place","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNR6RA-QEUZg9mR9rrhkIy-hHpvwt5R5I40hL40&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2021-3-18"},{"Name":"Marcus Xiong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNKHkNu0r9L6u_s13vBOcHGIOl_tisn1xjH9tQbojiCd_NkDw-YQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a quick place to grab a meal, and the food isn't low quality either. The pizza is freshly made and rebaked when someone orders them. The food is brought up quickly. I like the unique sesame seeds on the crust, and adds extra flavor to the pizza. Sauce is rich, and the cheese and toppings are a nice addition.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONHV1r73zgfzQ_I6yWeRBU7_1WpRBMDqnxvZ2_&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2023-11-13"}]

[{"Name":"Beatrice Sebastian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUUwek93RSRQI7WTfEuNcqVL7HGmZluvzKeumWSk0H6j-wxN_r7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So many options and all of them good! I had the spicy veggie and avocado frittata, while my partner had the one with sausages in it! Packed with lots of flavour, and spicy enough where it’s not overpowering, but there is still a kick. We also had the chai latte and the Thai milk tea, the latter being my choice. The prices are very reasonable as well, and I left with extra","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMrV7r33OaiAb880nhUGDColmaJCXMDk_5rTOI&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Felipe Nardini Semedo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURszN0SB5gfUgG15JRA2VZnMKg9saOc8VB56_o8u8YD-YjWkyM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The place is very nice that is for sure, and the food was pretty good. The employees were kind and friendly. Though, it is quite expensive. Paid 15 dollars for this:","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUve_LEC5JMNxUojeXyKD3s4aLHWVChffsvrbP&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Rebecca Crean","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJffXx9jAHNGss4kYu6c34jLTh2TEgTCsOy2Ri5WTEPdAkIcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can not recommend this restaurant enough. Staff are always so welcoming and friendly. My personal favorite from the menu is the spicy egg ciabatta with bacon and avocado, with hasbrowns. It has to be the best lunch spot in UBC for sure!! Also, I have tried many of their Indian dishes, and they are so tasty and authentic. Butter chicken is amazing!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMR-lz9EE8USNUNZ7pDTmoKSZKRdbDkLAxGw5xW&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Ethaniel Chou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfW0x1CC0hsJlAWDv_pkaw3wzcOBSIvaLMpmRqZz5EHutkyWNl=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went in a few minutes AFTER closing without realizing that they were closed. They were so kind and offered to make eggs Benedict for me anyways, even though it was after closing time! The food was delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjgRxG3YdMn_U7cN7A3ThxuqiOpgxyGanjrio1&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We ordered two sandwiches. The turkey melt was nicely filled with turkey hams, cheese, and tomatoes, and it wasn't skimpy at all. For the pesto chicken and cheese sandwich, we chose the spicy version, but it was too spicy for our tastes, and not in a pleasant way. They serve frozen fries, which were unremarkable, so I might skip those next time. The portions were good for the price. Overall, we enjoyed our meal and plan to try other items in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjuWCCjG3bKAaRvShSvmkeAFyJhhm5ItRN4pFj&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Suha Khan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocINzwRxo4T3JStfrT3enCk3zn4WB4wfUp-_mi52cxtbb_WFgNA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really enjoy this small cafe along my campus quite a bit! The food is so authentic and quite flavourful. I’m from Mumbai so the Indian menu here definitely reminds me of home and the environment itself is absolutely friendly! The owner, Mr. Arwan is such a nice person, and he always greets me and asks me about my day and if the food was to my liking. If you’re looking for a unique, yet quiet place, this is definitely it! The food comes under 5 minutes to your table, and the amount is impressive. Worth every penny!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zaayer Nasib","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkh0fpj6mvCROx8j1Ux0TdNtszR1GgFfGTRvlt6JMDCheOJwvK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ratings Scale 0 - 10
Variety: 8
Service or Product: 7
Customer Service: 6
Environment: 6
Cleaning: 6
Washroom: 6
Cost: 4

While the food itself was decent, 2 factors made me give this page a 2 star rating:

Price: its too expensive! For a simple 2 person breakfast with tea, it cost us $42!!

Service: The service from the waitress and counter person were fine but another rude guy ruined the experience. I simply wanted to know ingredients of the cheese they use for my dietary restrictions. Instead of listening to me properly and guiding me he said he doesn't know. I asked if I could see the packaging and he said he threw the packaging out and then proceeded to leave without listening further. Pathetic. Will never visit again even though the food was decent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMq2SIcp5YKM2nN8KcchNCIq7FwbYOyHNtJ3iQV&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2019-3-12"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Five years living at UBC and I have been sleeping on this place. Finally stopped in to try their Indian food for lunch and was very pleasantly surprised. I had the Kadhi Onion Pakora Chawal and it was so good. Nothing too fancy, but just excellent Indian comfort food. I’m not in a place to say whether Indian food is “authentic” or not, but this was not the relatively bland take on Indian food that you might expect from this unassuming brunch place, it was pleasantly rich. And the paratha was so soft and flaky! The portion was also very filling, so good value for your money. I like that the Indian section of the menu has so many (vegetarian) breakfast dishes that most Indian lunch/dinner restaurants don’t serve. I’m kind of curious about the Western brunch menu too, but will definitely be back to try more of the Indian food if nothing else.
I had a Piña Colada smoothie too. It wasn’t bad, but it didn’t really do anything for me. They called this a “fruit smoothie” but it was so sweet and tasted closer to a flavoured slush to me. I'd skip the smoothie next time since the main meal was enough.
The atmosphere is totally bare-bones, it’s not sketchy or anything, there’s just absolutely no ambiance to speak of. The staff was nice enough though, especially the person taking orders at the front. It’s not a hip brunch place at all, but a great place for some no-fuss good eats. Although I can’t speak for the Western brunch stuff, I can definitely recommend you check them out for the Indian dishes if you live around UBC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGkL616_ijo3iJGYtqCaMmv43q99ohyD-11woA&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2022-9-11"}]
