user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went there for the grad students meeting and absolutely loved it! The place was packed with vibrant people which gave such an energetic atmosphere. Staff was very friendly and contributed to the experience. The beers were great and the burger I had was good enough – not very large but also not expensive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDgBUdvc8jRuHppQfgKjuHI0zVR3S0Q2HrSskp&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Aileen Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtnbeuRSCrTtTivdNIO4OHLKHO_ilmZOOqqMZVCM5535PBeWYx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had our wedding at Koerner's Pub two weekends ago and we are beyond happy with the venue and how everything turned out! Caroline did such a great job with communication throughout the whole process and making whatever we wanted to do a reality. When we first booked, they said they're very flexible and can customize our wedding however we liked, and they really meant it! We added a signature cocktail a couple of months before the wedding and they made it happen with no hesitation. We are just blown away by how accommodating they are. We wanted a cozy, intimate, laid back wedding with the ceremony on the open patio and a cocktail style reception with canapes, platters and food stations and they more than delivered on that. The outdoor space is just beautiful surrounded by the tall trees, the atmosphere inside was absolutely perfect and the food was delicious! Our guests raved about everything! I could not recommend Koerner's Pub enough!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSpoODXsooMuueBjFMVUbAncCRWmoP1B6ORPuo&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2023-11-7"},{"Name":"Jerry J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9DQ7B_TRq3u3bo5NkgYrIEp3oIpu1Uv2owPApsfpA107EzZBD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Don’t come here for the food. They “only do two things, tacos and burgers, but hey do those well” according to the staff on duty - LOL 🫠

The burger patty was as thin and crispy (smashed burger) as the one tiny stripe of bacon that you get for an additional $2.50 - for me, the smashed thing is mainly a cost saving measure. No lettuce or fresh tomato, just the mushy bun and greasy undercooked fries, all served on a plastic tray (no plate) to give it the perfect canteen finish.

The person at the counter did not want to be here (bad day for them it seems). Deco and atmosphere is ok, nice garden/patio. Beer and water good.

In summary, the place called Freshii at Wesbrook and this pub battle for the bottom of the list of eating out on campus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMV5sDHilMGHK49b7Ep2ceOcuYUZ4P5cInKnkPf&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Nat D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVq59Bz_Kc8jFzJNz9bEb180ByB9AU4nY2IRQXQnfI8npN0Tz_3=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Koerner’s pub is my go to for the BEST vegan tacos in the city! 🤤🌮 As a tasty side dish, be sure to order their yummy fries smothered in vegan mushroom gravy - truly heavenly! 😋 The prices and portions are very fair as well. The staff is always super warm and welcoming, and I greatly enjoy the pub ambience as well as the large patio surrounded by the lush greenery and mature trees. On a side note, be sure to check in advance to see if the pub is open as sometimes they host special events and will close for the day. This place is truly a hidden gem!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPV3UKCC0-8HY8nb3tMBs5r1g2Yp3mZ1z7ifA-D&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2022-8-2"},{"Name":"Jess A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQcaZCQGrB5OVS66pu43CkqxqUxwzuyGP2ki5075OI4cgNK_DdiA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had our wedding ceremony and reception at Koerner's this past weekend. It was one of the best nights of our lives, in no small part to the staff at Keorner's. Ana, the venue coordinator, is on top of everything and was an invaluable resource. She responded quickly to all our communications, and went the extra mile to fulfill every request, including accomodating allergies and liasing with vendors to get the site setup just how we wanted.

The venue looked stunning - more beautiful that we could have imagined. It is an idyllic setting. It looking like our own little forest oasis! We had a night ceremony and it felt right out of a Midsummer Night's Dream.

The food was exceptional. I wish the chef had a restaurant we could eat at all the time! Our guests were comfortable and happy the whole night. The staff were attentive and fun. The beers they had on tap were awesome - even my favourite, Four Winds saison! We really can't say enough good things.

It was fun getting to know the venue - we visited a few times in the leadup, and hung out eating burgers and tacos. The vibe is great. We will be back as customers and look forward to attending one of their drag nights someday soon!

Big recommend and lots of love for this place!! <3","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsoFuH2exuiAgDyAF2BAIjMYZg0qGUDYavAiXb&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2022-8-29"},{"Name":"Nanook Bearkiller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGd-lKZGiw3s1Cstm96X_oNJSIZl-bTkcRWm3S82g26MG6YQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Really poor service.
Went there at 12:30 pm. I had to wait for one full hour only to receive my burger. And then had to devour it without really tasting the damn food because my class was starting. This team is not good enough to be on campus. They're severely short staffed with inexperienced undergraduate students serving tables of 6 people. But with absolutely no competition around, they survive on monopoly.
I don't think I want to go there ever again. I try to change my friends' minds too if they suggest this place for any sort of gathering.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jason wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAr7OPM3u3i7bBkh0r7Q9kS7_8Gu_88Crv223BgydShD66TQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very good taco’s but the the menu is very limited.. Very crowded on the weekends.. very hip hang out for the UBC students..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMK9pm6ZuPgIIUqe-PBzrXbwWZ2KyumEdlGl06e&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2024-3-16"},{"Name":"Daniella Stewart","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJvrtZ9JggwDL2AwQ_WItI2VaTglWpBeElIlHroHM6ga-UoOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"**Beautiful Wedding Venue***
We recently had our wedding at Koerner's Pub and we are so happy with that decision. The location is beautiful, Loafe catering was delicious, and Marcela and her team were great.
Having our wedding at Koerner's made for an easy day with no extra travel for ourselves or our guests between the ceremony and the reception. It felt intimate in the garden ceremony with a beautiful backdrop for photos. The tables already at Koerner's provided a simple and elegant feel that didn't require a ton of decorations which made for easy planning. Multiple guests came up to share how delicious the food was (we definitely recommend the flank steak with chimichurri).
Would highly recommend considering Koerner's for your wedding!","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Carlson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfSH3Mvx6Gquzf2h2Yz13MuXUcH81ASX8ObjzRJu92XMv3J9M3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really enjoy the decor and atmosphere of the place! The prices are not bad for a place in UBC and they have great specials on different days of the week. You can even get a can of hard iced tea for $3 on Wednesdays! The food was pretty good as well and service was quick. Definitely a cool hangout spots for students","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyTwuCZccSL-7X42Ctxdh6oCHq4iBc2RWWDEgi&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-9-17"},{"Name":"Anson Leung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLpRG7sV65M0Vk9fJln2fqg-G8cTgdbnIHe6i_26HAHg5rk2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This was the second time coming here for the all you can eat pasta.  Unfortunately, the policies have changed and a beverage and gratuity is added, very fair, since I was told that some didn't tip, so the policy changed from this week. From this visit, the sauce amount has decreased, and the pasta has gone from al dente to harder, basically raw pasta.

The first plate of pasta was almost perfectly al dente but still slightly under what I preferred, and was still a treat to enjoy.  After the first plate, I had asked if the pasta could be made softer for the next.  They said that it would not be possible since the pasta is par-cooked.  However, for the next 2 plates, the pasta got harder and harder until I tasted flour and I decided to cut into one.  Well, it was raw inside (photo included).  At this point after 2.5 plates of hard pasta, I didn't feel like asking for it to be remade since they told me before that it wasn't possible.

Overall, the food experience was marginally unacceptable after the first plate. The service was good and the sports bar atmosphere was excellent.   I recommend the rigatoni alla vodka sauce for the all access pasta since it tastes the best, pesto the second.

After the complaint, I was told there had been a miscommunication that the pasta couldn't be cooked longer, and the drink cost was taken off as a result.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMb5h3FMgcqIKIxfIJ4PYZyyEEGjALlZXy1MfK1&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Simon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWq3mMD7x0QRiQPROCB5BEqtJbykKAfvm5IFcPhyVt8QiitDIxq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I got introduced to this place by a foodie influencer  (Howie) and got to enjoy a lot of their food. This visit, however, was solo and only just on a Monday evening so it wasn't very busy inside. There is  outdoor patio seating which is was my preference.

I ordered the Steak Sandwich which came with EXCELLENTLY crisp fries and a small dipping sauce. If you ask for any kind of hot sauce, they will charge you $1.50 - SO BE CAREFUL! The Steak  Sandwich was *absolutely* delicious! The taste from the AAA medium-rare flat iron Steak with the  goat cheese and bbq sauce had such a really nice, umami flavour and mouth feel. It was just so delicious!

I also ordered a Nashville Chicken Sando. No pictures taken as the first bite literally made me devour it on the spot! Will definitely come back again to take a photo.

Overall, I had a great experience at Sports  Ilustrated Clubhouse. Nothing to say about their  interior or service.

Definitely recommend although I will say most items in the menu is quite expensive for the value. About 10-20% more expensive than what I consider reasonable price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZ_l_-O0YA_6zwiOUN1AOIRb233AEnDOfUPpUz&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Nai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIReum1hobq8yy8xS95oLeLTMWqUAVsUqS3FQjvLQXW9PrM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I’ve been here twice during the day-time and the service was great both times, I came with two friends during the evening yesterday as it was their first time and we thought it would be a fun place to come to in our own neighbourhood; however, the service last night was not it! We left feeling uncomfortable. The server made it seem like we were a bother, she gave two of us the wrong bills granted we should have double checked but we couldn’t because we felt rushed… the Attempt of a pleasant interaction was only when we were paying our bills and we left feeling really bad at that service! Mind you, we left at around 8pm and the restaurant was not busy. She wasn’t welcoming at all from the start. We were still all smiles though. For my friends that came there for the first time, I don’t think they appreciated last nights service. It kinda sucks cause I was happy that they could finally come there. It takes one little experience like that to throw you off! I appreciate the server the times I’ve been there during the day though, she was great! Food is good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lou CB","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiUtEy3y60GPfgpVV5JSZrfFEBJi2Q16v4jzANAcFWH_TE0GBffw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We had the BLT sandwich which came with fries and a salad, and the sizzling brownie. The BLT was well seasoned with quality bacon, generous amounts of tomato and shredded lettuce and the fries were tasty and crispy. The brownie was served with a scoop of vanilla ice cream. Good solid food in a bright clean space — ambience very different from when it was a pub, and some will miss the vibe! Still, will be back to try other items on the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNh087caXrJbS0HKIa3aQ2-peVfgUHsyIosCQ2v&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2023-12-9"},{"Name":"Mahsa Haghjoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRSnT0Wip7Pbg6Z8m0cglGHkWd61YfkTkUIlG6b0IkPWIUcJi2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"If you are in the village you might wanna check out this place. Food was delicious, plenty of seats and you can even sit outside. Food was good","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5VsJRScu6NCdsyshKWhhH-ZIiDoIN1Y9DqH8-&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-9-26"},{"Name":"Elaine S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXw0NZVlw-DYhg6yu3CwCqawu2sEc8yv_yDRJNRZHiHpXsjuXCx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A couple of days ago I met with my BFF for a much-needed catch up. We started off at the UBC Botanical Gardens and then she suggested Sports Illustrated Clubhouse for lunch.

It was a quiet afternoon which made the atmosphere perfect for us for a wonderful visit, and the food was great. The best part was the incredible service by Emi! She was such a lovely person, so friendly, and she took such great care of us!

My friend and I shared the truffle fries (they were sooo good!) and house salad. And Emi recommended the perfect beer - my new favourite - Main Street Brewing Hula Hula Tropical Sour!

Thank you Emi - you made the visit with my bestie so special!! We will be back! XX","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkqcVOmUrER6YSL3yQW180GcblcqGtJukGWVDB&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Eugene Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvb9M5oHuuuLu9F3QxDe3Xu-5rsVsCB6BayNIPfvQOtlwnoIIv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a great place to watch a game. They have a massive screen above the bar flanked by smaller ones next to it, then more around the corner. There are also several TVs throughout other areas so there are almost no bad tables

The food was pretty good for the most part. Other than the guacamole being a bit bland and not as creamy as I’d expect (maybe they did a chunky style on purpose?), we enjoyed everything else. My Nashville Chicken Sando was awesome (normally I don’t think much of coleslaw in a sandwich but it really worked with this one). The brussel sprouts with bacon was awesome as well. My friends enjoyed their burgers and Caesar salads while their regular fries were extra crispy and tasty (it’s got some seasoning on it and isn’t just plain salted).

The drinks menu was pretty big and there are a lot of beer options.

The server was friendly and attentive despite a packed house for the Canucks/Kings game.

We’ll definitely be back for more games and meals.

Sorry for the sad food photo; we were focusing on the game too much. 😃","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPmEGUSnxAI5BuksllsLzdLs3sDJ4ayGy7dA9vP&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-3-1"}]

[{"Name":"Jeff Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVeVKpdfNOdTnoZ-ITkSuOW-c2zXalTP1RiXc0xiQ5ZEZBSpWaGw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I’m a huge fan of Xi’an cuisine so I got the Cumin Lamb Noodles. This was dressed in a fragrant chilli oil sauce, and was decently spicy/numbing. (The kind that makes you sweat and blow your nose mid-meal). Generous portion of thicker hand-pulled noodles and sliced lamb, and only a handful of gratuitous veggies at the bottom. This is a heavier option for a meal so be warned. Decent value for $15+tax. Only wish it was tad less greasy and included more veggies. Service was super friendly!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsGHmIHxKdxVTdO5K1hvrNzisuObOdV8gOpEDr&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Josh J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXe42PdxuYHUOJL_X8RN0pr9xXBVzrdppHzz1uqjoxioU06wUY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered a Beef Fried Rice Noodle. The entire bowl had only a handful of beef (around 3-5 pieces). The rest is bean sprouts. Literally around 500g of bean sprouted on my bowl. And doused in so much oil I can't taste anything but the oil.

I get that there's cost cutting measures but this is just inexcusable for the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNShl1CT87CReQzrVfSvBSP_m74OWBFYD5Au1Tf&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-8-7"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered two dishes, one with two toppings and one with three toppings. The base was fried rice with vegetables, which was tasty. Our favorite topping was the sweet and sour chicken, followed by the spicy fried shrimp. I'm not a fan of beef brisket, so I didn't enjoy it as much, but it wasn't bad at all. The tofu and fried chicken were also good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYn5ivfW57olI8tk1-SStvN0ONJf03iQ8hIsij&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-3-23"},{"Name":"Serena Jiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdrdumUkGSxjbtk1_LQZc0knhS2eGprfXet3quGlQUesHypA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food was lukewarm and you could see oil coagulating in the trays. I understand it’s made earlier in the day but shouldn’t fast food at least be served hot considering people are eating it right away? Also I’m clearly getting tiny portions of the items compared to the photos here and from the reviews saying “generous portions/ good portion for the price”. To be fair I could imagine the braised beef tasting really good for tray food if it’s hot, hence one more star than this experience deserves.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNl6gVMVsuDEnQrnqEc4lczMnKqKGZ-0QpTvEE9&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-5-5"},{"Name":"Thanh To","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVd1WYJP1UmnIbSg76XorhMDMrCl48AkAncBIVkE7p0lcIIllbB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Not sure why all the hate but Sesame probably gives the most bang for your bucks on campus. The food is consistent and the portions are huge. Sure, the Chinese food in the international basement is cheaper but at least here you can see how clean the kitchen is. That said, prices have increased within the last few months. Also, come near closing for a discount.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzwl9JXPv3noDGVsPFDwOkpgy-9dPOYukS4_lY&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2023-9-11"},{"Name":"Rhiannon Wallace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAx5QcOsQKCDu6tdQ5r1AX6YB3HZHIwCoaxkohXBCloCBZAxbs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food was prepared super quick so I’ll give them one star for service. I ordered the pad Thai with tofu. Portion size was large so one star there. The tofu was super dry and tasted like barbecue sauce so slightly disappointing. Overall food was average. Not likely to stop here for lunch again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwDsKfzc3kuo7Bobehbl0uPU2QObRCrtyoMp7I&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2023-8-21"},{"Name":"E Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKy2o0HCNtv9vy3r48TF8rMzRuC3IjPPUXtIN5-DUX13g-Qqww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Really wonder where do the good reviews came from- we tried 3 dishes and all tasted like fast food.

Chicken with super thick batter not much chicken; frozen fried rice heated up. Sad veggie.

Lamb noodle taste like boiled noodles mix with sauces that’s all.

The menu photos look very tasty so that’s impressive, taste is no where near what the photos look like","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8D90SHV6CanI8GDvaEvc126_8yL3DphT7o50_&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2021-10-1"},{"Name":"Afindi Useng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURvlo3nZ4dDsYeBdJVxIo4OKsPCbGpPRUkFRo_W8UXjbvU9qFr=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I went in today and ordered their Mapo Tofu and was extremely disappointed by the food and service. What they served me was tofu cooked with peas, carrots and corn over rice. The description on their website says that it's "tofu in savoury and spicy sauce with white rice" and what I got was definitely NOT that. The worst part was that when I went back to the store and asked them if they got the order wrong and if they could fix it they just turned me down and argued that this was what it's supposed to be.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJfXtVta3AhH3AEpWaACERvuzzWr_SxMTKjoUT&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2021-9-26"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Miyuki Food","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIefbmBJIFd8vluRG1CtvO_cHUxsRdwtm3bVobO6E-icLpG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food comes very fast, portion size seems smaller than before. And there’s only 1 type of baked pasta a day (it was fine though). Garlic toast was fine, the salad dressing was great!! Pasta and garlic toast for 11 dollars is alright. UBC cinnamon bun was tasty but hard, maybe it was from the day before. I want to try the roast chicken leg next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTB5iX6q9Xe2yx-tVSbqgor_6fP9oxY5cREcs&fid=0x0:0x1edd3bffb80ccd29"],"When":"2024-3-25"},{"Name":"April Kang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpjudrVHdeiNcmDBFdIqiSbVKaOOs-ms-BSD_TFGabSaEbLhkK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The server was busy cleaning and didn’t take my order right away. So I was waiting for her to finish her cleaning until she can finally take my order. It was a little bit awkward, but no big deal. Then I ordered a cup of earl grey latte. It came super hot with no lid or sleeve cup holder. I only had one free hand to hold the drink. While holding the drink and walking to a table, I spilled and burned myself. I don’t want to complain, but I think the server really needs some safety training regarding hot drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMvMzTQlQO5LNRU9akNZ9JACjxxTMjIqf6AQtZ&fid=0x0:0x1edd3bffb80ccd29"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I seem to remember the pasta here being better… I had the Alla Norma today for the first time in a long while and was disappointed to get a stereotypical university cafeteria meal. The pasta sauce was fine and there were lots of veggies, so the dish likely would have been decent if it was cooked properly, but the pasta and vegetables were over-cooked and mushy, presumably from sitting in a hot-holding unit for who knows how long. The garlic bread was soaked and then some in butter. There was enough pooled in the nooks of the bread that I could just tip the bread over and pour it off. It’s not like the food was phenomenal before, but I thought it was good enough for a quick-service cafe, but this was just lazy.
The baked goods are still the same as you get at other UBC cafes, which I’m mostly a fan of. I find that the decaf espresso in drinks has kind of a burnt taste; it’s alright in lattes, but I had it as an americano today and it wasn’t really worth it for me.
On the upside, the value is decent. The pastas and flatbreads are heartier fare than you’ll find at most of the coffee shops (UBC-owned or not) around campus, and my pasta and (big) cookie today came out to about $14 total. The service is usually friendly enough and the space is nice. They have dine-in plates and mugs but you need to specifically request them - they will not ask you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9ttobxFHARwLEw1f2WIn8975E7NUIg_MlZcrK&fid=0x0:0x1edd3bffb80ccd29"],"When":"2023-1-29"},{"Name":"Mahish Rajdev","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTK_NiWhybybG5OSaEBGMB4IPAR1DXKbumCjO5eTpafLGTEMHWRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Pure and absolute garbage! Service was diminishing and incredible rude, to then have a disgusting, cold pastry with a coffee  that was made with an old shot she had laying around! Didn't even cared to be sneaky.
Even tim's is better than this waste.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very good cafe to have a quick bite or takeout on campus! The prices are reasonable, and they have plenty of study space around as well. I highly recommend their barbecue chicken flatbread :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbNWTbTPrSs7CWgWXbrxFwMFw1NvcN3g4MK4Fm&fid=0x0:0x1edd3bffb80ccd29"],"When":"2023-10-25"},{"Name":"Fei B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCSPR4b-Aju_3xzgvNmgK79_SKNPWkqhiQHmMJksqE4GdZMXE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"pretty decent food prices and they take UBC card here (at least when I last tried!)
I like the soups here as a filling and warming snack between my classes here. The pastas are pretty decent, but nothing special here. When I lived on campus, this was my favourite alternative to eating residence food!
The cashiers/servers here are honestly pretty unfriendly. Recently went and ordered soup and the lady didn't even look at me or say anything to me the entire time...not sure why.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ashley Xinyue C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIYz5MDYrhb1L2Ntf7XrdjiB5xemPws8aSeONm3ZAcvtG13jw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Really nice and juicy chicken but drip coffee is always cold","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Graham Douglas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIhuQ7JFTpvGa5zi_15HH4FFQnLd20ANHeexPlC6QR2fUoaZ3XVA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It’s a fine little cafe. Nothing really great or bad. The drip coffee is pour yourself which makes it fast when there is a crowd. It’s not the freshest coffee around though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMx4debrcztXIVIujqqYuB5b32E7-zG52FVWZ0t&fid=0x0:0x1edd3bffb80ccd29"],"When":"2018-6-1"}]

While the spring rolls were a tad oily, they were still enjoyable. However, the highlight was definitely the potato BBQ stick - it was spicy and utterly amazing! Overall, it was a fantastic dining experience that I would highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew Nichiporuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMUo7vJRTLjS5Vph1J5OjCQjPWsKGPlNJaI4FKpAmzwqfqZMPt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Definitely one of the best places to eat on campus. My only comment is I wish the spicy options were spicier. Friendly service, good value, and the fries are fantastic.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAsRUwM1kr5fYWMaPSOwtGOGh-_MAyOOzjDYfokhHY8k5IaUlm=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food is generally tasty here but I ordered delivery that was not delivered properly (never received the order) and when Ubereats (which was fulfilling the order) told me the restaurant was responsible for a refund, I informed them of this and they disagreed and refused to refund the order. If you want to throw away money at food that does not arrive and get zero customer service then order here\n\nEDIT: they did follow up and resolve it the next few days. It ended up being a fair resolution, but it was difficult in the moment because of uber. So good experience overall from the restaurant itself","Images":null,"When":""}]

I've never received such poor service in my life.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chris Call","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrKpicJlOGcEVE9WGUUdPmVFwru8M5H3WG_2_Aa35MnTzCLrQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"It's not the worst McD's in the city, but it's hopelessly overwhelmed. The staff can't handle it without burnout so they take it easy. I understand. Thing is, this area needs at least 2 McD's to serve the demand, frankly, it needs 3 or 4 of them. Regional management has had to be called in to deal with it before. Again, it's not the worst McD's in the region. It's not the best. It just can't begin to hope to cope with the volume. I've been to all the locations many times. Blenheim is the best in the city.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"I Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLvZ12JjwhqSTUOG1fhxcRBN5niWD0vOtNoQHx2VV4jUys_6g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Food not bad, same as other branches. [{"Name":"لجين علي عبدالله","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJknstfVQBYVOicM756T8lGplERKL0_UBI-91D2Lx8i3wQBxzk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was nice spot to have breakfast after a long walk. Order the spinach and eggs benny and tomatoes and chives omelette.
Didn’t try the coffee (which I regret) but my friend had English tea and it was great!
I liked the food but didn’t love it, need more spices from myside to hit that sweet spot.

Loved the view and it has great atmosphere, very relaxing place and would visit it again.

Also, use the front door entrance of the club, it also leads to the restaurant, don’t need to go around for the stairs entrance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMETZkxZHuffXBSBsYx-EvpU3vpLe7F4XwpUHnt&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Ben M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLY7-DFsqx-InW5CnlXpJd6DWvP1u6nfShJnLWMiHPMX_9EZw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great place for lunch in a sunny day. The view is beautiful. The shepherd's pie, mashed potato on the pie, and the sandwich are all very good. The French fries are so so.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOeS23iArM7RRGT9MMGW-BLlqdTh458oebRv1Dp&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2024-6-8"},{"Name":"P G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0fCU2Qc0a_c6EyAnrC9oWHMXOLKbAIpYaZPyN9xTdV9lbUoGm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice spot on a sunny afternoon/evening and food is quite ok (used to be better but maybe recent visit was a blip), just service is lacking and that’s a constant","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0IdqGqVO6XZ26pKrpEN0UmMy9Yc_gm_xQbLJh&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Lil Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDgF8p2j50UmJKzkx4VadmKu8Ao0Nvxlfi-pi40gh9UM4OrRn61w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice place. Pricey but not excessive for a nice patio golf course. Great view overlooking a garden with a bridge and stream. My husband had a decent burger, I had a turkey BLT sandwich with wholegrain (nice touch), our friend who invited us had an avocado salad. Second time this year dining here. Only complaint is their lunch menu does not start until 2pm by then most people had left!?! There were several young ladies serving us but sometimes have to flag them down but once you got them, they were really friendly and even recommended dating apps for our friend. LoL 😂","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzxDJvkBMo7yIDx75UBzMcOykNPDaOoc2-cWEz&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2023-8-2"},{"Name":"Jasmeher Kathuria","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRPxourZkFGqspJqITB0BgxzAESvenlWO0L3A_jSAljqDI09n1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The short rib rigatoni and the apple pie are my go to dishes. Always order them whenever I go and am greeted by welcoming staff members.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOm84TuBZ6_Hanftej6Q9Qh1oBHQJWYDM1JM6Vk&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2024-6-9"},{"Name":"No MSG No Garlic Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-PVOn6GcWxsKb-qqVJDTqvJ5rfua5QVuFocwcMF-ZRwuEIPLm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The points for this review is purely for the pleasure of sitting outside on a 2nd floor patio overlooking expansive area of green lawn, gardens and forest. I am also grateful for the non-metal chairs!
It was 27°. We've just been cooling in the forests of the beautiful UBC Botanical Garden and not quite ready to drive back to the city. Westward Ho at the UBC Golf Course came up on my Google search for brunch. Their patio picture was the deciding factor. Since it was nearly Happy Hour, the pub wasn't crowded and we were able to get a table in the impressively big patio. Not sure if it would be equally impressive had it been a really sunny day. We'd have to check that out another time. On this cloud day, the patio was very bright – almost to the point where I have to put on my sun glasses.
As for the food, we had a hard time choosing: fresh fish and chips, fish sandwich, Beyond Beef burger, all day breakfast, etc. I ordered a Club House with multigrain yam fries, my companion ordered fresh Cod and Chips. The bread in my Club House was dried out, the sandwich did not look as scrumptious as the one with sour dough presented to the table next to us. My sandwich was too 'orderly', the chicken did not spill out of the sandwich like the one I saw earlier. I enjoyed the cod fish though – very fresh and not over battered. So, I guess I ordered the wrong thing! I liked the choice of using vinegar on coleslaw instead of mayo. A decent size coleslaw for a more balanced meal. MSG? For a few hours afterwards, I was very thirsty, but did not get the usual sickly feeling from eating MSG. So, not sure what was in the food that caused my tongue to feel so dry.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjr8zNCvHQWWPDvIvCsF-m8vfK6OTg8xyORYzH&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2021-8-2"},{"Name":"Azi Jahan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVoCqSGFWxXVxJxNnyUrYmJjWJKEtREeG-G0RXpmBRv8kbELxEL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"For gulf lovers for sure, it's a well-known place.

Beautiful location and view🤌🏻
Delicious brunch
So kind and supportive staff

It's a peaceful weekend brunch location if you are looking for a calm weekend's brunch🤩","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4NKPC_4N4_VYCzznfOGLy34Q4VWIecJtPF0BY&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2022-7-29"},{"Name":"Paul Rogers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-2DEuMMhV7vJRExrjz5OPFG99Ya8EpWqhlLnkXnZqRJpDqw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My family went here with a few other people for dinner.  Nice staff (hence the 2 stars) but the food was very disappointing.  Out of the 3 in my family, none of us enjoyed our meals.  I had the fish tacos which were bland and mushy.  I would not recommend this restaurant.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Adil OKUMUŞ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWILc9czCClsi1y9wPizaOjmclU9tapIH8_ES7EWExaSXRNOBnE2g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The udon noodles lack firmness and that chewy texture you’d expect from it. The noodles here taste more like thick cut pasta boiled in water as the base has no taste to it as well. Though California rolls were tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgpY5DR5Gc-JXB-ZTL7HY7s60-DKODDDDNCMen\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can't say enough, but Nori bento is one of the most affordable and high-quality restaurants on campus if you're interested in Japanese food. From the bento options, I like the beef and katsu. For me, the bento is enough for two portions, but I usually eat less than a normal person, I think. The spicy udon noodles with spicy laska broth was nice, and my friend had a good experience. The spicy level for me was 8/10, but it was a nice kind of spiciness, so I definitely recommend it if you like spicy food. The sushi is also nice, but you need to visit the store in person as they're not available for delivery. We usually include one sushi roll, and they're always fresh and good. Also, they have nice staff, and they're pretty quick as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZrb_SeHHHdWxIoRXfkxukBgJQdtKYocmxBAFA\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2024-5-7"},{"Name":"Wei x","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_gqktxpcwm5-Ae9lvoeXAyfIgSzBgJfFmiGs2nilpJU5Zx6z7jw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Perfect place for a quick and inexpensive meal at a nice location. The place is  self serve. Order and pick up at the counter. Clean after done. Service is fast. The food has a good portion and is reasonably good for the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMyeadNAJAius8I8O1Mq2mHcpkypIT90B9ehVhh\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Hashan Peiris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQS5tXYmTSP8F6gc8CzViRW9uUkD3rHwc2GCIQJ7tX0r6Ne1oo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They have a good variety of food. Portion size and the temperature of food is good. Prices are reasonable and one of the best place in the area to taste Asian cuisines. I bought a bento box which came with a miso soup and some crab katsu. All of those were good in taste, portion size and temperature. I would love to try their other dishes and will keep you updated about them.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuATPhm51u0grXUAdBBxtTK-Z6qFsSoqfOzEJl\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2023-7-4"},{"Name":"Lil Crisis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUf-SqiEXi0v2ZRyt3xQxN2DW5nEhVrpSV4y3-tDyj00BCugBTa=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The noodles were pretty soft as if they were over cooked and the Kimchi Mentaiko Udon had very little kimchi in it, no green onion like the photo, and was warm rather than hot like you might expect it to be. I never waste good but had to throw out about half because I couldn’t bring myself to eat the rest of it","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Adrian Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJRz_uEV8AM70-EugybmCMjVZLIi0OfMP3My2LKS1PidWwGuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Deep fried teriyaki chicken. The chicken was crispy and crunchy and the portion was large. The tempura was also deep fried really crispy as well, in fact a bit too much in my opinion. Unique take on the normal Bento box. Salad was nice, California roll a bit lacking avocado. Overall really good value and probably the best Japanese on campus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMIeZ7EeRQsBlOSo1rGaRmqodc4UTnNmPZOLFnE\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2021-6-25"},{"Name":"w","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVECjtzjKwGGU2yagM5sH2sMNpUPFv0VdGQBZqvehtzvpFlyVDi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely bussin. Portion sizes are huge for the banging price. Food was ready 90 seconds after we ordered. Recommend the tonkotsu ramen.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNte3JWgReq0dfvd3nnvI63ELOzijrfb4q1Cjw_\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2022-12-20"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"It gets the job done if you have a craving for bento or sushi, but not the greatest. Portion size is okay, but everything is a little lacking in flavour and the rice and croquettes are pretty greasy. On some occasions the food has been better than others - I've never had a terrible experience here, but the quality floats around just alright to underwhelming. Service is also slower than I would expect for fast food, although the staff is nice. Again, though, it's good for satisfying a craving for Japanese comfort food if you don't have the time to go somewhere nicer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9ZNX2nVv53JUypILVN9dAbQQqy4GsB19SiOfB\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2021-2-3"}]

There's a good variety of options for the build-your-own bowls, ingredients are all fresh, and you can make some really tasty stuff.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPv3oqwVy0RLQ31MXkFigs_biZFWBN6jOG_Bit8\u0026fid=0x0:0x811ed40a9e945c43"],"When":"2021-10-2"},{"Name":"Chloe Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgExGuK1W-XgQc1tPnrQlqQkWxCTaNhdz977uVTTY3zjpsAzs-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great spot for healthier eats at UBC. I liked how easy it was to identify which options were vegan on the order sheet. I tried their vegan bacon and found it very salty, so would order a different protein next time around. Service was friendly!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7Yuy1PSgJyWRhI2c_32pcPDPMJebZyNiTnkWD\u0026fid=0x0:0x811ed40a9e945c43"],"When":"2022-10-23"},{"Name":"Steve Morgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmgrmzSyB3CC_qWamR3pXmaZna6-RxfqDluiFzTGNrypDReGc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This healthy option at the Nest allows you to custom tailor veggie bowls etc. The upside is that you get what you want. It comes free with brown rice if you'd like, and you get to choose your protein (the tofu is great!). The lineup is often long as the cashiers have to enter every ingredient you chose into their system but once your order is through it's quite quick. Worth trying if you're on campus.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alan Small","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKzLTrQnMjgBTtPZOLeWQyRNTv1apzwevnTMT_sb6y76t2nQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Waygu bowl with garlic chili or Chipotle sauce are DELICIOUS!! Maybe it was just this dish but seems like their ingredients were not fresh. Had stomach ache and cramps afterwards for hours.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Mostly rice with minimal side dishes. Would not recommend for the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEUJhyI1F-QPkD901l5ErcplyHAJE5DwPakWFQ\u0026fid=0x0:0xcf2b135094694222"],"When":"2023-8-14"},{"Name":"Ethan Zhang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjVKUxlEohxEizpTIfFkqep7gFOVNbAECr-jCSoo6uSIhlyOI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"TL, DR: quite authentic Chinese food with good portions, get whatever’s fresh out the kitchen.\nPretty authentic Chinese food that is higher than mall food court level and slightly lower than a good restaurant. The food is tasty and 15 dollars for a meal that can keep you going for at least 6-8 hours. My recommendation is to get whatever just came out; as once I was lucky to just go when they were refilling their sweet bell pepper fried chicken it was really a solid restaurant level. The crust was still crunchy and covered with sweet and sour sauce while the chicken was juicy and tender. I really recommend this place.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Steve Morgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmgrmzSyB3CC_qWamR3pXmaZna6-RxfqDluiFzTGNrypDReGc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fantastic sandwiches made to order, but expect long lineups from 11:30 to 1:30. Most members of the staff are friendly and quick, though some not so much. Prices (of hot food in particular) are a bit high for students, but that doesn't appear to deter crowds.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNpce1YcD1VUdaLqbvUnWhU2943HqxabsilhxY\u0026fid=0x0:0x8f55d57f925022a2"],"When":"2017-7-6"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has everything: curries, fresh sandwich bar, paninis and wraps, baked goods, coffee/tea, and packaged items to grab and go. The curries are tasty and pretty good quality for fast food. The portion is very filling, especially if you add naan. The veggie panini is really good with fresh ingredients. I also really like all of their desserts. Some of the items are more snack-size but most of their cookies/bars are huge.\nIt gets super busy at lunch time, and because there's so many counters and not a ton of space, it can be difficult to figure out where to stand, but the staff is helpful in directing you if you're confused. The service is generally friendly and efficient.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfu8xFtp31SbafS8exo8vtV3PxU4WDHonOiRtz\u0026fid=0x0:0x8f55d57f925022a2"],"When":"2021-10-18"},{"Name":"J P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJPNOwczxQeYq8Qup51h2PTCgzkWZZqiOeXeOFsoHWK1IWAROM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The line ups are very long during lunch hour. The prices are pretty high. If you get a half and half they still charge you for the higher costing item. Chaotic. The NEST doesn’t have many great food options (atleast not on a students budget). The food quality is average.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKmfPg0wMwMMlY1z0OpBGl6AV2fLqkXWwWiZcO\u0026fid=0x0:0x8f55d57f925022a2"],"When":"2017-9-27"},{"Name":"TK","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtNfsvt9Jqnmezc2PWV1KYVJeBq279Eo-JfhGEmrsy_0aCUzOt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I've been coming to the delly for years, as it's a cheap option with an assortment of options from salads, curries, sandwiches, and more. Over that time, the quality is about the same solid B- food, as in not stellar but not horrid. So generally a 3 star place. What has declined, however, and the reason for my lower rating is the cost and quantity. One thin slice of meat does not a turkey sandwich make. Basically, they are still making $5 sandwiches but charging $10 and with less sandwich...","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Akbar Shakenov","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9WrUR0ZbYb0_kT2kk93PgA35IDV6kz8G9jFG29yrL4NkVBN8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"So sad, your curry was my favorite food on campus, but last two times were bad. It tastes so different and portions got smaller. The green Thai is not spicy anymore and just tastes sour and weird, beef also tastes sour. Today I got large butter chicken, but there was very little chicken, I noticed it is sliced in smaller pieces to mask smaller portion. So disappointed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bradley Guislain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLh0F_SXPBcpfBlKWAZ6_wXX7FaGctRt2U9-fybYt8v7MSNOA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Great if you like spending 15 dollars to get skimped on a curry bowl filled with rice so hard it could break your teeth.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul Dante","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjLXYa-Gi41DR82MW72_OBOxUKdygmYUf0O2nH158d2eOhgB0p=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of my favourite places to eat lunch on campus. While they have curry, samosas, and some other premade dishes, I anyways go with a custom made sandwich. In my opinion they have the best sandwiches on campus even if they don't have the most creative ones.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aki Natsume","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4hZ3GWzNO9DGZPb0Orw2NLOrhz78JvXHgISNYxxLMzC6VSV8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The food is really good but the staffs not very nice. I was there pretty early and there was no one in line. However, I was standing in the wrong line and the sandwich staff proceeded to ignore me until another customer got in the correct line and then reminded me that I was standing in the wrong place.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Reliable for simple and satisfying homestyle Korean food. Nothing blows me away but everything is good and flavourful. The meals all include lots of vegetables which I appreciate, and things aren't overly oily.
There's no atmosphere to speak of and I think they probably have more takeout than dine-in customers, but having done both, dine-in is the way to go, because the food comes out super fresh. The people who work there are nice and hardworking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXR2zL3EAW7SvQOTWGiznVuK83Eyw_nBeqY_6G&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2024-2-25"},{"Name":"Yuchang Zhan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJCu1wqeMUBpitsBVSAyQ29MPKUdyLQ__YQ2QBJ3AHY3DJY3g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went several times and recommended to all my friends. The owners are truly caring about the customers and always have THE BEST service ever. Once I mentioned I was cold, and later the owner offered me warm miso soup for free. This really made my entire evening.

Soups are always served warm with large portion. The pork bone is absolutely my to-go dish. So flavourful with so so much meat!

Never disappointed with their inari, I have tried beef, spicy salmon, shrimp, spam, tuna, kimchi, seaweed, some were even gifted by the owner. All the toppings are so delicious and flavourful, it’s hard for me to pick one favourite to be honest! The seasoning of rice makes everything even another level.

Foods are so authentic. My Korean friends said the dishes really brought them back to Korea. If you love Korean foods like me, you should definitely try it out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNM3_rcDUbPQB4N10byn-i2gBKLWgdvTB41RrFy&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2022-3-10"},{"Name":"Sasha Sadiora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqMB9CioB05yUeMJrchJN57cOo1BuZF_w3T8u4DS8Px3X91XTp=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The lady was very nice but the fact I paid a EXTRA $3.50 for cheese and got a KRAFT SINGLES slice is CRAZY","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLwLofol73ghxQyaPInWLd2gYRGqz6pWOzjLKe&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Niloufar Sharif","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3A88lqgzyr_DZVby4DylCumivfYhcpesHqnFk78Ei2iZVsggWWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a student, this place is so comforting and the food tastes authentic and homemade. The owners here are AMAZING, so caring, and kindhearted! They gifted us three free inaris to try as well as miso soup! Now the food. The portions are so generous and they will not cheap out on quality or amount of protein despite the affordable prices.
We got the gamja-tang and galbitang. The galbitang has a very clean broth and you can taste the fresh ingredients. Gamja-tang was packed with flavors and spices and soooo much pork!

Cant wait to go back and try all of their other dishes 😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNkVy2Nj_O8RT1_bytgunpwMTz22R8HjUrX_Hu&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2022-3-6"},{"Name":"Ahnaf Muqset Haque","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9JdQZtXBMvD618JDWqRmaMkXk-I2NhqdPuW2NLQFP33Qn87KikQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The only reason for my four star is their  customer service is heart warming. Really welcoming and good service. However, if you are actually looking for really really good Korean food then this probably isn't the place. It's okay as I would describe it but definitely not the best. Also, quantity is not adequate. However, trying to improve quantity first would be resonable step towards improvement!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPATOMJVNA_QXKyqiMpX11OXghmAXYiZDhRB6OR&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2019-4-19"},{"Name":"Anne W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVq8l7IxqCBT6CUTt6a8ydNheNQQYDJZKBxOYNsNiNzdtSpTCtW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The quality of the food here is excellent! I got the Jjajang Beef Udon today and it's now one of my favourite meals on campus. The sauce is delicious, as is the side of pickled daikon. The sauce is generous, so I might be able to get a side of rice and stretch it to two lunches (helpful with the high cost of living these days!).

Staff are lovely and helpful people. The outdoor seats on a good weather day are in the sun, so it's a great spot to enjoy your lunch. So glad this place is here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2GSZ-Y2SmizoNXA-E9OpCto2VOEvGfTSaozkJ&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2023-3-21"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I ordered Inari, it’s ok. The meat or topping to rice proportion was a bit off. There’s more rice than topping. I ordered 3 but it’s not enough, and it came out to be around 14$ so I’ll say just order a regular meal instead of this as it’s not that filling. The service was pretty good tho and the atmosphere was nice and cozy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOanBKptQ-R_H5eiyx4s67HHQU7ukggwSAkZ7tv&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2023-10-2"},{"Name":"cbl Google","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKseLK4QE-uFmbW8_hEmTOkS9RGzjwTJs3q9tyPwtQSc-dy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Korean foods and such an awesome owner! Definitely a gem in the village area. Tried a few of their new inaris and was not disappointed. The spicy salmon and bulgigi are highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMixXDyBd0gN0Cf58omWSw-4LIfMRQAXe33CFI&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2021-10-11"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Na","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbWRUtiYRRPvrKwMe6vdozzm8j4VVPvwRIWUtuWvW0eKAOr20j=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this place and it’s really surprising that the food is so good in this sad-looking hidden away food court.  They were open even when classes were not in session.  I love the Dan Dan noodle with 2 lamb skewers combo (comes with a canned drink).  Both were not too spicy for me, super tasty and generous portions.  I also had a breakfast crepe for the first time (ever. I’m just more familiar with Cantonese food) and it was so good and very large and filling.  I like their noodles which have a bit of a chew (look hand pulled rather than the skinny noodles you might expect normally in Dan Dan).  They were the same type of noodles in the meat sauce noodle dish (no soup).  The fried chicken is super crunchy so worth a try if you like fried chicken but I’m not looking for such an oily lunch/dinner.  Everything is fresh because it’s made to order.  They are open at night too. Looks like several of the other food court stalls did not open much.  Best thing to eat on the whole campus in my opinion.  Fair prices but if cost is an issue get their stamp card.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8ICOnqvJ0g5JPS6M6p7-6Q0WHwEXrNY8NPAUg\u0026fid=0x0:0x97af90bfdba20390"],"When":"2021-8-8"},{"Name":"Sartaj Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1doLfhIpPIdYO53EoD_63mHYE3jrQc1kxM-CAvFcju93a6Z1xPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Decent food, decent price. Ordered the Dan Dan (egg) noodles, quite tasty but also quite oily. Would recommend for a staple cheap student meal but not more than that. Decent service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOz1PE39GZeDjp_uU0TwU4rZ1zCXKBiVoQNdxni\u0026fid=0x0:0x97af90bfdba20390"],"When":"2021-1-28"},{"Name":"J Chow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5nTjAm8gcoM8KEoMc5sPDIPLKdZEtk_2xDDFiiYwdxxyp1qQ7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tasty and relatively inexpensive. Unfortunately I misordered. Their spicy beef noodle soup does not have hand pulled noodles. It uses rice noodles! Get the hand pulled next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkPr0flQbuFkNy5blRTS4gtw1c4BAaOytWa_nW\u0026fid=0x0:0x97af90bfdba20390"],"When":"2019-3-13"},{"Name":"牛犇","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJjm733-p1EO9YisjFSmP81nw_wdJZywpGyNzzdUYijEmjJvQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This lanzhou noodle is pretty bad. It's kind of instant noodles. Doesn't match with the picture at all.  I won't be there any more.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jaden Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUM2ggNMzvyF3-mbTCuUBp5sV15NjtcwDNnBrTCqRD4nn9vAlRl=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"(Trying everything at UBC journal #1)\nOn my first stop, I went to Kung Fu Noodle in the international food court and ordered the Dandan noodles. However, to my disappointment, I would find a piece of small plastic in my food, which made me dock this place one star. The wait for the food was also a little long compared to other places at the IFC. [{"Name":"Seonjae Im","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIt1GgA1qP_NjMCQxVFgkQjulbXGtYGtfVP5U0gEJ-yvUVuQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Super cheap compared to rising economy.
It helped me survive most of my sophomore year.
Food here are okay but it is reasonably cheap.
Tables are not cleaned often so you have to bear with it or get takeout.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHdTccy2Q7cHtwZI9Xc9nGh1oxqRiOgFGxFSJt&fid=0x0:0x690511f5e60f3a95"],"When":"2023-3-7"},{"Name":"H W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKiEtu-Pfzzd7vMmnC1lRzmwYGQeuaGu_8hpE004heAd4NBbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Great location for some cheap and diverse eats. The place looks somewhat run down but has some pretty good deals for international cuisine (Chinese food, sushi, pho, falafel, etc.).

Their hours are a lifesaver, helps for late night meals. Staff are generally friendly and helpful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFAhHhNAAdpg0bYtqVDcCQqpyEHK7e1kohBHaK&fid=0x0:0x690511f5e60f3a95"],"When":"2019-10-12"},{"Name":"Max Hsu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLu1jhFG8wW5p1LMrMk4Cj7Gyqq2DzrOgApiEw96NN7dKOuDw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is little cheaper than in campus. And the amount of food is pretty large, if you are hungry, you can have a hearty meal there!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlHGpUAimV7S52WSxtJgq9a3eyz6vGGta6rKYo&fid=0x0:0x690511f5e60f3a95"],"When":"2019-7-15"},{"Name":"Daniel Z.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQPWk1igWiScMJLvbEfOGbn_E-SvYzWdnJ-_3R9XXD4Q9XGO0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cheapest, most worth it food on campus IMO. a quick comparison to on campus food: At Nest, you get rice+3 items for 13 dollars. In this place, you get rice/fried rice/noodle + 3 items for 9.5 dollars.

Taste is great as well, only downside is the the messiness and the lack of tables during peak hours, but still a good place place overall","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shekoofeh Azizi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWmVXX_fZYwJ9yhvcqQ9wSWDiE3BKS-9WvrgxClrWs1anQJPK1kzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"They have good, fresh food with reasonable price for students. [{"Name":"Fiona Fung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU4Y8UvfKbpBZL3nGJBx_FuHvLZmV1sVQTIEerwFZZQafAcA_Ee=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Portions are kind of strange for the bbq pork rice bowl, it’s 80% white rice with the most random “Asian sides” thrown on top 😭 pork is decent, small portions of meat ):
they put teriyaki sauce on it which is like putting ranch dressing and mayonnaise on pasta, really strange choices overall","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoSZLRvR2Zcx6oUTHILPjksFiAv_n1f9j8LO43&fid=0x0:0xca16dca60bb9a0bf"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"Nicole Chacon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUOyNOf4Zxv3CHlH_9NP8Ntg6poAWJAg4w-CsxcFFnyEjer1Np=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Got the new rice bowl item and it was so good! I got the pork belly rice bowl that comes with white rice, pork belly and veggies. It was so good, price was reasonable and meal size was big! Highly recommend it! They also have fish cod, BBQ pork and fried chicken options to try! I have also had some of their other menu items and would recommend checking them out :)))","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPwCVxG13NgajQT0NmPcYS7dpf28WWA8sCjPZl&fid=0x0:0xca16dca60bb9a0bf"],"When":"2023-3-29"},{"Name":"Hugh Gao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFlJmYlj82sx6sLKOje56IkZUG693ZnITvHtJUekoopvQlVKt9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Noodles were very salty, but overall their food is decent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPA1GKsaXFTWPQ3OiRayclZS8EXks5ehw0kcPOL&fid=0x0:0xca16dca60bb9a0bf"],"When":"2024-10-9"},{"Name":"Stacey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIr2ky43bys3DcRFRrWNzodZxwlBjABRWrQpGIfV9_HNZI9Xg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Really really really salty food and fried rice is hardly fried with very little veg and no garnish. Plus it was cold. It was like eating regular rice that happened to be yellow and happened to have 3 little carrots and peas thrown in by accident.

Pricing is not great. Better options around campus. Only came here because it was close. Only good thing is that the portion is enough for a meal and a half (two sides and rice). But what good is the portioning if the food was salted to hell?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaKdQibMNOUJ41HGsovT7aljEOpc1JMa4fR6Ax&fid=0x0:0xca16dca60bb9a0bf"],"When":"2022-12-22"},{"Name":"Sam Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK8M_6fDmVHX9w3rt6O40cBysEU3Heg2OUSiV_reWxWxpzk-g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Do not make the same mistake I made and avoid getting pad thai from here. It was also lacking key ingredients like egg and tofu. Total waste of ~$15, they should consider changing their name to Bland Noodle Emporium","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOiDY0HtQo9Q99D8dRezkz2f700QwnASV4dH2tE&fid=0x0:0xca16dca60bb9a0bf"],"When":"2022-10-4"},{"Name":"Kenneth Shih Khoon Nieh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDgh8BXeXvOayEPWu3bN-G-w4bI-mN49-SiT0r54KxlVOlmYyd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I checked their menu before coming to this place. Don't be fooled by their menu price on Google. Their menu on Google is outdated. There is a huge price surge over the last two years. Now 1 noodle with 2 siders cost $13.13 after tax. Just compare this to "my home cuisine" of which the same set cost $9.50 after tax. I understand this is a restaurant which explains the price differences but again the quality is no better than the other. I mean both of them are of poor quality. Especially their noodles are so dry. After one bite, I am eagering for drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOF0tnL9gOKYb5e7rjffp7eFVu04NCnouKBU1Yi&fid=0x0:0xca16dca60bb9a0bf"],"When":"2022-8-19"},{"Name":"anonymous vendetta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJyLds73Yo5WbHgmIUXIzCFGmMf9bdg3_iu0d3fSXfgLJ-1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"BBQ miso ramen is actually so bad. The meat is tasteless and the broth has no flavor.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJMUQOWy6JQtFoAkI3UpOnkbp_ZwSLaymyR5f4QckQ1gaFV1k8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The staff are so friendly, the service is so fast and acceptable for busy nest. I loved this part. And the idea behind decoration was interesting.
Well, well, well,...
The price was reasonable. However, as a rumen lover, I guess it could be better. So, from my point of view, it was a good rumen. But not more.
Another thing: Tofu miso ramen was the only one without pork in ramen category which made it hard for people looking for halal food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMv6gnHVXiaR_0568GH5l4rJ5Ly8q6QXIE1oXGk&fid=0x0:0xca16dca60bb9a0bf"],"When":"2020-1-30"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Jordan Bates","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfiSlogqPxTBz7X041V4ZcubJ3xk4d-ypWA52tlZknobCbzNR5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I’m from the U.S. originally so I’m no stranger to Chipotle and have been to several other locations in Vancouver, but this one is by far the worst. I’ve been here a couple times now with friends and the service staff are completely indifferent/unfriendly, the place seems disorganized, and it does not feel remotely comparable to any other Chipotle location I’ve been to. The portion sizes are not consistent from visit to visit and it seems as though the staff have taken some creative liberties as to how portioning and presentation should look. Every time my friends and I have visited this location, we have had to ask for more lettuce. They sprinkle it in the corner like it’s a garnish (picture attached was after asking for more). With the other toppings (corn, cheese) as well, they sprinkle minuscule portions with their fingers instead of using a standardized measuring device. I’ve only been during lunch rush, but I feel they start heavily skimping so that they have to do less prep or worry about changing containers mid rush. They do not follow “fifo” procedures (first-in, first out) and my friend and I (who both have experience in the food service industry) watched them on multiple occasions just dump new prep on top of older prepped toppings instead of switching containers. It’s about half the portion of food you’d get at any other Chipotle, which is a shame since you’re paying the same $17-$20 price tag. Seeing more experienced individuals in food service or service management at this location would be nice, in place of the youthful and evidently lacking in training/experienced staff at present. My friends and I have been here 3-4 times now but I don’t think we will continue as it stands. Hopefully changes are made so it’s more like every other Chipotle out there!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWSZEiO33TrzJ28Rpi7SrKJEuFe807cpuShEC1\u0026fid=0x0:0xa21f97d8c0582245"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Ella Bender","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWy_6ygK4WcuTSytOxPzocdO2ji3fAN1LtRbmZJjQICX--PpR4v=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Got a bowl but it feels only half full. The service felt super rushed, even when I was the only person in the store. I had to ask for more lettuce and there's still barely any. I didn't bother asking for more rice and chicken but I definitely should have. Also did the prices get increased?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7u31reHHCAIzpoh02TTXFGSt_s4NUiGxCHLpu\u0026fid=0x0:0xa21f97d8c0582245"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Tracy S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2KIvjxx-0xSdgN7X_lDT6LFt5P_11tk9uyS8O7df2vE0ddIQt=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Please gimme lettuce bro… this looks so sad. Why is the portion size always so small compared any other chipotle?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPrn-QB4qjtpmSwMtPKVES8kTtcXK0Iz9T1N_7O\u0026fid=0x0:0xa21f97d8c0582245"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Jake.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXi8ZWMWuMxlnpD5_maiEkPwNBNscsPle1pfRNmmb4_cshcMp9K=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Chipotle is known for its quickness and portion sizes and this restaurant is horrible at both. Twice in a row I have pre-ordered online only to have to wait 15 minutes beyond what was expected and all that to have shockingly small proportions. It amazes me that every other location has reasonable portion sizes and yet the one location near broke college kids skimps out? The restaurant is understaffed and proportions are absurdly small, hopefully management sees all these awful reviews and makes some change.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"gan ning","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVMjHOBXHKN8Tphl-H0LL997Q3L2sNhXFNNl90TwErPr42122A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I've been a regular at the Chipotle in my hometown for several years now. As a loyal customer, I was hoping to be able to work here as a UBC student. However, my interview got cancelled less than an hour before it was set to be held which is so disrespectful of my time and effort to commute and prepare. I was willing to overlook this location being constantly out of ingredients because of the high volume of customers but now it seems that this place is simply poorly managed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"William Cai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLowDo9VdBFQi300S4kjpXRwZghe-KspAmuoouT66ufKVCRug=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered a few items and the staff made three severe mistakes during the process, requiring them to remake the items. My order was not particularly complicated, no extras or particulars. It was simply two different items. I made an effort to speak more clearly after the first mistake but the problem persisted.\n\nOn the last error I gave up and just accepted what they did for my order.
