user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ivy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2btWvwldxPAFdVC30WRTnDiJDb4PhrEfk_b3M_t3CbTqvHC0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The ramen taste burn and the matcha ice cream had a weird taste🤮🤮🤮🤢🤢🤢such low quality food with such expensive price would not recommend 🤢🤢🤢🤮🤮🤮🤮🤮壁嘞","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdRK5BM3beGQhxrAC3I49SGPyZrU6PGt0ZqMA6&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"YVR Duke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbrjJ5U6gKw7Gn1zE_GlxhUndims9WHlh7sVaHLXVrjOFlYd_B=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"**Rating: 3/5**

The ramen broth here has potential but needs less water to enhance its flavor. The pork was well-prepared, albeit too small a piece. The thick noodles I chose were an absolute disaster – the worst noodle texture I've ever experienced, both in North America and Asia.

The gyoza were deep-fried, which isn't typical in Asia but is common in North America due to the preference for fried foods and the ease of preparation. Thankfully, their frying technique was spot on, with the right temperature making the skin crunchy and not greasy.

Overall, this ramen shop is one step away from being good, but that one step is significant. I'm puzzled by its high rating; perhaps it's because it's being compared to other campus food options?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEZscgOvkrJVwnAhJ_ijxCSFxfSYjODwksU3PC&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Alexander Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKntg94WsHup3cVgJBk3yO0jaRf4K-ndL2T0xGy94s_gBQtie8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My friend and I had the opportunity to visit the Kinton Ramen UBC. At 6 pm on the weekday for dinner, there was a lot of space available. There are options for indoor and outdoor seating. This will be great for friends, couples or groups of friends. Indoor seating can sit around 15 people. Outdoor seating can sit around 20 people. The chairs inside are small, and the space feels somewhat cramped.

The prices for the food are on the upside as per usual for restaurants near the university campus. Both my friend and I ordered the Pork Original with thick noodles. The portions were small (somewhat little noodles, two pieces of pork), but the thick noodles and broth tasted great. Service was fast, but servers are friendly and attentive.

Our final bill came around to around $40 dollars which can be quite expensive for students or those living on campus in student housing. If the portions were more and the prices were cheaper, I will be returning here for more food. I would recommend people to try out this restaurant if they have not before, but not to rely here for a full stomach.

The washrooms are clean. The restaurant is wheelchair accessible, but the space is cramped and washroom are also small. There is underground parking quite close.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1m_bO2WcI2xuf2eO5LkkMFM0jEGbqyphVHSSq&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2024-4-10"},{"Name":"Keith Ver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVdqxLCf1LEt0AU82myo-eUqDcb2LcbdnfhupJTEW0sPAQ-qQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely loved the Beef Original ramen! First time to visit UBC and glad we found a ramen place! We also ordered their Pork Shoyu ramen, Chicken Karaage, and for desert, we had matcha and black sesame cheesecake. Service was fast and staff were friendly too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPO-3TfmeZZtj6P98VvroDVI_hKZpPM5w2f4y24&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2024-5-8"},{"Name":"Paul Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXn3m0AZWl28VYBOwUKfmGVllVddsvt-pe4tcU6-ebIHORKGYiIPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The food itself is somewhat decent but literally 4 out of 5 water cups have remaining food scraps in it. I have a big question mark on how they clean their dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIL8vKD7fXBElGg1uiIiCByV4FaLETlaqoBpr9&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Cassie P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJK1sFu6ktgIyFAwh9CV60GZepOJ-TiQPcseS5ixBK1mh7Q0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely Love the Veg Spicy Garlic Ramen!! The spice really hits the spot and the broth has so much flavour! Everything i want in my vegetarian ramen. Had both take out and dine in on the same day since i was in the area and wasn’t disappointed!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNr4nHcBpRR_Duj50YdmXJq9iz_1Vv5absT8zeO&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2024-2-22"},{"Name":"Hugh Gao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFlJmYlj82sx6sLKOje56IkZUG693ZnITvHtJUekoopvQlVKt9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great ramen; better than most restaurants at UBC. The photo is of a seasonal menu item.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-IZRVp5puXQ0CIxFBqvjK7o1R7pJZhFcHSiZx&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Jinny C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJF1E0u7aAYhoG0Ugnl_mjrDGZEqbFrHAer59dj1QQcIcrSbw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They have outdoor seatings now, but not covered. Ramen got great flavour. We can ask for thin or thick noodle, less cooked (harder,chewier) or more cooked (softer) noodle. Personally I like the harder noodle but that's personal preference. I like the fact that we have the option to request. Ordered pork original and chicken original.  They don't disappoint.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMo2qLMaaPicifOygXPejkBOxOWmXI-8Tz6gDgT&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2021-3-10"}]

I ordered #1 to go which was $12.95 before tax if I remember correctly (as of Oct. 8, 2024).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOank77KH0ZN3OqtoLCsXe-0VzK27LLBdl7gHEZ&fid=0x0:0x48535312e395315d"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Amity Chiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJYIqhcYzNuOhGHtmQQKnKIbfu2MFgw-Oud25eme8BQJzg47A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is an OG and a hidden gem located in UBC Village’s International Food Court (downstairs).

I greatly appreciate the owners approach to their pricing to be accessible to students. There are a lot of food options on campus now but we always come back to Miyamae.

We love their Bento Box 1 (Chicken Teriyaki + California roll) & Box 2 (Beef Teriyaki + spicy tuna roll), each comes with miso soup, rice, salad and 3-piece tempura. Their food is consistently fresh and the rolls are made to order.

Box 1 is $12.95
Box 2 is $13.95

With tax, everything in the photo came up to be $28.25!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO248i8Am-Ff9mEdX81uKGmSyViBuxxpETKrM-E&fid=0x0:0x48535312e395315d"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Ron Friedman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3HlybQ5wATQGzc9dsWu8bps1pgOdJjJiLFpwPODdXQf1m9A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cheap prices compared to similar food at UBC. Surprisingly big portions for the price and quick, no-frills service.
The quality of the sushi isn’t exceptional, but it’s always fresh and tasty.
I’ve come here many times and will continue to do so in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"This food","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaxcCslaGrcC0u202g67ni7XJGWWGyPYtSKkUjWo5gpcXXO0Yv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fair price for their sushi and the curry katsu! I recommend the katsu if your craving anything fried.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORNZP9PObXB6Sz4lUpRTdZI1AxEOj1RUlbw_Pt&fid=0x0:0x48535312e395315d"],"When":"2022-7-26"},{"Name":"Krista Precosky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIibGDCJ3ieE9oxm9X4XZ0uMf4E_0Xy_dvsgK3FwPp2mr7Pzw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I alway come here when I'm in Vancouver! Big pieces of fish in the chirashi don... Very good 😊","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTrCjaR0uMvkTsDtHmw6HvHPC2K6C9mSnxxj73&fid=0x0:0x48535312e395315d"],"When":"2024-7-10"},{"Name":"Claire Padvaiskas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocINFso4NsHpotpRg6JOestnmKF2FI_8YEIY8jUm1LobTLjR=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered a salmon avocado roll with spicy mayo on top and it was DELICIOUS!! And the service was great, she was really nice and helped me choose the best options :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxGps2TpWl4ZaIo9igfjKn_o84hHy6SiiGWHBt\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lots of cool choices for hotdogs and very vegetarian-friendly since you can get a veggie sausage with any of the dogs on the menu (not as vegan-friendly since most options include mayo and/or cheese). The guy who works there is super nice. There are also Korean subs and other snacks, and bingsu. They use a good veggie sausage and the toppings are always fresh. The hot dogs and snack foods are very reasonably priced, the bingsu are more splurge-y, but they are pretty big. The shop is very small, but the buzzer system they have works well, so you can wait for your order outside and get a buzz to pick it up.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQM6Ga7Xs7_kR11FSzwpQzsjueEtvJo9hL6iqh\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2023-8-12"},{"Name":"J Psk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJysbWTRrHYTp8s-srkk4zt31Bl_q_WrtM2a-GsVp2w2ODMSw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Don't order the chi-bap (fried chicken rice) whatsoever. What I got was comletely different from the photo on the menu. The chicken is not fried chicken at all, they use oven baked chicken nuggets. The corn salad had like 3 grains of corn. NOT worth 15$ at all...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7aidT799VL6AA3Zdo-Tt2GjLqBpKF4IutJdaK\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Yesong Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZ91KZByxRVp7hNBb-aKt5xKC5uCcHWJErPks1BHnBM5NsPqdN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Easy to order, super quick pickup, and the Vegetarian Kimchi hotdog was good (I am from South Korea 🤣👍). The staff were kind💚 Looking forward to coming back. Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRlR3UB5562u53xdhKrOsGJiz4rkZrE-p0ZaKU\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2024-10-2"},{"Name":"NixOil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWa0-gf5561LR0YaDvsEO2rH9HzBIiXnz8EIWyrMmynW44HE3yV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best hotdog I have ever had in my entire life. This place was super fast and the hotdog was just amazing. I got the pizza dog which sounds weird but was so good that I had to review this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPV_LPo5uQklvQIOPMQmDjk9t5JYYTmqDNQoyQC\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2023-12-30"},{"Name":"K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK8Kffru-eJ-MFdAxDjN_kWwnt7cEHBHmGbUwwPuMFBkRwEcGM5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best hot dog place we’ve ever been to! The hotdogs were juicy, tasted fresh, and all of the toppings went so well together. We ordered 2 kimchi hotdogs ($9 each) and 2 seoul hotdogs ($10 each). Not going into lie, we had some difficulty finding this place but we would definitely come here again.  there’s not really a place you can sit and eat because it’s just a bench right outside the place, and you’re likely going to be harassed by birds so be cautious when you’re eating lol. The food took a bit of time (15 to 20 minutes maybe?) to make but we weren’t in a rush and there was only 1 guy making all the hotdogs fresh in front of us. Highly recommend this place if you’re at UBC!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyyvUswrdO-Ws48fgWp7Nkh-O9hEzBay1CETlT\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2023-11-13"},{"Name":"Marvin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIOUB9fqPRyAnJAGsLqhyOV_Bp81x_bJC8wIyyATYNP2vGJzmc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small little shop with amazing customer service. Guy at the front was very welcoming and nice. Hot dog was pretty good, a little expensive for what it was but still great. Definitely will be back to try some other stuff.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Rina Tedja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCUXpJzYjJvgoEpkOVkc0pbrgG_5eFoaZqgY-XQUp-9x6VbVQf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Made a reservation to celebrate my friends graduation, glad that they have a big table to accommodate all of us. Food were good, and we didn't have to wait too long. Price was students friendly, not too expensive. And the waitress was willing to separate the bills. Thank you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOECwl2kQckPquUlCvPef_3x4Heu87O09BQYUEo&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Olive Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWaNKzMiC0kwUfahhPHKJzI23aKwHnkWquzcNkJSLJCjhuJoC_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Restaurant's price with food court level of food and presentation.
$20 bento with only a little bit of rice, the avocado in California roll went half black, the egg tasted disgusting, the miso soup was served in a plastic bowl and the green tea from the water bottle was cold. The fried chicken was the only good thing....but definitely not come back again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kit Kat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3dZjoko9sqyxGJIpo6Vuc0LAP-G_ufVv3gqG1OzG8hLIiI4o=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dined in for the first time two months ago and the food was absolutely delicious! I've tried all of the bento boxes as they are my favourite to get a little bit of everything and they never disappoint. I've since returned many more times to enjoy the food here, and the staff are all so friendly. I would absolutely recommend coming here for a bite to eat 10/10","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Luke Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-nw_Hipvgt6UpenAw0abcDlQMvwpFIko8ke_8Sy_24ohAlwTK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"New food location here at UBC and of course I had to try it out. The restaurant was very clean and had very good COVID 19 precautions set up with electronic little hand sanitizing bottles set up at the entrance and payment counter. The server was nice and very direct. The overall environment while in the environment was very comfortable.

They had quite the variety of food on their menu and at affordable prices considering campus food prices. The menu was large, not overcrowded with menu items, and easy to follow. I ordered Bento Box A with beef (roughly $14) to go. I went at around 3pm on a Sunday, there were a few tables inside and I waited for just over 10 minutes for my food, which was a little longer than I had expected.  The packaging for takeout was pretty meticulous with everything being packed nicely in a large brown paper bag. The food was the typical bento box style food but everything was quite tasty. The beef to rice ratio was a bit lacking but the beef had adequate flavor and the added tamago (sweet eg) was a nice bonus. The California rolls were pretty good and the assorted tempura was light and did not leave an oily taste layer in my mouth.

Overall, a pretty good first experience here at this new establishment on campus. I will be back to try one of their curries.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzR7fkKpZwe8yvCpZLjeSxdz3pIlm7XjwH-llL&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2020-9-15"},{"Name":"Daniel Slick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_rZhDYtX3p8Slyn1b3td54gJ7P5nOU91uTlm-nX3vMAWbK9f5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was very fresh and nicely prepared. Service was very warm and friendly but a little slow.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMV_MEbs8rViQqFqmGdJS2OXO_u5BMXbXZn7vqj&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Tina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAKiC5J1ql1LsLTTfBwgvAj6sVGUusHXghumDKVG9ZTQ8QjcD_1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Quick food and good price! I love their Bento box A (for around $14) with a good variety of thing: tempura, sushi, salad, tamago. It’s just enough to sample all and the chicken rice is very filling.
Also the service is great and they got my order ready really fast. Recommend for students!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeaPUY7Q--PH_Rutk0VgFbhkRyMSLT8gkqANqC&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2023-6-15"},{"Name":"Sepehr Mirzaei","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZMkP1FM4xSnxxmsChX6t7nGX4XBELdM4VoX6LyFTiA8owPtU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Relatively good food at good prices for UBC. Love the gyu don, the beef Curry, and the fried bento boxes are quite nice too! I wish the tea was a little bit hotter though, but it's free so I can't complain. Sometimes the "wait to be seated" sign makes it hard to enter due to obstruction of the path though which can be a little frustrating","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPiSfDXfg5R1CM-ASn3rWTpnHdczFlq5NuBF7av&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2024-2-23"},{"Name":"w","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVECjtzjKwGGU2yagM5sH2sMNpUPFv0VdGQBZqvehtzvpFlyVDi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"good prices, quick with the food. place is small and cute. waitresses checked up on us regularly.

update: has gotten even better! niku udon tastes authentic and looks amazing","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhtgbisEJ4_pTdVmEGp0QaIsyHLa7DR3Xe8sDg&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2022-8-16"}]

[{"Name":"Allely Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtHxde_F8vk5lVftENM6SLTkZPGO7dWB67i3AK5rZruYP6D6kqsQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I have ordered several time their Bulgogi over rice. It’s my fav dish from them because they made it right there and it’s always hot. The only bad thing about it is that it’s a kinda oily / greasy. And that recently I noticed they had been giving less in their portion. Tip: they will charge you a bit less if you bring your own container.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPU0hn5Mg4l0zHpKMkGJIxxHqeplCD1bDAmH6oB&fid=0x0:0xcd0ee9e06776c19d"],"When":"2024-3-13"},{"Name":"Grace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpyR6lW9JHiyXGuG73lo5A19PTb1WXFzVLCnrO84Gv3hfeDE5c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It’s in a convenient location in the Nest, so I’ve eaten here very often throughout undergrad. My go-to are the salmon maki or takoyaki if I want a snack, or a bento or donburi if I’m more hungry. The crispy chicken is very good. I also like adding on a miso soup for $0.99.

One time, I decided to get some chicken karaage for the first time here, and it was TERRIBLE. It had gone bad and was super stale, it felt like I was chewing plastic.

According to some other reviewers, they’ve also had bad experiences here. I’d say that Honor Roll’s food is generally okay and consistent - but once in a while you might get unlucky and get something really bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdCG-1pati8qnNiy0_MICxOyMcRU20pemZxOiB&fid=0x0:0xcd0ee9e06776c19d"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Marc L. Dauchez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVeVV96R-NCc8CX96gFheQOEKzYgXX6vGRggH8frurN6ted2o4f=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The vendor is not greeting the customers. When passing the order the vendor did not flinch nor talk to me.
The vendor through a number at me without telling me what it was for.
When the food was ready the vendor did not say anything, I had to check myself.
So she lost her tips - obviously.
Like most students, the vendor doesn't need the income for which she works but it's not a reason to be despicably unprofessional.
It is pathetic to realize how low AMS is ready to go to hire aid.
Not everyone is meant to work, especially the privileged kids who despise labor work because they know it is not something they'll have to do.
The people in charge of hiring SHOULD REALLY start questioning themselves","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"elaine !","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeWGmQ6CCD8spyKKy_hRGpa5E8CPoGuFlTOZITz-n1J3qegRp-=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"i shouldve listened to the reviews, the sushi rice was as hard as a rock and tasted like it was many days old. the sashimi shrimp tasted like sand and was also hard. avoid the take out food if possible","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Decent selection of grab-and-go items which is of just okay quality compared to sushi in general but a lot better than the average premade sushi. They also have a pretty good menu of rolls made fresh (or if they're out of something in the grab-and-go case you can ask them to make it fresh), which are slightly better than the grab-and-go stuff for quality, but the variety is a little more interesting. They also have some donburi and poke. I haven't tried the poke but do not recommend the veggie donburi since it's just steamed carrots and broccoli over rice. Staff are nice, the line gets long at lunch time and can move slowly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGYxNwkhIA7fiuU1eKBSw0G48e2D98C8X227zV&fid=0x0:0xcd0ee9e06776c19d"],"When":"2021-9-9"},{"Name":"i love t series","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKsmpJoyX1ORsSWDhSs1Mq_BBHTtT_JK03WbUFNEIkPfozaeg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Food is terrible, is lowk kinda yuck and small. Service was super bad, guy was really rude and unhelpful. I asked for a napkin cuz they ran out and then he said "too bad im finna refill it tmr". Music lowk hype tho!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuJMclSb6kXxmROmBxScI2Ajd_a0mv81t6UlADn-rwYztas-2c=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered chicken teriyaki. Feels like the chicken stayed in the fridge for years. Frozen on the inside and you will need very strong teeth to bite it open - better prepare a bowl for any falling teeth.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elton Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_SVkVqkNe3SvSFwaZ1xrBYHObNVkTiTTXXYykf58guqGIk3qy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I had a walk in the UBC and it was my first time there. Felt hungry and entered the UBC Neat for a late lunch. This sushi roll store came into my sight. I had a Dynamite roll combo. The portion was just right with a miso soup. The combo had the fried shrimp roll with a few pieces of sushi. Taste ok for a quick fix.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJfO5xplOGPr511EXaNamka-RRALeKJ1--bpA&fid=0x0:0xcd0ee9e06776c19d"],"When":"2021-8-21"}]

[{"Name":"Ali","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVc2yFZO2stJjMAA_yC-haWWL7s20-2uvdCcNdcZmJ0nShSIEgN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Lemongrass Chicken with spring rolls was extremely tasty and definitely worth the $19. While some comments suggest this place might not be the destination for authentic food, our experience was fantastic! The chicken was juicy, the salad was well-dressed, and the vermicelli was cooked to perfection. The portion sizes were so generous that we ended up taking most of our food home for later. I would definitely come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAr1GhD8M7eOKgDtd4ILOfEhn0gSPEBWV4dytn&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"Arroyo Spero","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxtGzSht4hUue94OJChsO0T0v5gn-kGbLMxKrdo9nYj-1wKfpi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The rare beef pho was the best I’ve had in Vancouver,  if not the world.  I also had a great chat with my server who was knowledgeable,  kind and extremely efficient.  I will always recommend this restaurant as the go to for Pho in Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPh0pmw8fVpITDOGmScrITwuse1QuIG3sFBEY7x&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Tony Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPKcy0N8L_e03kCanD-kbqBYJvghgec1_Wu16Qs-S8YjI-PLg2nw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"For a pho place at UBC, it's pretty good but it lacks authenticity. I mean, the broth is great but you don't get a plate of bean sprouts and basil leaves like you do at other pho restaurants. I thought maybe at first, they forgot but my second time eating in, they forgot again. No one got it so that seems to be the norm. Service is prompt. Food is good. Also for big eaters, try to do an add-on. I added a lemongrass chicken to my pho and ended up bringing home 2 large pieces of grilled chicken for dinner. The servings are plentiful. Meat balls can be a little more plump, quail eggs in a seafood soup?? Music is a bit rad for this place too but catered to students, it's understandable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjOQVegjA6Q1U07IN_MZnnr7auHBN2VOCLhu2c&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2024-4-30"},{"Name":"ITwins (iTwins)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUUfk9fQ2wnUPyx22p2MtHChD4th8SauoOfDx9kxsrTGIv_31wePQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went to UBC for the Food Truck Festival. Instead, we ended up having lunch here. We should have eaten at the festival.

This is an imitation Phở restaurant or a Phở-wannabe restaurant. Their phở soup tasted nothing like authentic ones. It also has no Vietnamese phở names, like Bún Bò Huế, Phở tái Nam, or Phở bò viên, for example.

My $18.50 "Spicy Beef Noodle Soup" tastes somewhat similar to Bun Bo Hue but lacks all the major ingredients found in real BBH. It only comes with meatballs and beef slices typically used in Hot Pots or Shabu Shabu. 😅 The taste is also very mild in comparison and lacks any herb flavor.

The $19 "Special Noodle Soup" is laughable, not even close to any beef pho we have ever tasted. But nothing is worse than what I am about to say....

In both the noodles, the beef slices were HOLY SH*T!! - SO MUCH FAT! 🫣😮‍💨😵 There were less than half edible meat portions in each slice. Don't know if we should ROFL or go postal. Either way, one of the worst beef phở we have ever eaten in the world (only two other phở restaurants in the world are worse than Phở With Us', and we have eaten many phở in many, many countries in our world travels!)

Three hours later, my stomach was growling and I had to eat a full meal. Therefore, Pho With Us' pho is considered a snack. $19 FOR A SNACK. Sheesh!!!

.

Picture 1: $18.50 "S1 Spicy Beef Noodle Soup." Doesn't look greasy initially. Wait till the end....

Picture 2: $19 "P1 Special Noodles Soup"

Picture 3: Every beef slice is filled with fats. Not for human consumption!

Picture 4: A thick layer of grease formed on the surface at the end of the meal

.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvVQMHXUy43_OHH3GX22WtlqJezpi7tgHp1wiY&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2024-4-6"},{"Name":"Harry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-RtcD0-6ye1J2JBnA5bvdHPLsbB6QNrfMYYEBmsFbjc_dS_Co=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best bowls of pho I've ever had! The soup is really really good and there were plenty of beef and beef balls in the soup. The shrimp salad rolls are also really good but I couldn't finish it because of the large portion size of the pho. The only thing I would change about the special pho is adding some beef tripes to the pho, but it's not a popular ingredient outside of Asia so that is understandable. The staff is super nice too! The ambiance is also super nice with speakers playing pop music that I actually recognize. Honestly a super wonderful experience! The restaurant deserves a higher rating than the current average rating since I was unsure about the quality from reading the rating and the low rating is a little misleading.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNomg64hwrqeNIsRWfQmdhF93tXomr06ajxhY-o&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2024-3-20"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I didn’t know where to set my expectations for Pho  with Us, but I was pretty impressed with the food here! I had the Tofu & Veggie Rolls with Dry Noodles and a Tofu Pudding w/ Ginger Syrup. The noodle dish (vermicelli) was totally delicious, especially the veggie spring rolls! Even though the tofu and spring rolls were deep-fried, the dish didn’t have an oily taste. I saved one of the spring rolls for later and was still very full - I could have gotten two light but complete meals out of this if I hadn’t gotten excited and eaten so fast to start out with. The tofu pudding was okay, kind of bland. I haven’t had a dessert like this from a Vietnamese restaurant before so I don’t know how it usually should be. I appreciated that the ginger syrup wasn’t too sweet but I would have liked the ginger to be stronger. This was also a large portion so I took half home.
Like other restaurants in University Marketplace, the environment is rather cafeteria-like, meaning not much ambiance to speak of, but the people who run it are nice and hard-working. Considering it’s campus eats, it checks all the boxes: tasty, great value, and quick. And it’s great to have a Vietnamese restaurant at UBC now.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNpGIHMY6CyqkBkK4uTFVZVKAfFxEqyve7u59Px&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2023-5-28"},{"Name":"This food","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaxcCslaGrcC0u202g67ni7XJGWWGyPYtSKkUjWo5gpcXXO0Yv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I’m so glad they opened a pho place at UBC! This is perfect for those cold days on campus.

The portions are big and it’s a fair price given the inflation. My sandwich was a little over $7 and had plenty of filling. The spring rolls were larger than expected and I was still able to take one roll home.

No issues with seating when we arrived on a weekday at around 12:15pm. Really enjoyed it here and will return to try pho. They take card. Paid parking at the front or free parking along the road after 6pm. Overall, I recommend coming here if you’re craving some pho or hang-over food when your in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNE4Pg5kLkE6ABWevnDyEibjpcF6lM-hSY-dlDf&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2023-3-29"},{"Name":"Florios Demosten","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKV_Z2MRxAoQMQk052NPA0eDIO0u7XtdAaudscAalqOrOtXLw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered Uber eats from here, I got the lemongrass chicken.

I don’t usually leave Google reviews so let that stand out for how bad this chicken was. It tasted like it was 2 days old and microwaved.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Hugh Gao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFlJmYlj82sx6sLKOje56IkZUG693ZnITvHtJUekoopvQlVKt9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came here for dinner in my first year at UBC almost everyday, because it’s probably the best dining hall out of the three. The food was very consistent. My recommendations: butter chicken from Square Kitchen, fried rice from Custom Kitchen, and the occasional dim sum on weekends. There used to be serious health safety issues with bugs being found in the food, so be careful of that","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMRDeLLpeWOB1zL0Lr950WO3mPYyfYGnkq9_BTJ&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Alexander Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKntg94WsHup3cVgJBk3yO0jaRf4K-ndL2T0xGy94s_gBQtie8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Orchid Common is one of the first year residence dining halls at UBC. Being built in 2016/2017, OC's dinning hall has a main seating area and another room for additional guests.

The atmosphere is really spacious and the architecture allows for great  natural sunlight. The seating there can sit 200-300 people. At regular meal time, 8am -9am, 11am to 12pm, 6pm to 7pm, expect there to be lots of people.

The food there is okay and there is variety there every day. The portion is small (all-you can eat, but you get pre-allocated portions) so you can get multiple kinds of food. Sometimes, the food is too saulty or the tasting is off. The dinning hall is open from 7am to 10pm every day, but the food may not be plentiful or have great variety when you come to eat outside of regular meal hours.

The pricing is cheapest around breakfast at around $12. Lunch is $16 and dinner is at $20. The food is all you can eat. If you have a UBC meal plan, then you can go to OC as many times as you want and are unlimited in entries. If you have residence meal plan, then the cost would not matter to you. You are not charged per entry, but charged for the entire meal plan as a whole.

For food options there, you can expect salad bar, yogurt ball, vegetarian options for food, stir-fry grill, and burger grill. There are fresh fruits like apple, bananas, oranges and plum. There is tea, coffee and juice available. Their Philly cheesesteak sandwich and burgers is good.

To know the menu of OC, you can download an app to see their menus. Their lunch and dinner menus are the same.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0aPX-vNdBTU_jqkiXOSgJRpgqyUEHS9HhAyML&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2023-9-13"},{"Name":"yoyo huang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHfL3bnaoL_4LM9Q6GkGocV7c7Sko1louBNBsuDc0OrdaDTJLa=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food here is very unstable, sometimes good, sometimes bad. Once was way too salty, it tastes like it got drowned in salt and it even stings my tongue. Not good👎","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Saskia Asyari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOw-vGRppaZWH-87l0DTjRp6cH2-cGmCr2why8D5leomPAj1GywA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here for lunch and this is probably the best value of $15 you will ever spend in Vancouver for an all-you-can-eat eatery option. They have salad bars, bakery section, beverage bars, and fruit baskets. Great selection of menus from western, Asian, Indian, and vegetarian foods. The menu varies everyday though, you can check on their website. They serve halal food options foods such as peri-peri chicken and kung pao chicken noodles. They grew some of their own veggies and fruits. When you’re leaving, you’ll be allowed to either take home a fruit or pastry and one beverage with your own mug/bottle. Will definitely be back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCaEKVOt1CdDyAyFi_ZBkw_TWa3ENkeMQ1oyuf&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2023-3-15"},{"Name":"dabossdud","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8qzSvvMAD5ffHxPidijA4FBHoh1MqBeLVTwN70J852UBbgpO7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"To be honest if it wasn't for the newer building, it would be pretty bad. The food is comparable to totem park, except they don't have pizza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkwULCaVFlfP0ezbHsbSwlugj6abTd-iAvQ9jg&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2024-2-17"},{"Name":"Monique L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9o0N3sSdNhQoJRm_UTMB_81UV1EwCg55ZvQAZUsA1N6LBkXzD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Best place to go for food by far on campus. The brunch is my go to at Open Kitchen and I'm never disappointed. Eggs Benny, super fresh breakfast sandwiches, buffet style yoghurt parfait, salad bars, dim sum, and so many selections! Something for every kind of eater (ie Vegan, Gluten free, paleo, carnivore). Definitely beats going to Vanier's or Totem cafeteria.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgNdCb4Sio0BJe6HhHYusx5okeS7mU7FNGVQRY&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2017-3-16"},{"Name":"Lizzie S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5qIG1VmBASZQRSYXsIMifm6rtLhZA6xcKTGDs0bvXyJT2pXkmsA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this student restaurant. Very fresh food. Good place for breakfast.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOU2m_RFTQNNcxwo_5q7KsyjSchNVQOGZMxhP5B&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2024-2-12"},{"Name":"Tala Vera","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJcvcL500DcEodS8A6CxW3NgQRJf6q0SX7Xd4hIbm5xb8dUiA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"UBC students in line for dinner at one of the school’s cafeterias were greeted by an unwelcome guest this week.
Video circulating online shows a dark-coloured rat on top of the grill station at Open Kitchen, a cafeteria in the Orchard Commons residence on UBC’s Vancouver campus.
ADVERTISEMENT

First-year student Isabel Curiston was in line for dinner around 7:30 p.m. Tuesday when she saw the rodent standing next to the food.

“I look up and I see this rat coming out of the cracks where they keep fruits and vegetables, and just standing there,” she said.
RELATED STORIES
UBC delays return to most in-person classes again, citing Omicron concerns
UBC obtains 1st edition of Shakespeare's First Folio, promises 'unprecedented' public access
UBC researchers look at 'gel' biomaterials to help treat spinal cord injuries
The rat caught the attention of many students in the cafeteria. Curiston pulled out her phone and recorded the encounter, which ended when a kitchen worker grabbed the rat with a pair of tongs. The critter fell to the floor, and the worker carried on with his duties.
Dinner service continued, but UBC told CTV News the grill station was immediately closed down and sanitized, and all the food was thrown out.
“(We) are working actively with our pest control partner to address the situation," said Colin Moore, director of UBC Food Services, in a statement to CTV News. "All employees have been informed and reminded about proper sanitation measures as necessary,”
UBC also confirmed Vancouver Coastal Health has since inspected the cafeteria, finding no evidence of rodent infestation and saying it’s content with the school’s sanitation and pest control measures.
Students living in several residences at UBC pay for a meal plan, which gives them credit to buy meals at school cafeterias and restaurants. Curiston wants UBC to consider giving students some form of a reimbursement or meal voucher, saying despite health inspectors signing off on the cafeteria’s cleanliness, the image of a rat in the kitchen will keep her from dining there for some time.
“I refuse to go back until I know for a fact they’ve dealt with the rat problem,” she said. “If they set out traps, I’d feel more safe eating there.”​","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdu1L40XRvbU__oyjBuTwVZOpwceqlwIHYwesg&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2022-1-20"}]

[{"Name":"Noah Budz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0Ewk2p4lJMjX0ya6ZuSed77GhQR6jmylO5a7E4Iur3n7agfRd=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food is very good especially the build your own bowl. It used to be very reasonably priced for the portions but they have suddenly raised their prices by a fair amount, raising the prices of all the bowls by about $5 making the small build your own bowl the same price as the previous large build your own bowl. This is now in the range of overpriced food and can no longer recommend eating at this place anymore","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Don K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUeMe3Z2Dwdjz2ebe9Hu9zPz3XZzwiZvAUP2ovxUEYWB0bHcVvHYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":""Unique" Japanese Dining Experience: Bones and Bad Attitudes

Just had the most "memorable" visit to a supposedly authentic Japanese restaurant in town, and let me tell you, it was quite an experience! 🍣🙄

If you're a fan of eel, I suggest you bring your own toolkit for removing bones because this place apparently believes in quantity over quality. 🐟😣 I've never encountered so many bone spurs in a single dish before, talk about a challenge!

The icing on the cake was the lovely attitude of the staff, especially the charming individual I suspect to be the owner. 🙄👎 If you're looking for that authentic Japanese politeness and hospitality, well, you won't find it here. They seemed more interested in asserting their authority than making guests feel welcome.

So, if you're in the mood for a unique dining experience that defies traditional Japanese standards, this is the spot for you! Otherwise, I'd suggest looking elsewhere if you want genuine quality and respectful service. Suddenly people started bringing their friends into line. Just about in 10 minutes we were crossed by 50 people. We waited for 45 minutes . We ended up leaving even being in good position in the line. There should be a rule for people who do not respect that others are waiting in the line. They should learn to respect and join the line from behind where the line starts, not to just around in middle. If you people love to bringing your friends randomly in the middle of the line. Then should also go back and join with them. Learn the professionalism of FIFO.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kai Kuelz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViWLpA3-vhfqtuM417wDaF7xiKwUhaIRXTGmtiwwd2n3GX3vBQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The security guards wouldn’t leave me alone the whole time. They pat me up and down shortly after I ordered my drinks and searched my bag. They eventually kicked me out after my friend went home for the night after pulling me aside multiple times to investigate what I’m doing. I was dancing and partying like everyone else. I can’t help but feel that I was singled out as a trans individual but they didn’t really give me a reason for forcing me out aside from the fact that I had drank quite a bit. Would not recommend coming here if you are LGBTQ+, especially trans. Waste of money.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSGp8SPKwcNjAB3HE-frfHnir9J2_4NoDkRqNK\u0026fid=0x0:0x14e80a2a1bf91fbe"],"When":"2024-4-6"},{"Name":"Rod Boss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQ7UxZLY6XJEIlLvm2eotizE36hG8YuFIh4GH9Z_NNVeriFjYM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was a great place to go to. Not the venue's fault more about the security however since it was part of the experience I couldn't go over 7/10.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPKdEl9spfQDJQF0VkmLuyn3BIUlJupFyuJsdm\u0026fid=0x0:0x14e80a2a1bf91fbe"],"When":"2023-3-17"},{"Name":"Luana De Sousa Carvalho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6rdPNFdHVRdn_9nViEtf-U6NQxK0R3xHyG-YkKRb3GBv7N2UcFw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wednesdays are for the squad 🔌 they’ll play your song request :)\n\nBottle service available","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfik3ujr1O_CUTXFQSlrmBh6u02X6xOvU_htxq\u0026fid=0x0:0x14e80a2a1bf91fbe"],"When":"2023-9-29"},{"Name":"rathik kashyap","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOIiPnDT2NQ1XacTueKvhVQyFywZlFdx5zg18kEav0lo4Z0rY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Hello. I am messaging regarding an incident which happened at the after party of the holi event. I arrived to the party with my group consisting of both boys and girls. I think mentioning that there were girls in my group is necessary for the stereotype behaviour which we went through.  There was a guard/bouncer, wouldn’t know what his designation was but the moment we arrived he targeted me stating that “you are too intoxicated to go inside”, mind you he let my other friends pass. I tried to reason with him that I was not intoxicated but he didn’t budge. I tried to come around a few times and the third time I tried there was someone else who let me in asking what the problem was. Clearly the person who let me in saw that I was not intoxicated. He even made a joke about it and we all laughed. This was already very insulting and humiliating for me. Later when we were inside the man again targeted our group but this time he pointed out to another guy that he’s intoxicated. Funny thing the guy he pointed out doesn’t even drink. It clearly shows that the man’s ego got hurt because the other guy let us in. He kicked my friend out solely on assumption that he was drunk. He even accused us of teasing girls. That was completely uncalled for. I have no idea why he was targeting us but he ruined our night, wasted our time and money. I am messaging this to you so something can be done about it. I cannot emphasise more on the point of it being absolutely humiliating. I hope you question that person or at least some action is taken against him. This was downright harassment.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Henry Lawson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKrVcBfk4jvR6H06WX-8L1W5-YaCibqm968OzCac7VgiiWkFg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Terrible queue management. Had a ticket for guest list but spent an hour in the queue. Terrible management something needs to change","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sandwich is a good size and lots of thin layers of meat: I got the medium Hat Trick on wheat, and it’s more than enough for lunch.

Cookie is pretty tiny, though.

If you order online, be sure to customize the sandwich to add veggies in.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOJUjYVedl9wR8yjoTYL8wKGYJPJhKyi0x8r4N&fid=0x0:0xbc372dfd791dd8c4"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Okay, here we go. Firehouse Subs. Wow!! They’re so good. First of all, the best staff ever at the UBC branch—thanks for all the hard work there. We ordered for the first time and got two subs: one Montreal smoked meat and one NewYork Steamer, and we loved them. We loved them so much that we ordered again the next day—one Steak & Cheese and one Pepperoni Pizza Meatball—and again, we loved those. We’re probably going to keep ordering until we find our favorite. So far, we like these four in this order: Montreal Smoked Meat, Steak & Cheese, New York Steamer, and then Pepperoni Pizza Meatball. All of them are 7.5/10 or higher, so they’re really close. The pepperoni one is at the bottom of the list because the marinara sauce was a bit overwhelming, making it hard to really get to the pepperoni and meatball.

We also ordered the chili bowl and garlic bread. The garlic bread is nice—normal garlic bread. You could get creative and make it a bit more interesting, but I kind of liked it with their special sauce. But the chili bowl is on another level—so good.

As you can guess, I’m definitely going to keep trying them again and again. Hope they keep up the good quality. 🥖 🚒 🔥

[Update, 2024, Aug 15]
Ordered two new subs:
1. Hat Trick Sub: A bit too much barbeque sauce, if you like bbq sauce a lot go for it. Enjoyed it. 7/10
2. Smokehouse Beef & Cheddar Brisket: again a bit too smoky for me. I enjoyed the beef and cheddar combination a lot tho. 7/10
Still everything is great and they're 5/5. 🔥","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNthhpGT-IdxtuSBJ3GBYDhSBF10nfABiTaR73v&fid=0x0:0xbc372dfd791dd8c4"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Alexandra Rousseau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCc1VRoWPX9lI6oLLlSyZp1wtcpy95ye2Jq395pgPsfvG22Z41=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Quick service and delicious sub. Lots of sandwich options, and large portions. I got the size medium, and I would say that there’s almost triple the meat of a Subway sub, would recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoSQpMVsainpAjodr6k3jnXld5Pk-Px0cMCsHi&fid=0x0:0xbc372dfd791dd8c4"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKf1RSg3_-AU0iu6cewVgjwGYoJmZNxdRNJCv62pXrCH7QK-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The presentation on this sandwich is amazing, it's restaurant quality. The flavor is, all I can say about this the best way to describe it, is this is a sexy sandwich! The staff were wonderful, talking to them I believe that they are treated very well by the owners. Which shows, cuz if you treat your staff father treat the customers well and they did, and they were good at their job as well. They all noticed when I walked in and when I left. The only thing I should mention, is I ordered a tuna (now I'm not sure why it wasn't on the board, but unfortunately there are some adjustments that could be made to the recipe. It might be, because when I enjoyed the sandwich, it was very wet, which tells me that when it was taken out of the can the fluid wasn't drained. So the Mayo is that was added was diluted a lot, Celeste liquid more mayo, as well the sandwich does need mustard for a tuna, and some black pepper would be ideal and a little bit of salt to bring out the flavor. )which was not on the board and I nearly walked out, except for the fact that I decided to ask just in case. So I think that listing that on the board would be great, cuz now I actually wonder what other hidden sandwiches you might have that are not listed. I will definitely be going back, and I don't even live in the city! A massive portion well worth the money, and I don't even know what it cost because I didn't care I was excited to find a place that my look and smell was really fresh.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHOmq62IGYnTZA43FR0ZLo308gMqm-CpD6eL9z&fid=0x0:0xbc372dfd791dd8c4"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Javidd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxIKHySek0FG53i0J4L70VrPkQxUMcSPGhMR3Qfp-EChdJEQU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrible sandwiches. Ordered a *pulled* chicken breast. What I got was a pathetic thing with huge, thick chunks of tasteless chicken breast 💀💀 The bread could not even hold these pieces of chicken. Nothing “pulled” about it

It’s unfortunate to see their qualities went downhill so quickly..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOD6uQ-CSmqe4qalRNGOGi8p-bqbzUo4gPg6hJY&fid=0x0:0xbc372dfd791dd8c4"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"John","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0dx-qAKgAKuEOeYA2KjNPHRCtWsDoi-sBydzQ5pea-AwJVaGq=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"From a gluten free perspective this is some of the worst food ive had and thats saying something. Ive been to firehouses all throughout the stated and they are generally incredibly consistent with a gf bun that doesnt make you mind paying extra. 3$ extra for a bun made of styrofoam is a major disappointment. Ruined the entire sandwich.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxgV-eFBk6t2rnaz9nKIEWNSvUQi8dW0PpZgrl&fid=0x0:0xbc372dfd791dd8c4"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"Adil OKUMUŞ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWILc9czCClsi1y9wPizaOjmclU9tapIH8_ES7EWExaSXRNOBnE2g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They have the freshest ingredients and a really good bread. The ingredients were generously put for a medium sandwich it was really filling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOX66yqZIIMOGQBXing6yys_JZ5RCYEBJhLiWNW&fid=0x0:0xbc372dfd791dd8c4"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Sam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXy7QZpn3Go4ZyAjfglxnKhqLNrYMMjJHTl8vpSDqgWHpvmziI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered online, but the sandwich was absolutely top tier. Got the Italian and it had plenty of meat, delicious sauce, and a nice amount of good veg. Excited to try them in person!! Would highly recommend to anyone!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Stephen Mac","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUoPC8lYoGwhrnfIc_f4se0z42VgmocbQORloZc6SPdkmVh6n0z=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"A great spot to visit during Happy Hour, conveniently located near the UBC Bookstore. They have outdoor picnic tables, perfect for enjoying sunny days. While their morning coffee and pastries are tasty, the lunch menu and beer selection are somewhat limited. Additionally, the food options are on the pricier side, with smaller portion sizes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbT3drdK9xEv2ja7-_sP67frGGeqnQHNZyU6RE&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Chloe Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgExGuK1W-XgQc1tPnrQlqQkWxCTaNhdz977uVTTY3zjpsAzs-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Subpar experience at Loafe for brunch on a Friday. The location is quite popular for students, with many tables filled by students with their laptops/books! We couldn't find an available table, so had to settle for sofas outside the café (inside the alumni centre). I could barely taste the oat milk in my decaf Americano, and the blend was not very strong itself. The hot chocolate was fine. The Mushroom Ricotta Rice Bowl ($13.95) had a nice marinade on the mushrooms, and a decent amount of ricotta (on a bed of rice and arugula). The rice is very plain, and perhaps a little mushy/overcooked.

I was disappointed with their Midnight in Havana Rice Bowl ($15), having asked for no arugula, and it coming with the bowl anyways. The place was packed so I didn't feel like asking them to remove it. The pork shoulder was not tender (it was more like dry pulled pork). They were able to use a balsamic dressing instead of their garlic aioli at my request, which was nice of them to accommodate. There are some inconsistencies with their in-store menu and what's online on their Square site, as the Square site says the bowl comes with caramelized onions, but in-store it's pickled onions. On top of the pickled jalapenos, I thought it was too much acidity toppings wise and would have benefited from the caramelized type. Self-service after you receive your order. Would be interested in trying their baked goods (which are unlabelled in their display case), but would skip the bowls.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiE8GLojK31GVv4M8k9y-jJfyWRKUikLidQ0ZW&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Roman Kozak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXaei_E5eRgQInxhzdn1QSNV_at7npoBUF_sdv7jvDoiE-7SM2Uw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"High quality food and pastries. Excellent coffee. Lots of indoor and outdoor seating but gets busy so hard to find seating.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEq_0tU5sB0MEcKHfk2ujiVdIA1tltgD1iAZz-&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Soefae Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWO7ZNgUf5Dwk1W_QTwOUDH5IE-lT_O8VF-ftw5oM5hbRZ-8oOz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried this place after two separate friends recommended it to me. It was quite crowded and busy, but the wait for food wasn’t too bad. I loved the toast — creamy and crunchy — and the portion was great too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4E03kf6fYhGFCf_COAC14gCZPFHbjW4gjYUbj&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2024-2-16"},{"Name":"Sartaj Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1doLfhIpPIdYO53EoD_63mHYE3jrQc1kxM-CAvFcju93a6Z1xPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pretty great spot to grab a coffee or a bite! Great place to study too if you’re a student. Can work out to be a bit pricey for certain items but the quality is great! Service is good too but not as friendly as most places on campus. Pictured is a chocolate croissant and the Havana “sandwich” which is really a pulled pork burger but is not advertised as such (tasted great was just surprised by what I was served compared to the order).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlziy98Efwm1emaGHuaminWA-fhktmoVLuvY71&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2021-2-20"},{"Name":"Bahar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUU5aKs1eICwt862xHyk6eML8Nhxgoc_vXAN8CVDAAXDoHVGQ78=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I recently visited Loafe Cafe and had a mixed experience. The Huli Huli chicken sandwich was disappointing—completely tasteless and definitely overpriced for what it was. On the bright side, the Earl Grey tea latte was excellent—perfectly made and one of the best I’ve had in a while.

However, what really stood out was the service. Despite ordering food, we were politely asked to leave to free up some seats for other customers. While I appreciate the politeness, it was frustrating considering we were paying customers.

Overall, Loafe Cafe has potential, but they need to improve on the food quality and customer experience to justify the prices.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chels","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIEG8ImuHXjQ-hpfgYhplAhH9cls8PSmkmT9KPxEmPx9DwGMw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered smashed avo toast for breakfast but it was so cold as a toast. It costs almost 12 dollars.

I feel so unhappy and it is pricey as such a toast. I won’t come here again for any sandwiches.

The server said the kitchen staff didn’t work this morning.

The food is so bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxOhRzHWMZG6JrD4sH-xnGaPJ51NdAA0A_CanW&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2023-9-17"},{"Name":"Josh Adams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSvEV1wbWNmITPLILC0Yrj8KqIzEYTYtwHybPjIq7PlceuYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I used to be a regular customer at the Sauder location, however once I found out my favourite Barista “Tom” had left I was quite upset (still great staff at Sauder, just different ya kno).
However I was walking past the Alumni Center Location and saw a familiar face smiling behind the counter, lo and behold, it was Tom! He is now the manager at the Alumni Center location and I have never been happier.
Hearing his kind voice say “how’s it going Josh? You want the usual?” was music to my ears. He even recommended his personal favourite “chicken avocado rice bowl” and it was amazing. I’ll definitely be returning to this Loafe cafe and am excited to see what changes Tom brings to the cafe.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyG6LpRVr068PHL6LI0b4McMll6dKr_xChK8fl&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2024-6-14"}]

[{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Lots of seating at this Triple O’s location within the UBC campus. Menu is standard across all locations. You order at the counter and you get a number which they will call when your order is ready. Food is average fast food burger. Prices are a bit higher than the regular fast food restaurants. Service was relatively quick. Lots of garbage accumulated near the disposal area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkLm49YmLku_AT_Q089Oc1E98YewRHGmw1R3Tm&fid=0x0:0x688850f7f499fe90"],"When":"2023-12-27"},{"Name":"Hugh Gao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFlJmYlj82sx6sLKOje56IkZUG693ZnITvHtJUekoopvQlVKt9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great burgers that are a bit more expensive than other fast food restaurants, but worth the price. Come on Tuesdays for cheaper prices. Online ordering is also pretty convenient.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2RdCBbOiZ1lANFnbMlv4MR8BgSqpY_v82i2CAQnMwId2nHX4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The salad they served me is made of rotten lettuce! Please see the pictures! Look like garbage!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQL0I3B_Z8sBDNSTudKyJkRHZqCemrsx9iJNut&fid=0x0:0x688850f7f499fe90"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Hari haran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIiG04_8rXv0XFEGQSVtxLwFR51JdEUoQ099gTHIIYGUB0FAw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Unfortunately I had small dark colored particles from the straw provided for the milkshake. See attached photos.

Seems like a good place to grab a veggie burger. But the plastics problem is a big one ! I didn't realize it until I came home 😔","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_-94PYLbNgDNUQ9Wwo9-UfyZbDt7ThhOb0hB1&fid=0x0:0x688850f7f499fe90"],"When":"2024-3-20"},{"Name":"Tony A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZiODPA4JsIbC6cSBJZ_RVgZ4q0TYfuzdShQyHwHbnBVpMEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The only Triple O’s that charges $ for the infamous sauce if requested on the side…ridiculous!!
The service wasn’t anything special either- I got burnt fries.
However, an excellent location and clean","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lucas Chretien","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIn-MzI_6UqyLKUeJcrIQPohlzHiJxP-XYcCE0C3c2gTcLOig=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Sry but this burger ruined my day. The meat patty was just so dry and bad. Although, in fairness, I did like the milshake and the crunchy lettuce in the burger. So, if u want to come here, just get the shakes, or the lettuce. Cheers.

PS. The fries also suck","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joanna “바내나” Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIfdnARYVIBDrr_F-1nTbFy1pge1d4Xtp6cphSFg6T8dGPwwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I usually never post reviews but here I am.

SERVICE HERE IS 0. Ordered the simplest original burger with fries, IT TOOK 20 MINS to come out ALTHOUGH the food was right there on the counter already done made. The lady in charge of sending out the menu was so unrespectful and irresponsible. I have asked the woman to check if there was any mistake in the order, she did not even bother to ask my order number and just told me to wait. Cashiers receive as many orders as possible, but have no ability to serve the orders they received without making the customers wait for such a long time. Their organizing system is messed up and they don’t know what they’re doing most of the time.

I ended up receiving the food that I ordered, but the plate had a different number on it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMIF06Q4wknrfMEKceeThMYIdsfxuUMLkefsNKu&fid=0x0:0x688850f7f499fe90"],"When":"2019-1-22"},{"Name":"Hagen Lai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI0JsecRNUVWZmLoLdCDfqA77CYNv2Z44tPR1pD5xKgpWQBtg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Onion rings were sitting on the counter long before I ordered. They were not fresh and barely warm.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tried their cinnamon bun and it was surprisingly delicious in taste and texture. Reheated it at home and it was extra tasty. Lots of cinnamon flavour but also not too dense and heavy. It’s an above average cinnamon bun.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcTrXmy2mk7KggpQXy6Kc5QBBMvTE6uOJYeztz&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-9-15"},{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I’m told Blue Chip is known for its cookies: their chunky chocolate chip cookie is quite decadent and unhealthy (as all good cookies are).

The egg sandwich makes it clear why they’re not known for their sandwiches. To be fair, the multigrain bread is pretty great, and you really better like bread if you order their sandwiches because it’s pretty much all bread: there’s a thin layer of filling inside as if just to flavour the bread. Sandwich places are not so often pitiful: the egg salad itself, I do a way better one at home; I swear this had to be store bought in bulk.  $7++. No wonder people pack lunches here.

Service is certainly fine: you line up and place your order like any other quick-service café, and they did toast it nicely (on one side) for me.

Overall, as a student organization operated outfit, you'd think they would try to offer better value for revenue-less students.

Note that Blue Chip has moved from their small location (in the same building, by the side) to the airy south end of the Nest. Lots of seating everywhere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzLTMm7Za2T10ggJ62fHI4Rw32gE5i5Q3UFuVI&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-7-26"},{"Name":"Lancelot Xu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUU7AtUL5RSbEqhx7nxJ8l31yO7iHUO4yb3ZiKg_LXM4h2NF1s=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Blue Chip Cafe is a gem! The food is always fresh, delicious, and beautifully presented. Their menu has a great variety, and every dish I’ve tried has been flavorful and satisfying. The atmosphere is cozy, and the staff are friendly and welcoming. Highly recommend for a quality meal and coffee!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0SGKwzYKBmMXlDRjkyIbr59KLBWS4m0ujDRsP&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-11-14"},{"Name":"Alex Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpCadF-dmx5XTlgh_E5TB__7n649M3gDsKp0UgTsGtzt1oywZE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Solid bagels and pastries, matcha is decent too. Great atmosphere with plenty of seating overlooking the ground floor. A little pricey for food after factoring the single use containers fees.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4xZLMQjg1UFWQF2VZHZx0apLyoKKoM6O1eEWF&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-7-5"},{"Name":"Kayla Mizuki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcEGcj5JPeyIAIQJw3qGO8j1u7XbI927-7frVyMbwPWPc2pbjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a UBC student, I can’t emphasize enough how I enjoy this bagel every single day for school. These bagels are unbelievably soft and undoubtedly the most delicious treats I’ve ever tasted, almost like savory bagel cakes. My top recommendation is the rosemary bagel with butter; it’s under $3 and easily my favorite bagel in the city. It’s bittersweet to be done with school for the year, knowing I won’t get to savor this daily delight anymore.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOekSWPTjiTB-hlKTDXA7-GvWCVwJVJMEKLM6hx&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-5-1"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Known for their freshly baked cookies, it’s also a pretty good all-around cafe, although quality is a mixed bag ranging from okay to great depending on what you order. The great: most cookies, bagels and bagel sandwiches, date square, butter mochi, muffins and loaves. The okay: pre-made sandwiches and wraps, sugar cookies and vegan cookie, dessert bars besides the date square, and tiramisu. The coffee is more variable but generally pretty good, and I think the matcha latte is actually one of the best on campus (or at least the smoothest). Do not order an iced London fog/turmeric fog though - they tell you they can make it, but you will get a cold tea bag in watery milk, not a properly steeped iced tea latte.
The students who work there are usually pretty friendly and the speed of service is reasonable even though the line gets long at lunchtime when school is in session. Like other AMS-owned outlets, you can not only bring your own drink cup but also bring your own food containers and save $.25 per item.
They recently moved across the Nest to a bigger space with more seating. With the move, they now offer for-here mugs for hot drinks, but you have to be kind of aggressive if you want one - you have to say you want your drink for here, in a mug, and probably repeat yourself, otherwise they will probably ignore you, I guess because they’re not expecting it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqKjJmYV6mZmMyuj4wO5b6DaK9WwoWHXvk-COc&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2023-7-24"},{"Name":"Bekah French","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiYLh-7emQ9AthzE2N_CGxwmtRUdZguPeMRuVIWmhyOtllxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Visited new location on Saturday (on opposite side of building to where they were before). Ordered Turkey and Brie, without the Brie. Very yummy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmZNOxehejwf2wBMhNJWaXcSR-jtZKucO-MKCI&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Rhofa Mae Realista","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLDRtU7fV1AfY8do5JUFssXSrDFilnJOloJt5l_LixJpPuW-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This cafe makes one of the best iced matcha lattes! The place is REALLY busy (I usually go here during lunch so ofc it’ll be busy), but the line moves quite quickly. The staff are full of smiles despite working nonstop to accommodate customers. Took around 10 minutes for me to receive my drink, but it’s all good since it’s busy. They also have tables in front and around so you can study or chill after.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good coffee and lattes, with great seasonal specials. The desserts are delicious and reasonably priced. My favourites are the tiramisu and matcha parfaits. The prepackaged sushi available in the fridge is edible but not great, the sandwiches are better but still nothing special - I would come for the drinks and snacks, not the food. The staff is usually friendly and quick at making drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKaY80NvBrp9MejmRXGXmZFkt4EuAqiv-HNs4Q\u0026fid=0x0:0x1d82acab1faef3e3"],"When":"2022-11-26"},{"Name":"Manu Goyal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZ9bGCnzhlvZbFUtYdBmuIDxw5aGDmnpBiY-LPoM3HSUmqDce-uA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Tried latte and tiramisu here. I asked for extra hot latte but it was cold when I got it. And tiramisu was good taste wise but it was very watery from the bottom and looked like it was made a few days ago. It would’ve been really delicious if it had been fresh. You wouldn’t want to eat old stuff when you’re paying that much money. Instead of spending 12 bucks on only coffee and tiramisu I’d say it’s better to check out the kitchen next door. It’s just $16 for unlimited food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOu2ouFAuJdpws1H7wpXAcuZRoFm0GGWpnBn9RY\u0026fid=0x0:0x1d82acab1faef3e3"],"When":"2023-12-3"},{"Name":"phoebe chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgGAAqUtg35VI0StSFv5qlfLxxuWpGYhE1ErUcNuvoAqdMRwU-=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Yum coffee at UBC. We always grab coffee here before starting our grind at McLeod (walking distance).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkx97tqCQMA8q30lW1xq0P86Es7ClQypguo_AC\u0026fid=0x0:0x1d82acab1faef3e3"],"When":"2024-3-3"},{"Name":"Sartaj Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1doLfhIpPIdYO53EoD_63mHYE3jrQc1kxM-CAvFcju93a6Z1xPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing coffee (get the Papa New Guinea pour over). Their cookies are amazing too including the Mexican wedding cookie!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emily Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtvkqUTGqKJKZItQ-dpfTy5xGKvVe2IaCtHawVqb-9NXvJNjqP4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Coffee was ok… definitely don’t go there for food. Also couldn’t get my stroller around their display to get to the fridge. They sometimes have Mochi here and sometimes don’t. Their frozen cheesecakes are also always missing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hash Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLExeuh0C9VNkYa2zON0uFAstj3F0xPIKlp5QJJJRUEiJHWQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst service ever. One female server of an Indonesian ethnicity gave me a bad attitude as she IGNORED me, because I was wearing a cheap hoodie that day. It is certainly concerning how such a snobbish woman can get a job here, and it is appalling to see such disingenuous behavior toward the customers. I am cynical toward the way this place is managed, cynical to the snobs that work there, and downright appalled by the discrimination that occurs here on a day to day basis.\n\nA comment to the owner's response: Yes I do remember when this happened, approximately a year ago. I remember it so vividly because of my disbelief in such an appalling service attitude. It concerns me that unqualified workers such as this person work in UBC's food services, and I find it incompetent of you being oblivious of situations like this.","Images":null,"When":""}]
