[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of the better cafes at UBC for quality. Service can be a little slow and people camp here to study, so it’s pretty difficult to get a table inside during late morning-mid afternoon on weekdays (the patio is easier and quieter when weather permits). On the weekends, though, it’s very quiet.
Food and drink are generally good, especially sandwiches. The kimchi grilled cheese and avocado toast are my favourites. They have lots of vegan and gluten free baked goods, though these are sometimes dry or underbaked. The matcha latte is a little weak.
I would definitely recommend this Loafe over the chains or UBC-owned cafes. It’s comparable in overall quality to other independent shops on campus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAprulsuk_dAkmTTBr7HCi3HBB1DpdgdWrlVgw&fid=0x0:0x94d026007847cea1"],"When":"2023-2-27"},{"Name":"Naheed G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKCMr_R2sPkvHyPnPR1A8YtFfOj7NFXUnGWqEdJIzLrWna4ufVnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Avocado toast was the 3rd option I chose - the 1st two items weren't available. For $12, i got one piece of bread. Not impressed when I leave a place hungry hungrier than when I arrived.  Feed.Your.Students.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEoDcmfLpSqp56JQ-zl-JnExBA2Ze8EsfC13Hm&fid=0x0:0x94d026007847cea1"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Ben Wells","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-91uU5BSvZ5NPIXZC1dHenwZQufEwUCi4pg29RVkdAJ-ALjIM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I don't understand why this place has a 4+ star rating. Every time I stop here for something I'm disappointed by some aspect of the experience. Consider:
**Value**
- For a $6 oat milk flat white, they use the cheap 2L earth's own oat milk, not delicious Barista oat milk as at most premium cafes (eg Great Dane coffee), resulting in a watery, bad tasting flat white or latte.
- On an $11 breakfast sandwich, there is only 1/2 an egg!!! Or the $11 avocado toast has like 3 tbsp of avocado on it and a teaspoon of feta. Their aggressive control of ingredient portions makes the prices totally unreasonable.
- The $5 treats like brownies, lemon bars etc are made en masse and frozen, and kept too many days in a row: they taste like fridge and have poor texture. Absolutely not worth it. (the spinach and feta croissant is a bit more reliable)
**Service**
- Every single time I find myself wondering how the service is so slow. They don't train the team to be attentive to orders or to move with pace. On my last order, the kitchen person was picking mint leaves off of stems very slowly and chatting to the barista. They ignored or did not notice when the food order came out of the printer right by their face, and took a full 5 mins to start making the order. Once they did, they became distracted: I could hear the oven beeping after toasting the bun for a full min after it was finished before someone else picked up the task. Note, the cafe was NOT busy at this time. Just inefficient. Slowness is a theme every time I order from there.
**Atmosphere**
This part is fine! Nice that they have the patio space.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A great place for a quick bite during classes! They have really good sandwiches, though I am not too huge on their drinks. But they do have a decent price for their portions and taste. I highly recommend their bacon and cheese sandwich :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZFVf-F0nOX9IKuvrT3YxrP0bXoHXvfLP0xWvC&fid=0x0:0x94d026007847cea1"],"When":"2023-10-4"},{"Name":"M D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgYfqGJ25uGc8cn5Foi08q73KwDbqZaEL9gTHw5c043KXpcnID=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The drinks are quite terrible. Bad enough to write a review so that should say something. The atmosphere is the only thing that really saves it. Overall just go somewhere else to spend $8 on a latte","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Allison Chao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1_VXjvqeFRnOuPZPqR4all6wEIKzVuAp-eQ-1290s2ubS2w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I ordered a matcha latte with oat milk, however, they made it with regular milk instead. Matcha flavour wasn’t really strong either so kinda disappointing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marvin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIOUB9fqPRyAnJAGsLqhyOV_Bp81x_bJC8wIyyATYNP2vGJzmc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Busy and wasn’t able to get a seat, got the garlic chicken sandwich and it was pretty good, however more on the expensive side for the portion. Would try some of the other items on the menu. Overall alright.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Josh Adams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSvEV1wbWNmITPLILC0Yrj8KqIzEYTYtwHybPjIq7PlceuYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went to this Loafe cafe instead of my usual Tim Hortons, and oh boy, I’m never going to Timmie’s again. The Turkey Club sandwich was SOOO good, the coffee was tasty and the guy who served me (Tom I think) was a ray of sunshine on a cloudy morning. His smile felt genuine and warm, not like the faked smile I usually get at Timmie’s. 10/10 service, 10/10 sandwich and I’ll definitely be going back.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Jeffrey Cheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuvw0DoMq0pOe2JGvzQ4U1FjBGerEQ4O70pk3YVGChUNSu7g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Update: I sent an email 2 months ago after the owner's review and have NOT received a reply at all. They have not done anything nor kept their promise. Totally soured by the customer service and have adjusted that to 1 star. Absolutely frustrated to see that happening and will never go back to the restaurant again.

The pasta was okay, nothing special and the pizza was awful, so watery","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAiQ5ZLOeaIrS5F737cTKWhpPO1WHu_H6eZ73O&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Wii Games","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1LF1yLZYvfPxybsCpHOF5AtzGVIeAoFgQLne7csT7MMJt7gY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Considering their pizzas are priced at a premium (average of 25 dollars,) you would expect their pizzas to be of higher quality. The toppings taste fresh, but the pizzas are extremely runny and the dough is very chewy even for Neapolitan style pizza. The crust lacks the air and lightness of other places. I also noticed that they don't use any wood in their oven, which just doesn't achieve the same flavor profile.

In terms of the service, i have come to this place a few times and seen the waiters talking and not noticing myself or other guests that come in at times.

The atmosphere overall is not bad, but personally i feel as though the place has an industrial feeling and is not the most welcoming .","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brad Snelling","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEo3ECglbJcC95bDjcm377gDXh3jMd9KEP9ANqJRBVc9D4SrM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Thank you Maddie for the great service and the birthday cake…and thanks to chefs Shaq and Yuriko for the tasty food (the Il Bastardo and Salami e Funghi pizzas and the pasta cream pasta were amazing!).  I will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNB5_ERDFOPMNUkHdMilCQ_UHzkC088WqZp8ggb&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Eve C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3TRd28YHMD0xZgG9Qff6WuaVQUBD8KHHFSJUDtDhJtE0o6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was really excited to hear that Nicli has reopened in Wesbrook. I used to go to the gastown location all the time and was sad when they closed. I heard they are under new ownership, so we were weren’t sure what to expect. Luckily, it was still just as delicious as I remember 😋

We came for lunch and ordered four pizzas to share amongst 6 people. It was the perfect amount of food and we left very satisfied. They also have a lunch menu with slightly smaller pizzas and pasta options. The pizzas were full of quality ingredients and incredibly delicious. Our server was so friendly and made sure we were well taken care of. Will be coming back more often 🩷","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alysia Duemler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOP2WaoVuXuPDA2rQrEDkqLAVmEa-LLcH53nj472C_ni_q4VtISQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such a charming neighbourhood Italian restaurant with many gluten-free and vegetarian options, thankfully. It was the best pizza I’ve had in Vancouver, the cocktails were refreshing, the server was friendly, funny and attentive, and the atmosphere was pleasant. Had a nice little date there and would recommend. It’s nice to be able to sit outside, too. The prices are also fair.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcjHM66qrYK1NntlYCYUZ5aePNW-D9gzlCt-Gq&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2023-8-25"},{"Name":"Michael Moriarity","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNhkYaB9zjlkkl74OBPcplO2QslT6bqh419yvto-fc4bLKxsqAKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This local pizza location in UBC Westbrook Mall invites the pizza and Italian food scene customer for a fine tasting menu..we chose the Salimi & Fungi pizza and the Bolognese pasta…there was a warm welcome and we appreciated the many items on the menu…there was plenty of parking in the area..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNx9nIE0qOANzuFm6Ak0SYk8JNr2vubnJicmWxq&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-2-27"},{"Name":"Ray Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3wj8Ne3ngI4eg9ouEU6zPmvERlQuudbckz4ma4Vg6pfYrsWM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The service was excellent. There was only one server and one chef but the two were very efficient. We really enjoyed the Napoli style pizza, and the fresh pasta had an interesting fusion sauce with a mixture of miso and carbonara. The guanciale in the carbonara sauce was rich and and full of flavour. The pasta was perfectly al dente and picked up the sauce nicely.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_SKvNF7awsi_PmQuHT87A8CDKGDP9aZlr2pKR&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"Ishita Malik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWV5NuG1NBDfsD_WLq2-zLuV8LgB51UWdsUfOaqy47D5rsrTXb5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went there 3-4 times for some authentic Italian food.
Was so glad to see they had so many vegan options, gluten free, dairy free. And even said they can substitute any of the ingredients for vegan.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFFFm767jOmR1P2iGRESAiZf8Zoovic4TFcWxj&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2023-8-30"}]

[{"Name":"Frank Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_FRblBfSgHTr-UE0tiLX-XMrs2VlygGYnC4upIgoM9g7vtg6H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The beef bento didn’t have tempuras. Sushi is very quality for Vancouver standards.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOoyABnsH0HDFxgk3Q5EPPiKc_8p8FFPcNWidyM&fid=0x0:0xf3a92119710ebb23"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Moh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUURXtN_rXoKjrzbodNAJoJdyyunaG5DUkiAvqgEbBIvPZ35zjP=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Consistently fresh and delicious!

I have been ordering from this location of Togo Sushi multiple times a week since 2019. They have always been exceptionally friendly, their food has always tasted great with noticeably fresh ingredients, and most importantly is they're consistently good at providing these measures of quality! I have never had a bad experience here.

Clean and convenient location and very fair prices!

Their menu offers a great selection of items, I understand they aren't world class, what they offer is some very classic items, and a small menu of special rolls that is always satisfying. My mouth is watering in anticipation of my next order!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9n6R_94uKjbA4gnHDpOU5pUPWD8IlYPDL4fsh&fid=0x0:0xf3a92119710ebb23"],"When":"2021-8-6"},{"Name":"Andrew Varley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLjnq84TKWkg-tLqF45oNeQLJbZsKNJSF5Wh6BdqPtFv1Xd1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is the only sushi option in Wesbrook  so I'm thankful to have it, but it's pretty simple and not great value. Whenever I have the option, I prefer to go into Vancouver for sushi.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Robert Faber","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqlViLqCEhpGzgcEARoB-mqp64QIrzZlu6T999j9zGAfEPnw_J=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I’m visiting Vancouver which has incredible sushi…normally. The texture of the fish was like biting a whole raw fish straight from an icebox. Yuck","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Adrian Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJRz_uEV8AM70-EugybmCMjVZLIi0OfMP3My2LKS1PidWwGuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Decent quality sushi for a reasonable price. Found the cooked food to be not as good. Service is friendly and reasonably quick but the location can sometimes be a bit busy around lunch so be prepared for a short wait after ordering. Enjoyed the Maki combo.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObxgSafmjFMuJ5l3yWyz6uc13Q1ijoIifYT7GH&fid=0x0:0xf3a92119710ebb23"],"When":"2021-10-8"},{"Name":"F52","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUA5hxcDaUg_IcmxK7gW_t5jVMBKXVPVI5gzaMoDUvqo8gvlj_M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food and service. [{"Name":"Moses Anderson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqP9o2Mxh1TbUgGeu8SzUgOoEYSltQvoNI1vKtAa_4jpobxCL5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing baked goods! I am very impressed that the vegan and GF muffins are large, have good texture, and lots of flavours to choose from 👍 Also, even my cat seems to like the scones.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbx7PB-wr1q7IhJ04-Yt0yTK7qPtHQNSMcLR9W&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love their sandwiches! The atmosphere is great, they have a mini bonfire outdoor sitting which I love. It does get packed during school term tho. The drinks are ok.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOS_Zq_evUK07fQpAswcFGj_GtmlHZX4AUnVmz_&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Jamie Glennon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLOjs5-jqgyQWUX_yOuzgUG9TpUgCo3VZBWVH5vnxr8HdflLs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great spot close to Chan Centre and Gage Towers for a high quality coffee and baked good in the morning.

Much better than the chain coffee shops!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWllLnH-9j6g8HteXdulm-5IuO4DeupNnsxwGs&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"Justbeing Sam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWM9hiJK-AfVP-qSHlK2ogC-KKU9aHv9jB-f8Zpy8fNkox9PG5e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nestled in a cozy corner, this cafe is a warm embrace of delicious coffee and friendly vibes in UBC . Baristas greet you with smiles, crafting your perfect cup with care. Vintage decor and irresistible pastries add to the charm, making it the perfect spot to unwind and connect.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIzHKWJ5uIM5OYLtmxcD6VblvJoIt7iesMyagS&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2024-3-22"},{"Name":"Eden","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgHIQ66Jm9chZEYySFVv8p0ryPQbWvKkG3vS_9dnDINf-CKCV_ZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This beautiful cafe is highly suggested if you ever decide to staycation or study at UBC.

It is a pet-friendly cafe and offers quality products of fresh sandwiches, espressos, delicious homemade pastries [ with options of gluten-free], and spacious atmosphere with an outdoor fireplace! The staff were so welcoming, friendly, and excellent counter-costumer service.

Their business hours may not meet your needs nor expectations but they'll be opening early and close late once school starts in September.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyppoj0m0i95g6EEpfFj7iN4tIukn51d2QckpU&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2021-8-8"},{"Name":"Jessica Lu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTqZgPj0eXg_JYgAnVgUcTOilpA24BvBnkompjw1nEkEUn2g3_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Only been here once and ordered a matcha latte. It sucks. Tastes like milk and the matcha flavour is absent. My mistake for ordering drinks when this place is known for their sandwiches. The latte art was cute.

Staff are very kind and efficient especially because this place gets super busy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tario Sultan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVs5egw4ytTDIua69pxGET59kVTaWgbfGJaRgqyQl37e1dCXZiC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Dane Coffee shop located towards the north side of UBC campus.

The staff is super friendly and helpful. Pretty good quality coffee, the price is definitely reasonable.

Highly recommended!

Keep it up guys.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYAsbfa3t9q9Juj68FHljEPh0OO5hRwXWah_gi&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2022-12-14"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Iconic coffee shop at UBC. The staff is really chill and friendly so the vibe is great, and the food/drink is good all around. In particular they have some of my favourite scones around. Their veggie sandwich is very very good (as long as you're prepared for your hands to smell like focaccia for the rest of the day). Except for during the summer, they have a daily soup which is always very tasty. The regular dessert pastries (brownie, cookies, dessert bars) are all good but not stand-out good, but they sometimes have fancier cakes which are amazing.
For their drinks, it is also really hard to go wrong. The masala chai latte is amazing - it's sweet but also richly flavoured with spices. The London fog is also very good. Both of these tea lattes use stone ground tea instead of brewed tea which I think contributes to the intensity. They do a great job with the matcha latte too - it's never clumpy at all. I used to be not the biggest fan of their coffee, but it's grown on me a lot. It's a bit on the acidic side, but if you don't mind that, then the flavour is pretty nice. I really like their mocha too (especially the peppermint mocha available in winter) - this is actually the only place where I really get mochas!
They have pizza nights now (7-10 Wed-Fri) where you can get a flatbread pizza big enough to feed two for less than $15. Only the very basic flavours available (margherita, bianca, or pepperoni), but super tasty (and cheesy).
The seating inside is limited and the space is so narrow that I find it very hard to be comfortable inside unless you go during a rare quiet hour, but I love the patio, which is huge and mostly covered. They sometimes turn the fireplace on during the cold season.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWhxuY6zE3pvpsEAp5I-7RS-wKJgHl_8B7qvR0&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2020-10-24"}]

Additionally, the quality of the chicken was subpar.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfO5RDIAxL5yUixp2Xyode6M7MkXv8-zeEBtxY&fid=0x0:0xfba7b2899b4f414c"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"eshita Bhatia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUY-tStRltFZvbyB3WKXJ4NtHfoS2-Wo4TtAutQDeWB3ZjsK7aNpA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Only one worker working and doing everything. The milkshake tastes like chocolate milk, plain liquid, no thickness to it for $8. Waste of money, will not be returning","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Gong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVU6Nrm_sRXxa4lpEjkIrZxamz6LceMGV7mYsCaPEW4FMeyz2s=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Most over-priced burger and fries I have ever had in my life. I paid $20+ for those two low quality items, and I spent 20 mins waiting for my order. Unbelievable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN631R1cPS3wdtE7V2X44E-JEd_XK6KnfeYAx-X&fid=0x0:0xfba7b2899b4f414c"],"When":"2022-8-25"},{"Name":"Hoori Barkh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVsmGMB0Ma8Q_QX1b7LIeHjfj2OE3c7JiglHyQcJ3rqf9KbgA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Skip Vera’s!
Ordered online and paid, when we got to the store apparently they never received our order so we ordered again and paid (1 week later I’m still waiting for my online order refund).
Took a while to get the food ready (that’s fine, made fresh-ok) but the quality of the burgers was just mediocre. Nothing to complain about but nothing to rave about either.
Restaurant was completely empty on a Friday night. Surprised they are still in business to be honest.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eric Grant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhVR02aPzwVvQvqn63QlXyk0bgYy0E-LewKb9qSI5x_FX_h9ejyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"There are many great mysteries in life. How were the Pyramids built? What is Love? And most mysterious of all, how is this place still in business? It is always empty. Never go to an empty restaurant.
Only thing I tried was the chocolate milkshake. Was disappointed with the size, price, and texture and the time it took to make it. Why does it take 15 minutes to make a milkshake when I am the only one there? If you are going to get one make sure to ask for it well blended or get a spoon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Esmed P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPaVfVvhS7UlShhw7n3W_Eju3p15-TBYDAUGYnwKIb2zgwxN8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went during my lunch hour & ordered. I wait, & after 25 minutes pass watching the person who took my order have a conversation with another staff in the kitchen, I get up & start to hover at the counter. I guess they noticed, because I saw only then, did they start cooking my order. There's no ketchup available, so I asked for some. The lady seemed confused, then insited they keep it behind the counter. Finally after waiting another 20 minutes, I'm given my burger with smallest amount of ketchup possible, after this lady had sassed me about literally, 3 drips of water which fell from my fountain drink after pouring myself water. I didn't bother to try to ask for more kerchup I wanted. Bottom line, do not go here, unless you want horrendously slow & rude service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brian Taylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVS9FnL1Xm2VSimjexdVbc5QM_VHkzVtM3eQen6wRNt-IyDFLYSYA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I'm not sure how this place stays in business. I used the Vera's app to order a burger and got confirmation of my order at 6:12 pm, but the burger wouldn't be ready until 6:45 pm (not that the restaurant was the slightest bit busy). I showed up at the restaurant at 6:35 and the staff weren't aware of my order and asked what app I used. Really? Once the order was located they proceeded to make the burger and it was ready by 6:50. I had ordered a Vera burger ($10.50) with a few free toppings, cheese ($2 extra) and bacon ($2.50 extra). When I sat down to eat the burger I thought they'd forgotten the bacon so I brought it up to the counter. It was pointed out to me that there was a piece of bacon on the burger, but at most it was one square inch! For $2.50? The burger tasted fine and I've enjoyed Vera burgers for a long time, but if there were a Five Guys anywhere on the West Side I would never go back to Veras.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tano Pham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLZTH6gNWlc-cb4ja-Rt0oeskyJW7A4uEUVtm6QYAF2hoCk8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely terrible service on a non-school day at the UBC campus location by this employee. Had ordered my burger 35 minutes ahead on the app and she did not accept the order until I physically got there.
What is the point of skip the line function of the app if takes your money and not process your order","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuESOGkrJ4ca-F7MGAy2wyT8MDyLvBk6Wdks6G&fid=0x0:0xfba7b2899b4f414c"],"When":"2019-2-23"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Hiep Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMRHHZ7t798igHqhwEObqqiXXBYRe7_vTRRS3-gXG7fOgZlXSH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here tonight with some friends for an event so decided to have dinner here beforehand. It's my first time here, but my 3 friends have been here before. The atmosphere and energy in the place was fun and upbeat. When I told the cashier it's my first time,  please explain to me the level of spicy that comes with the chicken....he yelled "we got a first timer here!", and everyone in the back kitchen started shouting and cheering. That was different and created a fun atmosphere.  Let's get down to the chicken review 😋.  I ordered 2 piece with fries for $16.90, since I already had a drink in hand from somewhere else. I got it medium spicy. The chicken came with a slice of white bread underneath!? I was too carbed out to eat the bread. The seasoning and spice on the chicken was very tasty. It wasn't spicy at all, I liked the aroma. The fries were over fried, cause I don't taste the potato in it. Fortunately the seasoning made it easier to eat, so because of that I gave 5 stars for food since there's no 4.5 stars.  My friends all got the chicken sandwich or the waffle burger.....they loved it. Guess next time I will try a burger.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNR0vIuazIqKD1CR4YW4wDEWJcCBDsJelIUWijn&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"Kanwar SEKHON","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6CQMCc3TK9DOgcaVwnWRnMj24w6Pf6GP7z7TXjOEVhEyXN7Sx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Downlow Chicken Shack at UBC is a hidden gem! The food is absolutely immaculate—crispy, flavorful fries and a juicy, perfectly cooked chicken sandwich that hits all the right notes. The sauces were on point, adding just the right kick to the meal.

The only downside is the overpriced soda—$3.50 feels a bit steep—but other than that, everything else was spot on. The ambiance of the restaurant is fun and casual, making it a great spot for a quick bite. Highly recommend if you’re craving top-notch fried chicken near campus! Parking does become an issue while there’s just limited spots at front","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOh1_86RgN87YR6du_1Nn77FF8N5IgnKapjPj7Q&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-12-24"},{"Name":"Karen Mitchell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcKSF5TnT2tFwehIpLls1j_5b_VIihK99BbPy203xWx-oz-Aqc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was our first time and the service was exceptional.  We really enjoyed ourselves and felt welcomed off the jump.
The food was exploding with flavour and freshness, we ordered the mac n cheese, creamy and flavourful, the OG, OG hot, and the stinger and stinger hot… all of our sandos were well balanced spice and sweet, crunchy and juicy.  The crinkle cut fries were hot and crisp with soft potato inside, they were well dusted with truffle spice… I’d like to try plain fries too next time. We also tried the in house original drinks which complemented our eats perfectly.
Loved this elevated fast food, delicious. We’ll be back absolutely.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMf26xJfgETJH4lBjHqTLZIVii_ZzZRykCBzdMj&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Bradley Jones","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQSjOdt_NCThfrgQQSPCAI9c1m2q4Cia70lWTZMyAGLNwKu8R3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Chicken is all the rage.  We’ve done the wraps the smoothies the frozen yogurts it’s now the fried chicken.  Is it good yes is it pricey yes.  I actually have probably aged out here as I had to have one of my 16 year old’s order for me.  It seems to be the same chicken with different temperatures.  For those into the chicken crazy it’s a must as the chicken is moist and the battery is excellent.  So join the craze and go loco. Lemonade is a must.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0yUOD3jwNom_AFqWw3hkYZTDxPzF7kou6k6jA&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"AJ R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLo4tIvUrcwNXdNPm8MhPpZgzsQXb-_lGpW8MEceFXJ5buZ1dI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my favourite fried chicken joint in the city! I’ve been going to the commercial spot for years and it never disappoints, and I’m glad they opened a spot closer to where I live! Lemon pepper chicken was my favourite, but it’s not on the menu now so I switched to Jerk as my go to. I’d recommend trying any new/special flavours that come in because they’re always great. The chicken is so juicy and perfectly seasoned. Great sides as well!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuLHSwiIug5WM9aa9EYGCga2X_ilVbOoqBSqZw&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Flo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQ1akzv9WR_KmITyG3KFOeHflaL3qvQNBp7BgDlj35f6xKGqcT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I got chicken thighs and fries! Food was decent enough and it has large portions that I couldn’t even finish. Cashier was nice. One suggestion is to maybe have a sign or let customers know they can wait anywhere outside or inside for order. I didn’t know so was standing by tablet with orders and felt I was in the way and was accidentally bumped into. And I tried to ask where I should be for order and then they let me know after I asked. I wish I knew earlier, so I’d wouldn’t have been in the way. Also I think they thought I might be in rush to get order. But I was not in a rush at all. I just didn’t know protocol for where to wait at Downlow since it’s my first time. Cafes usually make you wait at the end of counter to get drinks with your names on it. So I assumed it’s the same. A sign letting customers know would make a difference in the whole experience for everyone. Just a suggestion! Thanks :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvfSmmgJwve3XFFkCmrkmLNL8pofRE9hZA2yQc&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Oba Onabanjo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXW_LaEsiqKs72-cl7kUfU4hZlVuhuF321Bgnqi7uTxAz-piEFt=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Having a good chicken place on campus is such a blessing. The atmostphere is great , the staff are  really nice and personable and the music is a vibe . If you are a UBC The student special is a great deal, with respectable portions, which is a rarity on campus.  Would definitely recommend stopping by , especially if you like spicy food","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8oDj7cvSDXAc2LBgQ1NlTNO72Rm12157sNc-P&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Michelle Siaril","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvNHVR_L-5eCK2usU0kQoT055SV9vB2qDNPyrA7CmG9QXO2IM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Finally tried this fried chicken on campus. I’ve heard mixed reviews from friends so been always hesitant to try. We all got the tender (extra hot and medium) and fries ($18.25/each) since we aren’t into dark meat. Honestly tasted average, pretty decent if a bit bland. Even the extra hot didn’t taste spicy but rather just peppery, whereas the medium had a more pronounced herby flavour. Batter was way too flakey and fell apart really easily, which led me to believe it was either too thin or not fried long enough. Sauces were pretty good in terms of variety though, the honey mustard and sweet&sour were pretty good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYfT4rTK4QjwO-zwmj9uQVqHI99ixDrq2hQ6Q&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-4-28"}]

[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It’s a convenient place if you are near IKB. I’ve found that the early morning staff is super sweet but the attitude of the afternoon staff is a toss-up. The convenience is the main draw. They have Upmeals entrees and UBC-issue bake goods. The Upmeals stuff is healthy and easy on the palate but interesting. In the past I’ve found that even some of the fresh baked goods somehow came out tasting stale, but this year’s iteration of UBC baking seems better. They’ve also instituted a Pearl Fever “pop-up” where you can get a limited selection bubble tea here (which is good, although I’ve only tried the jelly, which is harder to mess up than pearls) and also ice cream with taiyaki (the waffle is good, the soft serve is just okay - little icy - but it’s an accessible way to experience a fun dessert that’s a little hard to find).
My experience with the espresso drinks is - and I only drink decaf, so this may or may not be representative - it’s not awful, but it does taste a little over-roasted. Sometimes adding milk can mellow out bitter coffee but this one basically tastes the same in americano or latte form. The chai is not offensive but is made from a concentrate that’s very sweet and the London fog is also very sweet. Be careful because the hot drinks come out intensely hot. If you just need a coffee or tea, this will do the job, but definitely go somewhere else if you’re a coffee snob.
At peak studying hours, it’s crowded, but at off hours, the clean, quiet environment is very relaxing.
Good place for students/UBC-people if you want a break from heavy food or fast food, not the place I’d necessarily recommend to campus visitors.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCIoyH-0sdLvK7eGkdXRaADKQuUnvNnYAN71NY&fid=0x0:0x38c96d30bcb01b2f"],"When":"2023-8-29"},{"Name":"Oakley Nance","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwVuB38LSpIWv_yGP7nRej-Jw5m59HC-jukdf9PfQxIccZsQIsjA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was the only person in line, i ordered and had to clarify my friends drink order, the bubble was literally typing as I was ordering and the lady asked if the drink was iced or hot. I was like "One sec she's just clarifying through the text," and she audibly sighed and walked away. All throughout this order I said numerous times that I needed oat milk in the drink and she never verbally responded so I repeated "yes with oat milk" every time she went over the order and she rolled her eyes at me so I figured she heard and was annoyed I was repeating myself. As I see her make it she uses regular milk so I interjected and said " Oh shoot that was supposed to have oat milk," and she was upset with me and said she didn't hear me. I was just shocked by how rude she was.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Clara Sui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDpfMVOFlSfYJkiY3GBxSPXynTXF_RcCUHA_sqSaVyj6n4b46n=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Love the baked goods but would love to see the hot pasta entrees back! Also the soups! - I’ve noticed a huge drop in quality since 2019. Every order is mostly just spices, salt, water, and starch. There are very little toppings and the texture is incredibly runny, especially for the split pea and ham soup. Would never recommend them. Sandwiches and salads are okay but on the bland side.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jenny Tao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXl7qwNZdMK5UNeVm4Ss-BcTIDEv1k4P2sX-wHjGHKDHLJN9-0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Compared with the other cafes (not residence cafeterias) on campus, Ike's has a better selection of hot entrees and overall food. I love their pasta feature and now they have this huge chicken leg/breast for $8. Hot entrees always comes with side salads too. Not a huge fan of their drinks though. Service is speedy. My favorite cafe on campus :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lucy T.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKgUI8Y67OZjnaU2GTvCShItivsl_UV40o2V1eXoQZn3MU36Iw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Sometimes I would come by this cafe if I hadn't decided where to have a light lunch. I tried their beef wrap, mac& cheese, salads, and a few drinks. They're all at an average level. During summer season when there were few students, their soup seemed to be reheated for many times, not fresh at all. Once I wanted to get hot water from their dispenser, the staff member gave me an unfriendly look and behaved rudely. If you study in the IKB, and don't want to go far for food, it's a convenient spot. But do not have high expectation; it's just an ordinary cafe with standard campus food and it-depends-on-who-serves-you service quality.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nicole","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDjZJdREKI7_BD8K9KUQFoFVw5xhXpFyRgJEI-_J1YSIYrGDdt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Most of the staff here are friendly and I like the baked goods and salads. I've been picking up my morning coffee here as of late because the line usually moves quickly, but this morning I was charged $7.30 for a medium coffee. I went back to talk to a server (a different one from the one that charged me) and while they expressed concern by asking who had served me, the woman that served me didn't so much as apologize. I used to be a barista and I know that early morning shifts can throw you off sometimes, but I think that was quite rude. I wasn't offered a refund, but the other server told me that I can take some baked goods to even out the cost.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Z.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQPWk1igWiScMJLvbEfOGbn_E-SvYzWdnJ-_3R9XXD4Q9XGO0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Not gonna lie, a not-so-big, leftover, expires-in-a-day breakfast wrap and a small dessert for $10 doesn't sound very good. I wouldn't say anything special about taste either. I was too lazy to buy food elsewhere while I was at IKB, and so this was the best I got. I'll spare this review from the one star because I think I picked the wrong foods. After all, this is a coffee place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Meghan K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUfBN1bKKzFYujQ7qqMJ4sRqtV75B4nnaJOolJ96kg6M8dnXzkfdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The worst. Please go somewhere else. Coffee tastes like cardboard, REALLY overpriced mediocre food, chicken is all fat and gristle, pasta tastes like hard crunchy paper. Your money is worth way more than what they are charging you- yes it's convenient, but it's so bad. Staff are also RUDE.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Mehmud Iqbal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzdKzd7CEtSWik7PUDkAL2bm7hm1Q3Nn4JMf0vY7aaPod9GjZfWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Highly recommend this place for authentic Italian cuisine. The pasta was amazing and the servers were very cordial and our utmost attention to the customer needs. The ambience is amazing and suitable for every purposes whether that’s family or group of friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkd2evFh0o1-Gl_313Imi0RHeNvqA4YGu1M5EC&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Alex Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKIbHt8qTJa2xwClrVQAh4osofzP09STVVcRuaZPnZixApKqA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently dined at Milano Casa with a group of friends. Food was excellent as well as the service. My favourite dish here is Veal Chops. The manager wasn't not only friendly but also knowledgeable about wine. When we ask for recommendations, he guided us through the menu and suggesting wine pairing for our dishes. Overall, great service, great food. It's a place where you can unwind and enjoy delicious food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlLYVOTxipt4ZBeT91W7ivPgIqmehkuo82DGTh&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-2-16"},{"Name":"Ben M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLY7-DFsqx-InW5CnlXpJd6DWvP1u6nfShJnLWMiHPMX_9EZw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The bread is great - both the complimentary bread and the sandwich. The roasted chicken sandwich bread is crunchy outside and soft inside. The pappardelle taste very good.

We sent there for lunch on a weekday and there was only one waitress. She was friendly but was a bit slow, which is understandable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjYZ_ySR3AuaaNaLiBCvxh6fPxBHUUyWzZNIDY&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-6-14"},{"Name":"Fernán Oviedo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLMNyrTTiHR4Zfs_4KOSf072KTEBXxk2tD4rnh3ffoznWOycg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good food at its price point. We sat on some big chairs that were super comfortable. They were kind enough to split a plate of pasta in two for us to share.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCYtPCqEgECcqRWEUMECcyzfvU8llidqi7vFKs&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-6-22"},{"Name":"Ruohan Zhang (Morio)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLyrsA6Ajzj4MMiAAltl5rNoW7U9n4G_g-Ui2_Ju7FBqWwreA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would highly recommend this restaurant. It’s a quite random visit because I just pass by. And it surprises me by the cozy atmosphere and the amazing flavors of the dessert🥰","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjJKkn39MAjVfySo-JL1HVJihoQk-97B-eJBol&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Daniel Silver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJawI80c4qwvuA-pWmht_nhIypwFKNS8vUDHnZIepoqs0gJvft7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good food with enjoyable live music on the weekend at dinner. Love the complementary bread which was excellent. Portions are definitely on the larger side.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMlZ61Taxv7LWuGa0WjqPoVlS1JuMIqQwc2fVWN&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-5-13"},{"Name":"Tommy Byun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQhlW94B8T2fhww-HWh0iFh-RYIvFitfF4mjJX2E5t_heAv3Lb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking for a new place for a Christmas dinner with a big group (18), and Linda was very helpful in organizing a 3-course meal for the party.

The live music on a Saturday night was amazing, the servers were very friendly, and the owner Babito as well. The atmosphere was energetic, and the entire place is renovated substantially recently, so it was quite clean.

The shocking thing with this restaurant was that the portions for all their dishes were huge, and at least half of our members couldnt finish the main dish. This is difficult to find in any restaurant due to inflation. The only downside I felt was the taste of the food was average and the desert was too sweet, though it may differ between people.

Babito treated us a round of shot for everyone just for fun :) we took some good memories last night.

I gave Linda, the manager, a thank you email, and she got back to me with this😊

"We always try our best to make every guest happy. Because every day is a day to remember"

I was happy. Strongly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXfQZ4uw0Izw6Y_wvGRZOFEclqpgAAgcDENT4L&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2022-12-12"},{"Name":"Jamie You","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWETbFekq_Et68W-djuZjThdO4JZuMkSpHcfiSGZ5B7-99a9xk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If you like food that looks nothing like the pictures on google and are bland this is the place for you. The last main arrived 40 minutes after our first one arrived, we were a group of ~20. If you like waiting, this might also be a good choice of restaurant.","Images":null,"When":""}]

It’s 95% rice with a scattering of veggies on top","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcVudMpDOhY9B2y_C_sgViVrukWpF7qWiWrEWM&fid=0x0:0x5e70cd9bc564b542"],"When":"2022-11-23"},{"Name":"Winslow S.E.M.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2HCkP_vVp2Ah2D073WW_0Q4z9QlqqiZnhsuCp9Y3NbhCMfRg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Literally the worst Japanese food on campus, food does not match their price.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Athena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvcHYZ9C3U9WsCVWuvPpPPrR6DNL7Ywhr5D3WdUVxhk1FF9arkwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Usually udon is a safe choice but not here. It was the saltiest udon and the beef was even saltier. I didn't even drink the soup and it was this salty. Not worth the $13. Would not come back again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Z.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQPWk1igWiScMJLvbEfOGbn_E-SvYzWdnJ-_3R9XXD4Q9XGO0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Saw someone review "overpriced with really small portions": pretty much yeah. Got me through my afternoon but I was still hungry AF. The teriyaki beef has the texture of chewed-up beef jerky. The flavour overall is on the most generic end of the donburi awesomeness scale.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jakob Schmidt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgeN-BI2FD7doKOsV7ge4lNAIG3A31zObtODjG6FxxvBa-92Hb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The best part of the meal was the miso soup.

I got the chicken donburi once and the dynamite rolls when I went back. The chicken was pretty much like subway processed chicken breast; pre frozen tasteless protein block. The sauce flavours were what ketchup packets are to a good tomato soup.

The sushi is kind of congealed. You could say it tastes like “fridge”. Even the wasabi is bad. It’s fake fake wasabi.

The worst part is they charged me 10 bucks for it. To be honest I have a sushi place that’s probably a five minute walk from my house that charges 5 dollars for dynamite rolls. That’s half as much and fresh and absolutely delicious. I’m sorry but this place is a scam taking advantage of rushed students.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Max Hnatiuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBtN6HhvYUHvBHQU_xtNRl0s1V_J_Y2evW9fOX6UkEaHvn1REM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The Sushi is okay, but the rice is pretty low quality. The food is as expensive as eating at a restaurant but it's all served from a counter.  All the sushi is in togo boxes in a refrigerated area at the front; great for lunch on the go or in a rush. I personally did not enjoy the Ramen, I found it sweet and fairly small. I have yet to try the udon or poke but they appear to be popular options!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Very quick. Sushi and donburi are a bit expensive given the size. On occasion the rice in the sushi has been a little dry, but quality is usually okay. It seems you get a better value for your money with the udon.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Charlie YEUNG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGw5PX3p73-5KVe-phzoTYlIGXSlnqB4ERnoxBbKZsjrQC8qg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered half tendon half meat noodle and they gave us  2 pieces only. We also said less spicy but made it extremyly spicy. The bubble tea we order was brown sugar but they said there wasn't enough pearls and milk. So they gave us jelly instead or perals and we had to wait for a long time so they can buy milk. Their was barley and brown sugar syrup and just milk. It doesn't match the picture they posted. The lady that helped us has a bad attitude. We
Will never go back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJWaLddOdboelPqv6fJC5WXVeTQqmqIaRIdkRq&fid=0x0:0xe33771339bd2877f"],"When":"2023-4-23"},{"Name":"Jenny Hu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV6ab63Sz8wl7vCNCnb224YSdr8LS7oZYUO66THiemliu9kpOt8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The service was poor and the food is flavorless, price is very high as well. I ordered medium spicy and it taste like nothing. It looks very unappetizing nothing like the pictures they had online. 100% will not recommend to anybody. Very disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipME6RwNESu5C7Wh-qLS_NVY5osVlyH2NA5p3-16&fid=0x0:0xe33771339bd2877f"],"When":"2023-9-21"},{"Name":"Rafael Piczon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPdp_mJUCry4FPEse-GFV2xBMcqBsHiLtWEgCrd23xTymEwG5P=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food was okay. Ordered Beef and Tendon. There’s not enough meat and tendon, especially the meat. For $13.. I got one piece of meat and 2-3 tendon. Also the soup is not good/bland. There’s not really a brisket flavour to it or anything on it that would make a customer want to come back. Gave it a try but won’t be back and don’t recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Z.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQPWk1igWiScMJLvbEfOGbn_E-SvYzWdnJ-_3R9XXD4Q9XGO0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My experience at this restaurant wasn't satisfactory. I have to admit I put a lot of meat on my plate which is really heavy. I was just super disappointed that the employee didn't show me the price of the weighted food before cooking it. It is almost as if she wanted my decision to be final, even though I wanted to test how expensive was the food I got. She didn't even show me how much it weighed, so I was really frustrated. I probably could've put the ingredients back, since I didn't tamper with it at all.

My final pricing was $18 dollars or so, which isn't that bad if the quality of the food is good. Thing is, the food wasn't anything special. It was just spicy, and since everything is cooked frozen, there wasn't sufficient tenderness of the protein for my liking. I wouldn't want to eat here again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Delton Mira","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQ6siEE-8FxdXBJyypV5cT-D1vdMvtsbEpL1z3k--D4nHx1A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Bought something from here, paid by WeChat QR code and this middle aged lady said in my face REPEATEDLY that she’s ANNOYED TO DEATH because I paid via QR code. She said there’s something with their WeChat QR code receiver account AFTER I paid. But mind you that the payment went through successfully, yet she kept on saying how  “annoyed to death” she is super loudly and acted as if I didn’t pay.  She also asked her coworker to call the account holder to “check if they actually received the money”. Did she grow up without anyone teaching her proper manners or sth?

Message to that rude lady: 您没事儿吧？有病就去看别和我发癫行吗？Is your life really THAT sad? If you don’t want people scanning the QR code, how about DONT STICK IT ON THE MOST OBVIOUS AREA OF YOUR COUNTER or tell me if you DONT ACCEPT WECHAT PAY when I EXPLICITLY ASKED?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jason York","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2KL5JJiTZL1QVt_3AcqILQXXBIuqDWdYOdj3lYENvavlAma6S8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I ordered the B7 (Beef brisket & tendon).  The 2 pieces of beef brisket was tasty, but I've had more tender brisket elsewhere.  There were 2 massive pieces of tendon, unfortunately they were so chewy and hard that they were not edible.  The broth and noodles were very tasty.  If you order "mild" for spice level, expect it to feel like medium or even spicier for some people.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"lingg store","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLp8rYTvB8kwKj3EYBANj9yEssMXkKCmV_NIitip5UT6SXGBw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I ordered take out and when I opened the box at home, I can't find my spam, eggs and keep in there. They are stealing from your selection and this is a second time it happened to me. Thought it was a mistake last time, but now it's probably done on purpose. Never going again.

~~~Added later: Called them and they said they made a mistake during the busy lunch time, and offered me a free next meal if I'm going again someday.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tita P.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWekrIeEGVPa_ohvKbjJLrgrdPmpV3xbGliGkij1mFpHELvTokv1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my regular places to eat around UBC. I always order dried hotpot with rice (no.2) NEVER DISAPPOINTED. /every of my friends also like it/ The owners are friendly too  :)","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"An okay place to get a healthy and filling meal in this part of campus. Generally fresh ingredients, tasty bowls, and options for customization whether you go with one of the set bowls or build your own. Prices are fair for the portion size. Depending on who you get, service can be cheerful and reasonably quick or extremely sluggish. I've never had any serious problem with the food quality here, but some ingredients seem to not be as fresh or as high-quality as I've come to expect from poke (again, never had anything that was bad, but it's just missing that pristine touch). I also find that some of the flavour combinations are kind of odd, like the pesto-marinated tofu and pineapple or very guac-like avocado scoops. But I still generally find their bowls satisfying if you know how to pick your ingredients. The Main and the Cali are my favourite standard bowls. Although I like the personalization of just building a bowl, I wish you could get more than 3 toppings on a regular size. Service is iffy sometimes. Mostly nice people, but there are a few staff members that don’t seem to know what’s going on.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvNc8KhypRHAPOkrXn7ZvHo4XlMGwiMt5snuGO&fid=0x0:0xe8a0dead744320d8"],"When":"2022-3-27"},{"Name":"Max C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJv1TrjuIfxkeVrA_UPRCLq7NLIMbGYJSP-J-XbBeeEof06=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Just go to Steve’s. The quality is better at Steve’s and you get way more food. At Steve’s you get unlimited toppings but here you can only pick like 2 or 3 lol and they don’t tell you til after. The portion size is really small for the price. Just go to Steve’s. Not trying to be mean but like we are just uni students with limited funds.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sartaj Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1doLfhIpPIdYO53EoD_63mHYE3jrQc1kxM-CAvFcju93a6Z1xPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Have been waiting to visit this location for a while given its proximity and centrality on the UBC campus. I can’t say I was blown away but the food was sufficient. For the price I found it to a bit expensive but it’s possibly justifiable given that some of the ingredients such as tuna and salmon are generally more costly. Ordered The Main- item number one on the menu. Found it to be fine but the flavors were a bit strong on salt and umami. Overall, an average meal, though I will be returning to try the Açaí Bowl as that looked very interesting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjTvWJYB202PdXm_tJXu0Ky8bMTrRGstqjOsfb&fid=0x0:0xe8a0dead744320d8"],"When":"2021-2-28"},{"Name":"Fei B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCSPR4b-Aju_3xzgvNmgK79_SKNPWkqhiQHmMJksqE4GdZMXE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"2.5/5. The most mid poke I’ve ever had. The rice was pretty mushy, the fish didn’t taste right (I got spicy salmon and it didn’t actually taste like spicy mayo, it tasted…old?) and half my bowl was just pickled onions 😭
Service was fast, but the workers pretty much ignored me the entire time to keep up their animated conversation with each other instead. Don’t know why they were so disinterested in their customers…
anyway, only positive thing from this is that I didn’t pay full price for this bowl as it was the poke of the day.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Peter Davoust","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8DQNmU5U_e3Dga2hIsCodeIxxbhc4znCnX9gQ3E4kOGBe9jgX=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I eat here once a week. The poké is at the top end of what I would expect for fast-food poké. Delicious.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Milada Dzevitski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3KWypqQwKmMzwQlWsGazFRoM8rxmdETpWLeZSF1ojX57LELvw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best Poké on campus! Thank you!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexandra B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLf03Ev9sQmRzGrxl2Z2uYiGPDBSNsqtN4vU4Yc9VPN4a7dcA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They have a nice variety of different topping options to choose from. [{"Name":"Jiali_Scarlette Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAHenBjAeq0irWOkY2TcNco9ePZF6jrgubaqERKfHj3Cc5xQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"As other comments mentioned, they do mess up your order! The receipt indicated one of them was steak while what I received were both chicken. It didn’t taste anything like chipotle at all. The rice was not fresh either. They probably should rename their brand.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLJRbA4QFeF9Wht_42t33BD_rdYFnzDx2keRTS&fid=0x0:0x1862819c31467f8e"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"Gursewak Sandhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-lLjb-vHYgiWFoe4YzOBadS3guzh-uBd_Pju5v0jpVeyUPA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

I recently visited Freshii, and I couldn’t be more impressed! From the moment I walked in, I was greeted with a warm and welcoming atmosphere. The staff was incredibly friendly and knowledgeable about the menu, helping me choose the perfect meal.

The food was fresh, delicious, and healthy. I had the Buddha Satay bowl, and it was packed with flavor and nutrients. The ingredients were clearly high-quality and well-prepared. The variety on the menu is fantastic, offering something for everyone, including great options for vegetarians.

Overall, my experience at Freshii was outstanding. I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a healthy and tasty meal.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"H Serena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5g7xxXdAtEv-0Rp2jfszEYRekXVvYoQrpgJxQt_yCfVXEm2eM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered two teriyaki twist bowls. The rice was lukewarm and hard, the chicken had a sour taste, the broccoli and peas were bland and flavourless, the wontons were soggy, and the carrots were stuck together for some reason. I have never had such disgusting and stale food especially from a store that advertises fresh, nutritious, food. I tried to save it by adding some of my own condiments and sauces but I still had to throw away over 2/3rds of both bowls away. Waste of money. Even instant ramen is better. The service and atmosphere might make up for the trash they serve but I had the order delivered through Uber eats. Will never come back and will urge everyone in general to avoid this place like the plague. Would give it 0 stars if possible just based on food.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eric Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKY5_RlHBgmGgPDkl7cbMFpMjsTQJ9idjqlCbfzQiGVL1QpxA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered a cheese chicken quesadilla, but when it arrived, it had no cheese, and the chicken was cold. When I asked if they could remake it with cheese, I was told I would need to pay for another one. This was very disappointing, especially since the restaurant was empty, and a quesadilla only has three ingredients. I expected better service and attention to detail.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"kyla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKSvfatDoMlhFWqjbppyne302wCj7G1MLOAgut74F0sLrCJqw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Disgusting. First, they messed up my order. I bought one of their "Build your own wraps" and what I got was a bowl. I thought that maybe I shouldn't be too harsh and just try out the bowl because bowls are just as good for me. However, the ingredients tasted terribly old and smelled so bad. Especially the cheese that is super strong. I nearly gagged every time I took a bite and had to throw away half the bowl because I prioritize my health. Absolutely disgusting and a waste of money.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Abha Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIz-fxx-9FhjJeZBVOjAjYALrXo8vJBbKx-sHZerG5aR3UGRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst experience ever. Bought Chipotle bowl today. Total waste of money. Moreover washrooms are always out of service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jenny bansal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLUzm8HnXLH9DdGi3Y-m7oG_MSc8XPJrXJFxJpCzKt7K8NA4r0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great variety for both vegetarians and non-vegetarians. Got different kinds of dressings and drink such as smoothies(fresh made) and they do group orders as well with nice pricing.  Exponential customer service with knowledge staff. The best thing is you can customize everything.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdbmYHghD6Xc9hQQuLwfy2uupl48MhFwXICAj_&fid=0x0:0x1862819c31467f8e"],"When":"2019-9-13"},{"Name":"Matthew White","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXH70HYcALba1bSRnrQiYmwMbwFYFgO3S4UaNHREWYiaOwa9yE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"****DO NOT ORDER FROM THIS STORE, YOUR ORDER WILL GET MESSED UP AND THEY WONT REFUND YOU****

TLDR: before the long version: they forgot the $9.10 double chicken protein I added to my teriyaki bowl and even though that’s not the “entire” order (the bowl itself was $12.69 so the chicken made up like 42% of the order price who’s counting though!) it’s still totally a messed up order. They also lied about trying to context me about switching the grains in the bowl (quinoa for brown rice) and outright refused to give me a refund or help me in any way. Worse customer service experience of my life.

**Now the long version**

I wanted to order a teriyaki bowl after a long day at work. I saw the picture on DoorDash and it had chicken and I like teriyaki chicken so I ordered. It arrived, turns out the chicken is an add-on so my bowl had to chicken.

I said ok fine I don’t really have lunch plans for tomorrow at work so I’ll order again and select the double chicken protein option and I’ll use the spare second serving of chicken on the first bowl. The second order arrived, and there was no chicken. I checked the receipt this time and I had selected double chicken and was charged for it. They forgot it. I called their store and they claimed in their system it said there was no protein. Not only do I not believe them but they refused to give a refund and offered me zero remedy.

Moreover, to add insult to injury, the second bowl that arrived had quinoa instead of brown rice. This isn’t that big of a deal but what is in which they left a note claiming to have tried to “contact me” about the shortage of brown rice. I received no calls from their store at any point, my only contact was the aforementioned call I made TO them. There was also nothing from my dasher or the DoorDash app saying they tried to call me. So they are just flat out lying and taking my money.

Even if I were to believe them, again the DoorDash receipt clearly showed I added the double protein option for like an additional $9 dollars and I brought this up to them but they claimed the system showed the second order had the same price as the original order. So if they are telling the truth (I don’t believe they are!) THEN STILL THEIR SYSTEM IS BROKEN AND WILL SCREW UP YOUR ORDER AND THEY WONT DO ANYTHING ABOUT IT. Either they are liars or they have a broken mobile ordering system. Either way they screwed up my order by forgetting the one thing I needed to not make the entire order useless (again not a small little thing, it was a $9.10 add on, $3 less than the cost of the rest of the bowl which was $12.59).

If you managed to reach the end of this I am sorry it is so long but I wanted to accurately give every detail because this has been the worst ever experience I’ve had with mobile food delivery. Stay away from this store.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQvEBNSLn4v_ueWd9F7SE5QkTO2paXgdk4XnBb&fid=0x0:0x1862819c31467f8e"],"When":"2023-3-22"}]

Everyone is kind. Any mistakes made are honest are they are all learning. But the food is REAL and freshly cooked. The prices are very, very good. And the marginal 'profit' all goes towards benefiting students and addressing food scarcity. If it's even remotely near me, this is my go to campus cafe. Just double check the hours as these volunteers gotta go to class too, so hours can be limited.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Polly Tsao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHjs6JuXkTNSpcG8ZdpNO8nji0dnfwnfgMFiUQ3MFOilMZkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I used to be a volunteer 10 years ago! Great to see Agora Cafe still operates by an amazing team of volunteers. Love the food here - especially the granola bars \u003c3","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joti Tronson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLofHR3UL4QtQ_l7BUZVQPiwRHtrS7TbNIC4wVv2qBoljC_5w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Incredibly pleasantly surprised!!\nWe never had such a Cafe at the good old HR Macmillan Building at the turn of the century, when I was there.   I an looking forward to Thursday.  Much Love to me Agsci peeps.  💙🍄🍒🍅🍜🍯🍝💙","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_Rd83W_mG4tCSHwLVekfeOHmun3MwMZqA0BDUETRlky_WsaThjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best kept secrets on campus. Their vegan pumpkin coconut loaf is my new favourite snack when they make it(they change their baked goods everyday, and it's only a dollar). Also, it's only a dollar for tea, coffee, or hot chocolate if you have your own cup.","Images":null,"When":""}]

The lamb shank was tender and came with a ton of delicious sides. we also really enjoyed the seafood skillet. The atmosphere was so lovely here and I will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiJHdLuTbprlD8c6BxSDXT1aGnAK05UBhTekN0&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-12-12"},{"Name":"Hessam Dehqani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9_xTs6k7X3RgR-GYtpDaVcRhHZYvAkCWBCnak0FYwr9rofA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was a symphony of delight and pleasure dancing on my taste buds. Extravagant amounts of seafood in the seafood fettuccine. Sauce was perfect. The Chocolate Lava Cake was the perfect amount of fluffiness and chewy-ness all at once. The cake was the slightest bit warm and the giant scoop of ice cream served on the side was not too cold, making it the perfect combo. The friendly staff will make you feel at home.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJ5stowouGaXpUeYE6xdnYk5tTw2UAhlZkDP0B&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Sarah H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW92qwsfx_pIiwt2DlNeJL21vsXcUQcWFFO0CrTDqGo7aSuEtvR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We loved this Greek spot in Kits! We chose to share a range of appetizers- all were delicious, including the four olives with focaccia, the mezzo trio with the best pita, calamari, and spanakopita. We also had the yam fries- so perfectly hot and crispy. Everything came out quite quickly and fresh. The service was friendly and delicious. Definitely recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOboR7reOpDZb_p0TsC_cSRvUDH0o3Bk4IppOyh&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Lister Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWbNvO55wOzkDRxCcJ-fMoCcdWyut5hlx-H_zUreRnwso9_V0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed lunch special with beet argula salad, lamb souvlaki, and ice cream. Everything made carefully and plated beautifully. Yummy salad and tender flavourful lamb. Would recommend for both friendly outings and special occasions. Great food, personal service, clean ambiance. Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO--eXeeKqPcjAD_zKFBygtnPBJ296t7XWlMGx&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"andy a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ7Y7rwHyjfulEA1YHdfgv-xt7-eGezTRedst5phEBEmPsbXg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful experience, tried the four olives with the deep fried olives. If you enjoy olives I highly recommend them, you won't be disappointed.

The lamb shoulder was fork tender, and the Navajo bread was crispy fluffy and soft all at once.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPL8yvDzQrWpheoXTb2m_LsnPGF3AcaCpmykrT&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Yourstruly T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdAW_3mT95dnmWSH1jV5DzTjAp8VnRyKu5igqgCkvt_l-2XR77=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of dining at this delightful Mediterranean gem, and the experience was nothing short of extraordinary. The ambiance exuded jazzy vibes, creating a perfect backdrop for a cozy and homely atmosphere.

The moment I stepped in, the inviting warmth enveloped me, making it feel like I was enjoying a meal in the comfort of someone elses' home. The restaurant's decor and lighting contributed to the overall cozy vibes, setting the stage for a memorable dining experience.

The main course portions were generously sized. Each bite was a burst of deliciousness. Appies were so flavourful. For the dine-out menu, I really liked the Mushroom Arancini and the Garlic Prawns. Ugh!! So warm/flavourful..

A special shoutout to the owner or manager, Amar, whose friendly and attentive demeanor added a personal touch to the entire evening. His passion for the cuisine and commitment to customer satisfaction were evident in every aspect of the dining experience.

The potatoes, a standout side dish, were a delightful surprise with their sourly delicious taste. I couldn't get enough of them. The chicken skewers were another highlight – juicy, flavorful, and a true testament to the culinary expertise of the kitchen.

In conclusion, this Mediterranean restaurant is a must-visit for anyone seeking a jazzy, cozy, and homey dining experience. With mouthwatering dishes and a warm welcome from Amar, it's a culinary haven that I can't wait to revisit during patio season as well!!

xoxo,
@yourstrulyfoodie","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8hxYl3J7Guv437YZS_Uj8FCdYhvd9RqmOTMS1&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-1-16"},{"Name":"Daniel Silver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJawI80c4qwvuA-pWmht_nhIypwFKNS8vUDHnZIepoqs0gJvft7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I enjoyed everything we ordered. Portions were decent but not overly so. Definitely worth trying if you like Mediterranean food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODYFoK7X1vlNRzms1wWtQdlB7xQK729D7csvia&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-1-3"}]
