[{"Name":"H H (Anonymous)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0CCOw3xZUC4Jf140dg5ctXIilfoV-e5nt-AjupQqNUDd2WrdF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"UPDATE: I noticed that 2 new comments with five stars were written right after I put a review out. One says that it’s written from a UBC student but we were the only ones in the restaurant. Really??
—-
I came here with my friend for the first time because of the high reviews, but I was very underwhelmed by the quality of food.

We ordered 1 Carbonara pasta with 4 beef balls and a Creamy Pesto Sauce as well. The lady taking our order was extremely rude, holding her arms together most of the time (not even a proper eye contact too).

The portion of the pasta we got was smaller than expected, and the pasta sauce was very bland. I was also expecting actual beef meat balls for the protein, but it felt like eating processed, microwaved meatballs.

I can’t believe all of this including the mango lassi costs $56. We even tipped which made it $64 but we both felt that the food was not worth the price.

The only good thing was the mango lassi. It tasted good, but not worth the price considering it’s around $6 for a regular cup.

Overall, I’m extremely disappointed about my experience here. I noticed your team sends auto-generated responses for customer feedbacks, but honestly it really doesn’t reflect well on your new customers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObiPeftIl5M13d-Zi5CL5dxWo1asSNBVO640QA&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Priya Seenivasan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJMhKuaV0UByu_19lq9S8Z0RymGWLGeMkZW32FqcwJdXwdJC4O6=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was very tasty and the portion sizes were very generous for the price. The server gave us FREE Mango lasi and it was the GREATEST Mango lasi I've ever had. The food was hot and fresh and would 10/10 recommend if you are hungry. There are a lot of options for both vegetarian and non vegetarian and we had both of them and it was super good. They also play very good music for you to enjoy while you are eating. All and all the entire time was very nice and the owner and workers were very hospitable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZaBRVpHaOh3_rK63YSkIbFpjWPmoknQX1xSOn&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"Crew Member","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIW14Rkre9qUFJcBu_goFVES8rqZEo_nhoqcvS5y7IN5FVczw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my second time here and as good as it was the first, it is just as good now. The owner greeted me the first time and remembered me after over a week. I had the butter chicken poutine the first time on takeout and this visit I took my partner to share with her my love of this place. We had the butter chicken poutine and the peri-peri rice bowl. Will come again to try the various other poutines on the menu. I also wouldn’t hesitate ordering Indian food from their menu as well if the butter chicken is any indication of the taste and kwality. And yes that’s Kwality spelled with a K because it was that special!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFnFhaMwSrlDtTe_QXzwAmwsSniPSZ1JtJ3WuF&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"Karen Castelino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7hhw7USB5QEJWbaxhDcx84xG1_szAmojdVvw-2W8v9vRmg6g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a lovely spot for a quick lunch. The owner Sanjeet is very welcoming and happy to explain about the mixed menu items with passion.

He LOVES street food and he has a mix 9f Indian, German, Italian and Mexican street food which is pretty cool in one place.

Today I tried the Ghar ka Chai which was just like how we make it at home and they asked if I wanted sugar in or out😁 Definitely like af home. They serve it with two biscuits to dip in the Chai, just like at home.

He charmed me into trying his butter chicken samosas and I said, Why not?! They came out piping hot, with a green coriander chutney and an imli chutney - perfect zingy accompiments to the tasty samosas and quite large sized they were too.

He also gave me little tastes of his new spring rolls that had a chicken filling and a vegetarian filling. A nice little amuse bouche.

Today anyone who's come in so far has also got a little shot glass of mango Lassi- and it really hits the spot on a hot day.

A nice addition to West 10th, I'll be back again and might bring a friend or two with me!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFHT9vS7Xj7xZWcpTHB855Vl5ncFMvQXMmLcUq&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"Yvonne Chuang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqpGy6jnb7nEEZ8_2ji_kDkPiEtwUfRn1WZ4LYfiAMdNRgZihb=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a wonderful experience at this restaurant! The portion sizes were generous and offered great value for the price. The food was absolutely delicious, packed with authentic flavors. The owner was incredibly friendly and attentive, which added a warm, welcoming touch to our visit. To top it all off, my kids were delighted when the owner surprised them with free ice cream after the meal. We left with full stomachs and smiles all around – highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Valerie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsTdxaXYpowkoRFDEpRVok8X0NZLQqRjReyfUxLgMaFFBwHbFY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was delicious! I ordered the mango lassi and the 65 chicken rice bowl. Everything was freshly made, and the workers are really nice!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMP_KmSZB_VaqJZXpIu6pOs6SS1hZxRljgWuX2r&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Tommy Byun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQhlW94B8T2fhww-HWh0iFh-RYIvFitfF4mjJX2E5t_heAv3Lb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Casual Indian-Italian fusion restaurant on the way to UBC. It is relatively new, and it felt like it is targeting more of take outs and dine ins, as I was the only person dining in during a weekday lunch time. It may be different for a weekend dinner.

I ordered popcorn chicken poutine, peri-peri burger, and a coke. You prepay, and they bring out the food. I was talking to the owner a bit, and he was nice enough to let me try their mango lassi, which was pretty good.

Popcorn chicken poutine was really good considering the price (menu says $9.99, but the staff told me that it was increased to $10.99 when I ordered, which was kind of weird, as food delivery app has it even lower, at $8.99). It had good portion of the cheese curds & popcorn chicken. I would order the gravy on the side next time because the dish was salty overall. I would order this again for sure on Skip the Dish if its $8.99!

The Peri-peri burger was not good. It was dry, the bun was cheap, and vegetable was minimal. I would never order this again, unless the burger improves, as I commented this to the owner when he asked how the food was.

Next time I come, I would try other interesting menus like fusion pasta & wraps as well. I will provide further review with another visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeG9fj15NenmiUzLSavO5taxKqF3HlEJWBf5wS&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-5-13"},{"Name":"Monesha Basker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJdHrdFjVHsxCfq5iniLbrtk_RySGMC8r7uyasrbD_xG-PMw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was delicious! It was very appetising. The service was also very nice, very welcoming. Would recommend !!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQXn-Kt9TKt75SNVgXLgZn6SXC0MiR73v_Cy3l&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-9-29"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Standard selection for UBC cafés. They have some pre-made sandwiches and wraps (which can be heated), salads, and baked goods, and usually some sort of soup. Also a full coffee bar. The food is mostly decent as far as grab-and-go stuff goes, sometimes the wraps are kind of soggy. The coffee is the same price as you’ll pay at any of the independent shops on campus but not quite as good, but definitely acceptable. The staff is usually nice. Basically impossible to find a seat inside around lunch time since people in the Buchanan just treat the café area like any other study spot and camp there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDdLJPzUn7n24eMJB87t5qtL3U-BSyWyk6XbMK\u0026fid=0x0:0x4584be10efa073b2"],"When":"2022-7-2"},{"Name":"Navdeep Kundi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLR37nz--ycJy074sdUBv3DZUyxW4jzWvoXQP2HkN2_OCdDWA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good cafe in ubc with ample seating space .  food is good include some vegan options too","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Will Messcu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ0HMR67KoEZTEUofCAlE7qBksri5vMDUXCzBZdKkJUPkIUKw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I got ignored by the cashier while she chatted with her coworkers then recieved the worst breakfast wrap I've ever eaten, cold straight through and very small.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexandra Gil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGHVoZ6S-gccTuFX7t9yx29wH4TozOwS4lSatKljgktDTQENM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food is overpriced (just like any establishment in UBC), the quality doesn't justify the cost, small portions, nothing too special about it since you can find the same baked good in literally every cafe run by UBC. I have been served cold food there. I've been served cold food from there and that's the lease of my complaints regarding the place. The problems are not unique to this cafe, its a standard set across every UBC establishment.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eleanor Hawkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItAOkchaJ4fzYoHBipQXki6SVib53In7HwmfCCCtVg8XWMJQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food is good, but they reuse the same milk and re steam it for lattes. The London fog was undrinkable. Milk can only sit for 40 seconds before it should be dumped, and it should never be resteamed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bill Zhang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwbDKu19kVa0ubt7UJxezndgCB9k4mXuDX2262XNQEkLnwqt89=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good paninis at this place, I always ask for extra toasted cause it makes it really nice and crunchy. Ok price too so good place to get a quick bite before your next class.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Isobel Dawson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUusWJxAoDuIDLD2Rend5oOxhk_7NCFJvrYsxitwY3VG_9nDp5ylg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"pretty decent, nothing too exciting. one worker keeps berating her coworkers over things she doesn’t want to do, sad to see as she gets mad at them for no reason.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amy G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUyB9_jQgQDNOeSjqO6Hb6noFRRtRls_6tm8ZhkHxw7wcptajgO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"More expensive than Starbucks :/ lemon loaf tastes like a lot of vegetable shortening went into it. 8$ for a sandwich is too much...","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bought a 20oz cold brew this afternoon for under $5, takeout.
The donuts looked pretty fancy, and I’ll have to come back for one next time.
Service was good, quick, no problems.

They have bar seating downstairs with enough room to work on a laptop. Upstairs seating and more isolated into individual pairs or quads of seats, some very dark (almost pitch black like coders’ cubicles). Could be alright to work in, if you needed, but most of the table heights aren’t particularly suited to laptop work.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNI4qmEtB4N21oAzMs9tywfzjWAbycBO8paChkg&fid=0x0:0xf0b2db8921115ce5"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"S. Em","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvU9E4vn1Q9Po0cgEsgrGFBEAIwH-1YuABimdecViWHQsIkbflqg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"JJ bean is great for students needing a coffee and affordable snack.  But they really need to learn to up their pars on the most popular items. It's a campus with  construction crew everywhere and I often find they are out of the best muffins for example. Any other cafe would make more and set it up for times they are busy (lunch hour/4:00) but not this place. Often sold out of the best buy 11:15. Please consider this and upping your pars- esp on the jalapeno cheddar muffin!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rohini Mettu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFejkZ-30wz8Qnk6MZsgaXoKAmWI61rSnOugKhzDrxDe076MC43A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Im not local to Vancouver, but this coffeeshop feels like home away from home (Seattle)!! Wonderful atmosphere, I love the upstairs seating area for coffee chats and study time. They have a great selection of pastries as well - as a scone fan I would recommend trying the cheddar and chive scone 10/10. I got a London fog and my friend got a latte here - the coffee bean itself is not my favorite but I loved the tea!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNUYTZB1LOgf332fOOJr259GPFIis9sTbcIoDG&fid=0x0:0xf0b2db8921115ce5"],"When":"2023-8-21"},{"Name":"Bay Color","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJI1k4Sgd0aWDCqtosK7do8Vp3VfqEkz0STA2XewyBkbsa6hw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I ordered one butter croissant and a medium cup of  cappuccinom. The taste is not bad，but the staff provided a smaller croissant than one that showed in the display cabinet. Because I hurried up to go other place, I forgot to take a picture.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"JJ Bean has a nice selection of food ranging from snacks to full meals, and always delivers on flavour. Delicious jumbo muffins. They have a full range of espresso drinks and their coffee/espresso is nice and smooth. They also do a dreamy London fog. The one drink I wouldn't recommend is the matcha latte - the quality isn't super consistent. Usually it's passable with only a bit of clumping but I've also gotten just frothed almond milk with green clumps floating around. You can get a better matcha latte at any UBC coffee shop and the other drinks here are all worth your money so I would skip the matcha.
Staff is always nice and smiley. The cafe is very clean and there’s two levels with lots of seating inside and out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsyO6sCRzWquS6GzgViOyhgOixxNiSPBtapTmn&fid=0x0:0xf0b2db8921115ce5"],"When":"2020-10-15"},{"Name":"Komal _","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVe79YhMUnOs_CFq3VFFDZdsazH62kTyKFLVqsc0aMpMFY3ysgM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food and service is good; I'd come for that often. But, the seating, however, is very uncomfortable. Upstairs: all chairs, sofas and other sitting surfaces are hard and very right angled at the back -- which is not particularly comfortable to sit and work from. None of the tables are at a good height respective of the seat. The shop should throw in some cushions on the seats to make the space actually cozy and comfortable.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexandra Rousseau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCc1VRoWPX9lI6oLLlSyZp1wtcpy95ye2Jq395pgPsfvG22Z41=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"JJ Bean serves the BEST chocolate chunk cookies you can find in Vancouver. They’re actually magical - most of the time, they’re so fresh that the chocolate is still melty!

The vibes in the cafe are cozy, and I love finding a comfy study space on the second floor. I’m also a big fan of the gender neutral washrooms: it’s a welcoming space for everyone :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFjlPNj2axjHSTKksdL9AqkhEsCZXg_I5LH-ga&fid=0x0:0xf0b2db8921115ce5"],"When":"2023-3-15"},{"Name":"Michelle Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrZc4FOCz7AcGuorZE4SGdMyBNzLpAyMERBSqnXndHoxWZ5T_e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"JJ bean has a lot of stores around BC.  Itusually has a long line with people buying coffee and baked gooods.

What did I get?
⭐️Cold brew
⭐️Chocolate zucchini muffin
⭐️Chocolate croissant

Everything is very fresh. The muffin is gigantic (swipe to see). It’s even larger than my hand!! And it tastes absolutely delicious. The zucchini crunch adds texture and blends really well with the chocolate ( you don’t taste the zucchini). No wonder it’s one of the poplar muffins in the shop.
Chocolate croissant is very fresh and crunchy. It has a decent chocolate filling that we adore.
Cold brew is decent. I like the flavour. I’m down to try other coffee there. I also love that I can use reusable cup there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIsurmTJeHjqxBofZQgY141lMiAS23FkE4SsPk&fid=0x0:0xf0b2db8921115ce5"],"When":"2021-12-28"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Hassan Parsa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqI-yi5_g6jVvS56xjNyNhK2CpMhS24UMuxol4BdmDgUj7SkeS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I just went in on a random check for Indian food. I liked their food, the ambience and the service! The chef make an excellent job with the Naan! The lamb curry was also good. The only thing was the price of the Naan which was around $6 which I presume is a little too expensive for a Naan. I should admit it was garlic Naan and tasted really well! My overall say on that one experience is I liked it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHqQw9DT5wHsAfTuT9js_Bhcqb--Dvuz9hRL-4&fid=0x0:0x607c8163c4f26789"],"When":"2024-7-10"},{"Name":"Rox Ortega","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkUL9-cUrc1IAVugY6nVrUBRia3eXMBadJsQlS4avQYHladfx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The oiliest "chicken" tikka masala. I'm not even sure that meat is chicken. It has the texture of pork but kinda tastes like fish. Literally the curry is drowning in oil. I couldn't even eat it, it's disgusting. I'm so pissed off that I spent $30+ on this thing I can't even eat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyesUrRyMqQioSlPDycrqtiC30M2U3vho9p85A&fid=0x0:0x607c8163c4f26789"],"When":"2024-7-6"},{"Name":"Peter Cross","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHmBXMXmX9-43PxxMc-vQWx8OaX3r8ByLsfhp1pyyCEQpdxmTkCA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came tonight to celebrate a birthday. Group of six afforded us plenty to choose from with a variety of dishes for the table.  Service was great.  The room is nice with pleasant music.  The lamb is a bit tough as others have said. The rest of the meal was wonderful and we had a great time.  The dumplings were very tasty and the chicken tandoori was a bit bony and had little meat on the piece I got.  Sadly the waitress was very slow to clear our table after food and drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO6TcXMa-VONcmC7arUP3EfLZ8vrqf0_4wHOqOj&fid=0x0:0x607c8163c4f26789"],"When":"2023-5-21"},{"Name":"Johncy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNCcOOb16x--mvyjqmOGS_ekMiT8INhLzftV30QGSCPlNpdwog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good food and really good customer service; if you like spicy food, I would recommend you to tell them to make it spicy. I got channa masala and fish pokora, and it was really good. Also ordered for takeout for my friends and I got chicken & lamb biryani. My friends both liked the two biryani. Overall, I would rate this place a 4.5 out of 5.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvC2Q6n4xLACw457mAdsLrzye_N3KU3CkLTCfL&fid=0x0:0x607c8163c4f26789"],"When":"2024-3-19"},{"Name":"Aradhana Kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLGF8FufGWhI_LiUSm1UrLVnUnsBxHi0EfHfM_Ofg_MXDH00w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"When I first looked at the restaurant online, I thought that people wrote fake reviews about it, but I was wrong!
The food was amazing and traditional, it reminded me of my mom’s food.
This is the perfect restaurant if you’re looking for vegetarian options.
The staff is really friendly and caring when it comes to the service.
We had the chance to personally thank the chefs and take a picture with them!
They allowed me and my group to play songs of our choice and also let us dance after dinner which was fabulous!

I’d definitely come back again and I highly recommend it to people that love Indian and spicy food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2exvTf2NYpDGKTU3HbA6Fwt4hpAqJJOSyV22r&fid=0x0:0x607c8163c4f26789"],"When":"2023-7-15"},{"Name":"Sandra R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXi4xFFLZJN-zPiYf-Lw1A86uAbB0_czMuoffJLUFjjC4hQyww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place! Really great food, excellent value (huge take out servings), friendly service  and the atmosphere is cozy and warm in winter, open patio in summer. I love their gluten free offerings. One of our new favorites.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Holly Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL8JUvONVzomd94Off1-k_EXXhwoErw-2ELquSGN4FCIVH78w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ok... So lunch special is really a great price. <$15 for a complete combo. But, I didnt expect the portion to be that huge too.... It comes with 3 large pieces of naan. 😳
All of their menu that we ordered were extremely tasty and large-portioned. Three of us ordered 3 main items (Paneer Muttar, Bombay butter chicken lunch special and bombay wrap lunch special.) We couldn't even touch the wrap and we were still too full. I really wanted to try their desserts too, I'm kinda sad by this..😭
Great service. I would definitely come back to this. Would've loved to try buddha bowl too, but they were out of Avocado at that time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM27jZ9359i688UVYwPYVaHaCvCX-HNldpOpkpN&fid=0x0:0x607c8163c4f26789"],"When":"2022-3-30"},{"Name":"Daniel Silver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJawI80c4qwvuA-pWmht_nhIypwFKNS8vUDHnZIepoqs0gJvft7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyable Indian food if you're in the area. I appreciated the complimentary pappadam. They did a great job keeping the chicken moist in all our dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOec3R-wNLnUiI9yqV5PXbv4iU0Zv3zhvU70W37&fid=0x0:0x607c8163c4f26789"],"When":"2023-6-18"}]

[{"Name":"Yuanyuan Sui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLdUsII4WFykeYN8c39YhOD2C62_mZT6JQkdSrmnjzLZbsmJQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Every time I crave pizza, I always come here. The flavor is truly authentic because it’s baked in a real wood-fired oven. I believe the owner is a true pizza master. The other dishes are also incredibly delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMBRCuLguYXwPuDSHXYhdEfkET3OOM6nax7JqvL&fid=0x0:0x8e43cf5ba00b905e"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Ogulsheker Mammetgurbanova","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUe8GjaVTOl25hIpybW_uoLoO5ctTzcTdvyPEsg_Rc9eSJBHYd4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have eaten at this restaurant a few times and never had an issue until this year when their service and food quality really started getting bad.

I stopped by to get their creme caramel as it my go to at this restaurant, and to my surprise this is what I was served. Literally a plate of falling apart creme caramel and melting whipped cream. I have never seen anything worse than this.

The server was nice but I could see he was embarrassed. I'm not returning. Very disappointing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsOG1J5fhUgiOfGCwTVBHDLUR9X2M5EaPZrY3I&fid=0x0:0x8e43cf5ba00b905e"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Ghazal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUxPjakfUDfUlOphLX0NHrhY3j03bOfl1WB2qtK88VIEBoxSUc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice restaurant close to the beaches. We went for dinner about an hour before closing that it was quiet there.
The XL pizza is huge. It’s more than enough for two and you’ll be leaving with some leftovers.
The wine was good and the staff were nice.
Highly recommend the tiramisu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXucaGD_baqqZFuYfigDkVZL6M9AWt7NQzyH_L&fid=0x0:0x8e43cf5ba00b905e"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Amrinder K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKLMegKP69PmtwoPrtEd4-b0W2EN7BJl-5jao1JpatSzXqBPw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I wish I could give then 10 stars. The owner is very humble and kind .He know his job. He is a master chef. Must recommended if you are really looking for Italian food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOKDnxWoZnq8lg02X9fXWsxOBzqsSMB-fMjJL4q&fid=0x0:0x8e43cf5ba00b905e"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Alex Goey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgFYIQSym3lbrdcS7b1l0penbnuhiG6UJB--4lz7BR5wDuTrQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good service with good mood dinner.
The food has a very authentic Italian taste to it, and is overall very delicious","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyBMySuzVu0LPQXt5U79hv65ZzyOVN6upIbIOL&fid=0x0:0x8e43cf5ba00b905e"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Soo Ha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVa5w876ALIhElnLibu444mefnqSKkA2_AATN_vn40Y_jL19Vd0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely great food, great mood and great service. My daughter and I enjoyed a lot this lovely restaurant. We could have fantastic bonding time here. The owner was the nicest ever. I appreciate!! 🍕🍝","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMfBS2qcQEsiRjVUkfnMNnUip2e6c0DjfGu2YSl&fid=0x0:0x8e43cf5ba00b905e"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Colton White","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIgBF1v0pkrQkYoxHrxhLg09C1sy94cH8CGRv9cpAKg9Ob2MqM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our party of 4 came later in the evening and we were treated to a TOP NOTCH experience by the owner, Jimmy!!

Phenomenal. Huge portions, delicious food, and great value for Vancouver.

We tried the pasta dishes, their FREE appetizer bread, and we tasted their grapa (wine liquor) after our meal. Everything was fantastic.

Would absolutely recommend this place to anyone. Thanks for the great evening Jimmy!! 🙌🙌💯","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjcJ7LAZ5NiYy94Vzxml7zS7DbQZ22OTDzQf_j&fid=0x0:0x8e43cf5ba00b905e"],"When":"2023-3-20"},{"Name":"Ghaffar Salin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKlFMX8_wqaDRoOOTjjqrjIUczBOFhBiKmpBpeJPAzH3PAmqD-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Friends and I came here to celebrate a birthday party and man was the food AMAZING!

The pizza I highly recommend and the carbonara!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPP61ljSKUlmizLQiApWlWPYomiBWkyr9mDXO1_&fid=0x0:0x8e43cf5ba00b905e"],"When":"2024-10-15"}]

[{"Name":"Frida Michelle Samayoa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpmjtzFIjtvgDqyl4m5Pe8a7wjyq4pLwPJLdF6aF8Nivi5UpfDvg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I found myself in the UBC area and I just had to try out this new sandwich spot. I got the number 18 turkey sandwich as the server recommend it as one of their best sellers. This sandwich was sweet and spicy and I added hickory sticks to add some crunch to it. Turkey portion was great and the bread was slightly toasted which I liked. The price is definitely worth for what you get. I 100% recommend trying this place out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAwxYP75msUg3rmcnE5ZcUY5fCT1uMB0scL_ow&fid=0x0:0x86d6a5ca0fb459c9"],"When":"2024-7-11"},{"Name":"Miruna Alexandru","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHgzfQaNL4yr8HlTAW1t9pWpdcn82wgV2ycFYDE5A3efdp72Zz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is coming from client for life, so I hope someone reads this so I can adjust my review. Big Star are all excellent quality sandwiches, especially #33. Love the Langley location. This one could be just as incredible if the staff was trained to make a good, consistent sandwiches. Ordered 5 times over the last 2 weeks. First - incredible. Second and third - still very good, lack of love in assembly but the taste was there. Fourth - missing ingredients but still fairly good. Fifth - old tomatoes, no hickory sticks, mostly sauce, barely wanted to eat it. Please help them help you guys 🙏🥹","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Layla M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIULAGPd3LMFEyahySCqnfE9p9ldeKJvVtVaY3V4dMOe9Rkig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tried the roast beef sandwich (#14) for about $26, including a bottled drink and tip. It was okay, but they could offer more sauce and side options. The atmosphere wasn’t great, so I ate in my car, though the staff was friendly. Decent, but a bit pricey for what you get.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jaden Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUM2ggNMzvyF3-mbTCuUBp5sV15NjtcwDNnBrTCqRD4nn9vAlRl=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"<TRYING EVERYTHING AT UBC JOURNAL>

Been craving a sandwich but was wayy too lazy to hit up Subway on campus (😭)so I decided to give this spot a try. I must say it is quite pricy for the portion, but undeniably tasty. I got the number 27 with roast beef and crispy onions and it tasted great with the sauces that came with it. Not the most affordable, but I would come back once in a while and would recommend 👍
7.8/10","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"malkiat singh kahlon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPsGNUSCVAR1pHzoOXxS8NIubuuVm9PJhtJlmDjVlWAgelPhWQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"some of the best sandwiches we have ever tasted, must try very filling fresh and delicious. will definitely be going again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tracy C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWluVwmrPrFYLmbv807xEzXg--D3PL4qpZJ_7H1w3ugNl4vWuiGWw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place SLAPS!! Thankfully I'm not within walking distance because I'm pretty sure I'd need to eat here everyday.. and then would be broke 🙃 Absolutely delicious, and I have no doubt that everything on the menu is just as delicious as this Number 27!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPiuuZV1Uk0pBvhMF6V74dvkewigzcjjbXBSdhx&fid=0x0:0x86d6a5ca0fb459c9"],"When":"2023-11-17"},{"Name":"Chris Charles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrISq9W73HrjlGADtJWok_5lo7jNqrkaquC2lVl_FVv-ialwI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good local place for some creative yummy sandwiches.   Bit pricey but good quality ingredients and creative sandwich options.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5X5g8wziZEiW9RAr2x1E2UnvJadfiwlH2v855&fid=0x0:0x86d6a5ca0fb459c9"],"When":"2023-11-21"},{"Name":"William Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKlu5zowUzI-uuMKdp-caVGL82oFTV-KzIjrIOdJjDzEMZxtw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The portion size was very disappointing for the price. [{"Name":"Lisa Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2hRhOWIQf2ren7p1R3F9BVnb3q6vzlyk-JCc_U7cm7KJ7rH11fg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"i came to this restaurant starving after my afternoon classes. the service was pretty quick, we got our order around 10 mins of ordering. however the beef noodle was very disappointing, the beef tasted stiff and flavourless, the soup just tasted like soy sauce. The vegetables seemed undercooked. The texture of the noodles was fine. Overall, 3/10, was expecting better for the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOerFh-ScT0Avl732B3GQc_JRRKBuTvCqZjOmnU&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Henry Hu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOiklZbH_t_aRkBtZKTm3pDAeGGVqs_fJp0WPZNs_8inyrTWQy9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here with my aunt and her two young kids (we are Chinese).  Having seen poor reviews, we weren't expecting much, but the dinner was surprisingly very good!

The service was slow at the beginning even though there were few people there -- even after 10 minutes or so we still hadn't been served water or tea.  It was a cold night and the restaurant was also chilly.  The server was very friendly and spoke both Chinese and English.

The appetizers were fairly good (spicy beef tendon and beef slices).  I had the beef rolls (very good) and spicy beef noodles (very good).  The dumplings were ok.  The scallion pancakes were not very good.

At the end, it was close to closing time and she gave us some free mango shaved ice which tasted amazing!  Very fluffy with a subtle sweetness.  We will return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnk7CIbwaPs_5-VtCw29sqwvLTOj_7hFEQDruC&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"Katie Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIjMysay4-FQVEPUnU2iivCs6D7x1kzSWlLVk1hwpWr3ttr5es=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went at a time when there were almost no others at the restaurant. Pretty quiet meal aside from a few shouts by the staff (to each other?), which I think were instructions. Atmosphere was fine, normal restaurant vibes. Decent decor. Nice ceiling lights.

Service was fine, although I can see why some might see it as curt. She came by and refilled my tea without being asked, which is more than I can say for many asian restaurants nearby.

I ordered A3, and found the portions quite reasonable. The noodles are expensive but I think it's partially "ubc campus tax". They did put quite a bit of beef so I don't feel like the prices are all that unreasonable given the serving size and the location.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOCR7J2-cBxj_MhFTA2O0HRjFvAoVseKHkoYN8&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2023-10-23"},{"Name":"Sartaj Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1doLfhIpPIdYO53EoD_63mHYE3jrQc1kxM-CAvFcju93a6Z1xPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Got takeaway, the brisket was really good! Really simple but satisfying meal- was slightly pricy though (menu with prices posted in the photos). Service was fine but I can see how some people may comprehend it as a bit too curt.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOm_WNO5NXyIgHBbu7z5LTIAqt8lrxTtLO88Ta3&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2021-2-10"},{"Name":"Sunny Hsieh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKn7JfczJPilvGMT4s7fYXLEV9lFRbn9veIkFCwiRyDnuZfxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We order classic Taiwanese dishes here. The food taste average, but the dining environment is quite noisy since the stuffs talk so loud and don’t care what customers think.
If you’re looking for quiet dining, I suggest you order to take out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXHF2vu1lLnJY4nrIl9jXR3Nco4mSagrnqGZF6&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2021-7-25"},{"Name":"Ryan Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJg51dkTiELfwGSC3YeGg0Cqc2FbwTcp56uR5oMbjvMxs9-kgt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Came here with high hopes after being a happy customer of their West Van location that closed down, but was extremely disappointed with the terrible service and mediocre food.
Upon arriving, the restaurant was silent except for the yelling coming from the kitchen. The lady who brought us to our table didn't say a word to us, and left immediately after pointing to our table. The way she spoke, in both Chinese and English, seemed like she was upset that we were eating there and we were doing her an inconvenience.
Despite being only one out of two tables there, it took around 15 minutes for our order to be taken. Again, the lady sounded annoyed.
The soup was disappointingly bland - I had to add lots of chili oil and soy to make the broth taste of something at all. The noodles were overcooked and mushy, and the beef shank was tough and overly salty.
It's such a shame to see what Chef Hung has become, as it was once my favourite restaurant in Vancouver.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"nataku04","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_SbO1MAS8FGX9Q1u4rgyMAxUXyAbqpEXgjPOqBTAPYYTV2-Ed=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I have no experience of the restuarant itself since I go it delivered. I'd say its not that great, apologies for the semi eaten meal before taking photos. I was just starving, first meal of the day after a 20hour fast. The noodles are a decent texture yet being so thin. The tiny beef brisket chunks were tender enough but so salty. The broth would have been good its light but tasted watered down.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5ilPwOOcgkxQZCf75Ib1kTLwfreuMBYb5gUC2&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2022-8-30"},{"Name":"Eric","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiQoGWet_oXsOFHl9IApfn5oX44S-A0_Tz_vgzgQxRW9yw_IDK=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrendous experience. I've always despised this place for its terrible service, inconsistent quality, and mandatory tipping on takeout.
But today crossed the line—raw chicken. To make matters worse, the server literally shoved the chicken into the box with her hands because it didn’t fit.
Absolutely unacceptable.
I'd rather starve / eat Neptune than eat here.","Images":null,"When":""}]

The worst experiences we have never met.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMYtSdqJj03V3B94ILPOk5SfskXY5XzW29Nq33\u0026fid=0x0:0x4f0ca7813ea9fd69"],"When":"2023-6-4"},{"Name":"Sophia To","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfemfoLMDopq79u8NOfhH5E0jeaAtKfixSXUfKCXkmzZFxRoTV=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super friendly service. I think they are under new management. Had the bibimbap, a fried chicken combo, and cheese balls. Bibimbap is a staple, and was good. The cheese balls are wrapped in mochi and deep fried. Just a hint of sweetness and very satisfying. The chicken is less crunchy than some other places, which I appreciate (sometimes the crunchy stuff ends up taking a layer of skin off the roof of my mouth), and it did not feel greasy. The ordering system is a bit glitchy, but it didn't affect us because we went when it wasn't busy, so they were able to clarify what we wanted.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Forrester","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKclUfheJ5Bxu-Y63dr7FmLPgRgWHLqFZJYBG3AoUFZJiW0tA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We went in for family dinner.  The restaurant is under new management since the beginning of September.   Tteokbokki and corn cheese were a match made in heaven.  Regular chicken was delicious and crispy, and yangnyeom chicken was just right for us. (not too spicy)  Each table were equipped with ordering tablet which were self explanatory.  Definitely will visit again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Maggie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdRAltSXABaU9WZtDiDFGAwgNoF-T5Zl3pbuS7IiXA5Fsl5bFw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Only leaving 5 stars beacuse 10 stars isn't an option. Found this place by accident and so happy we did. The staff was very friendly and personable. The food was absolutely delicious and huge portions, a lot bigger than we expected. We were pleasantly surprised when several side dished were served with our meals. Prices are fair considering how much food you get. Everything on the menu looked amazing and we are so excited to go back and try more!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPRJ_Squw7YgeJoXdgOp-5lGtNC1QcYeieuJw0\u0026fid=0x0:0x4f0ca7813ea9fd69"],"When":"2023-8-30"}]

I'd like to try the Mac and cheese next time I go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMn6uYKQ5t4T6IGLJ25lRXeUHAo393hZ2YcA8dH&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2024-2-19"},{"Name":"Rhys G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKhDN_RhBJBaKomIPKrjzczztaQgfWjWmKvGOPFus9xAhXjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dined in and got served by Jan, so kind + welcoming + accommodating to my preferences! I ordered the lamb special and cherry cheesecake for dessert — 10/10 need to go again!! Definitely give this place a try when you’re in the area, this location specifically","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Blue Angel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7f51VtKBeHUyxFkPNC56JU91zCBjw1D7P5VQUMNOkHX1HFd_n=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Managed to locate a place nearby for dinner. Was quite a nice rusty restaurant with some special priced meals and drinks. Ordered the stew beef and lager beer for dinner. Beef was really great with rich flavour beef chunk. Hope to come again next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM57iEqsxZjXMgh47M_yP-vqPJrVMC7AbcfxNdv&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2023-9-5"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cute comfort food eatery. Very warm atmosphere, from the design of the inside to the friendly service. Because the place is relatively small, it’s probably not a good idea to bring a large group, but it’s a nice place for a smaller hang or even to chill by yourself. I have been curious for a while and just tried it with some friends. I probably will be back.
They have a great drink menu with lots of specialty cocktails and nonalcoholic drinks. I got a nonalcoholic pineapple guava soda. I don’t like drinks that are too sweet and this was good for me, but some people might find it weak compared to commercial fruit sodas.
I got a soup and sandwich combo as my entree with the Eggplant Caprese sandwich and the Crab Bisque. I really liked this take on a caprese sandwich, and the baguette was very fresh and soft. The bisque was very good too. Rather than being a super creamy bisque, this was more tomato-based and a little tangy. Good flavour with a fair amount of crab meat. I also liked the little side of coleslaw that was included in the combo.
Wasn’t really planning on getting dessert but then I saw they had a Chocolate Banana Bread Pudding, and I will rarely pass up on bread pudding. It was delicious but, as you might expect from bread pudding made of banana bread, with ice cream, with caramel sauce, VERY rich and heavy, and I had to get some help to finish it. I think this would be ideal for splitting between two people.
For this meal, with tip, I paid $48, which surprised me. I thought it was a good meal, but not $50 good - I’d associate that kind of price with a more upscale experience than this. I can understand the soup and sandwich pricing, the dessert was a little expensive, but what really strikes me as obviously overpriced would be the $8 soda. I understand it’s made in house, but it was just a fruity soda - no fruit bits or anything fancy, and no alcohol. It was a nice refreshing drink, but for $8 I wouldn’t say it was worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMA-33yhxlhuJWzrEmE3NBivENZ-qwhvFcoFjxN&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2023-5-20"},{"Name":"Keith Ver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVdqxLCf1LEt0AU82myo-eUqDcb2LcbdnfhupJTEW0sPAQ-qQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good food and good service! Loved the ambiance of the whole place. It gives me this vibe that you know you'll be ordering comfort food. Not only will it fill your tummy, but also your soul.

I ordered beef bourguignon and it reminded me of Filipino dish called Caldereta 🧡 - minus the mashed potatoes that is.

The whole place is accessible as they're located along Main street. Will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOT835yv9VmYFeqt5AwiAEPtu_4O-xMZON9EBlg&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2023-6-5"}]

[{"Name":"Mehmud Iqbal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzdKzd7CEtSWik7PUDkAL2bm7hm1Q3Nn4JMf0vY7aaPod9GjZfWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Browns never disappoints me and that belief continues to be strong after visiting this branch. The food tasted so good and their drinks menu are diverse. Helpful and pleasant service from the staffs all around which made the overall experience even better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-7I3aoI0pd-VwBTyDY9CSXnQbXwlt3w3MsrJC&fid=0x0:0x184dff507d14466e"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Elizabeth","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGQCC-3Yq5r5JFAxvF-sP_n-pSXPylbpJz_b9Z54D_klrEhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I ordered the tofu dragon bowl as takeout. The tofu had no sauce, no seasoning, and was completely dry. The rest of the bowl was mediocre at best. I've had good experiences at this location in person but this was really unappetizing and disappointing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbRvzrKUDTlb38Dj0j0nkT3Tj7VQqAV7cEFG7r&fid=0x0:0x184dff507d14466e"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Al May","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURsEKydI6yFDWfeEuJUm_zojUlbRJUnS2y7j3NZKmrARii_3iYLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I have been to another Brown's location last year. It was my first time at a Brown's Social House too. I was unimpressed by the food at that location. It was bland, so I wasn't expecting much here. I thought I'd get just some drinks and appies to pass the time.
I was pleasantly surprised. The food here was actually pretty tasty. The crispy cauliflower came hot, fresh and flavourful. The fish and chips were tasty too, and the fish tasted fresh. The Smokehouse BBQ Burger was massive and juicy. The yam fries were perfect. The calamari was ok.
We loved the food.
Service was friendly. I wish it was a bit more attentive, though in fairness, it was a busy Friday night.

I'll definitely go to this location again if I'm ever in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhjo4mOyjivdC-bwwDWaPsJVx7rRhwHuICm3wO&fid=0x0:0x184dff507d14466e"],"When":"2023-3-12"},{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A solid Brown's with the classic menu selection. The menu options are bit limited, and the space inside is a bit squished, but the food is pretty good! The cocktails are quite nice too, and the atmosphere is what you would expect out of a bar-restaurant. I highly recommend their pastas :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkRhxX67sOh4p3XXoU-SbVEBbk0QOkVZoJWA43&fid=0x0:0x184dff507d14466e"],"When":"2023-8-15"},{"Name":"Turtlekeeper Designs","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZmq2g731Yc8XnFSpBiniWaYnYNraL7GVOPNZyVCF5ChC8dro=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Impromptu dinner on a Thursday night. Took a while to be addressed as I stood in the door but after that it was ok. As expected bar pub ambiance. Service was straightforward. Food was actually nice and tasty. We ordered the veggie burger with yam fries (got lots of very fresh fries and they were so good) and the French Dip which was also good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbWZ7XD5i2236andTn7FbTaXTeva5_d-GElI_x&fid=0x0:0x184dff507d14466e"],"When":"2023-12-23"},{"Name":"A J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-fdMJBlly5BeXgZ67G8CHBNUziz56_MjRIlsaT8foeYrzHg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Service was excellent. Server was very kind. I wish I got her name. She had long brown curly hair and bangs. Delicious burger delicious nachos. I personally wasn't crazy about their selection and desserts so we went across the street to the bakery.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Karisa Bili","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-OVGPRqmVuQZW7xmX14s7bPwWHM2AbBJsLIiBZvQDv2TapMf8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We visited from out of town and were pleasantly surprised by this restaurant! Our server Nozomi was a gem: super sweet and always making sure we had what we needed. The nachos and fries were delicious!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nol Preen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKFsp06N458CPMCub5e1pFgaAgOfCsQxwk7g9CTgPVBeBZT1A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best service experience ever by Maddie tonight!
Super engaging
Super nice
Proactive on a complimentary dessert for my daughter as she saw her opening a gift bag!
If I could give her 6 stars of 5 I would!  Tipped her well too but you can tell she loves her job and not in it for tips!
Best server I ever had!
Oct 8th.
Thanks!","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Bill Lin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkSfWcd4_oHhnDwMXqX4CTdW7hRbaD60nvDPyUf1IyjHqvONpMzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Totally beyond my expectations, as all the university courses I've ever played are all so so.

A friend told me that as there's used to be a lot of rich people studied in UBC, hence the golf course had to be good enough to meet their bars.

Anyway, I enjoyed playing golf here A LOT, though not that much design to wow you, but the condition and landscape itself both are so amazing.

Particularly there's a "British Columbia Golf House Museum" at Hole 8, would love to spend sometime visiting it next time","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7tO5j6nNTZrTfJhTLEglHOZvtBD4IAow7olnA&fid=0x0:0x8c5ea9da7ae025f4"],"When":"2024-10-17"},{"Name":"irwin keshane","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLgC45fLJaFx8h484dEHDL3kofb7tTknt9zOOky1Eru_HjUYcy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Staff where so nice especially Bob had great time here and will be going back soon","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCQTWStLc931SzayhTd2XTuvwCJC7hmbN5NpT9&fid=0x0:0x8c5ea9da7ae025f4"],"When":"2024-10-30"},{"Name":"Rory Mcilroy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7x4CtfjVOJJlS296GoxsGCVZGMQV-tHy4a8hFcZn0YhB5Ky8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my home course and I also take golf lessons here with my mid coach Justin min , highly recommend him! This course have a lot of narrow fairways and some interesting holes. But this course is not my favourite. The 3 hole green is the toughest green in the world","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEBX3wZXHR5JOnNjhdW0BqPR6XqQmiJBpkzO9G&fid=0x0:0x8c5ea9da7ae025f4"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"Stephen Mac","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUoPC8lYoGwhrnfIc_f4se0z42VgmocbQORloZc6SPdkmVh6n0z=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We hosted our Christmas party here and the venue and staff were incredible. I also golf here often which is decent too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmujpaKbTI-VIGzls7FQ9PQm6TFC6437V5ErnT&fid=0x0:0x8c5ea9da7ae025f4"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Momo Kanev","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVYQ6DS2Gsv87TwjvsSMBEyjDcXlMYsAUFKgiFEIjH2jzjw7Em05A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"University Golf Club is an exceptional course. The fairways and greens are meticulously maintained, and the challenging layout will keep any golfer engaged. The staff is friendly and attentive, and the clubhouse offers delicious food. I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a top-notch golfing experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPg_2NznaTWR-KAYXg2f6KcUXazl41JJCQpN9ww&fid=0x0:0x8c5ea9da7ae025f4"],"When":"2023-4-4"},{"Name":"Martin S.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLuLW-A27WPwXI-_vFAiPKraBbHdcqW_zjf6q3yanvxdJcIjg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Played a great round here with some buddies. Rain came out but wasn't too bad so we played through.

My friends and I are fairly beginner, so this course was perfect for us, pretty open and easy greens. Did notice that the grass on the greens was actually a little long, cause we had almost zero break on pretty much every hole.

Great fun though and it's not stupidly expensive either.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHj3Lucm20HgkWx2zyDF00ycO4-gt5ctAwXAHD&fid=0x0:0x8c5ea9da7ae025f4"],"When":"2023-8-15"},{"Name":"WILLIAM REN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKRmqUVmhhErGGqKi-Bzn0et1-EnBX9lgvZO2NQ0f1pzZpZEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The University Golf Course has been around since 1929. This golf course is accessible to all levels of players and can be walked or driven at your leisure. Here you have no stress for worrying about loosing your balls, because no ditches, no ponds, no for the balls over. This is  a very traditional west coast golf experience with majestic, towering old growth trees and long narrow fairways that anyone can play, then this is it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2-k2_Z6Dl9rCo3Lc7-XuPFJaWWhOxIKtbNpNU&fid=0x0:0x8c5ea9da7ae025f4"],"When":"2022-9-12"},{"Name":"MIGUEL MARTINEZ CEJA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUztjwBaMsNtjBzVBFRcaUJ7t1cbUF1T1cS_N4MiFB5Ow65fUsX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everyone is welcome!
Golf classes for children  are fantastic.
You should bring your children from 3 - 99 years old if they want to try the sport.
Covid restrictions are gone, weather is nice most of the time, but a little bit of rain doesn't stop no one when you are having fun right.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGDWwAMvbT3JNUIGE3Ij-4iFEqfJFEoXOU0bqI&fid=0x0:0x8c5ea9da7ae025f4"],"When":"2022-4-16"}]

Great fish quality and nicely priced. Recommend salmon oshi!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNygfLGON0vLuTaTZmMnQuQ4U5NGIS2DxoPMU03\u0026fid=0x0:0x65487d900dd3e33a"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"brian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXurkC3J29Gx5T4WsGD59In4p_GamNc3jY-d2IGyJkBFHtJe9Gr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"had an excellent experience! the food was fresh and served promptly. open later than any other sushi house in the area. nice!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1v28HtItVCReiUTywVDFcKoSaS72qHxzD8_Mk\u0026fid=0x0:0x65487d900dd3e33a"],"When":"2024-3-17"},{"Name":"Alex Gosselin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9siCaYLlsVATR39GgP5c_1JUni8uTLMNUQCPgOFgC8qbw538h=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Eating at Sushi Inn was a very nice experience. The patio was cool and we'll shaded, which was very welcome after a long walk on a hot sunny day. I had the yam and vegetable sushi combos; miso soup and gomae included. The food was delicious and the server was  sweet and kind.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPahr_EiYlUODmZoumNlyjG65yNpyWdCjQ9rRBs\u0026fid=0x0:0x65487d900dd3e33a"],"When":"2021-5-12"},{"Name":"Gimgi Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCUiyfCYcwOc7rqjgh4Uu2x4-lkajxQ9eEs8JpA5MEMYuimDY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's alright ~sad about the assorted tempura, it only comes with 2 pieces of prawn tempura. We'd have asked before we ordered.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6RWE4f1M0St1EsrhAt2mtj_SOEgJAWHIXK_vv\u0026fid=0x0:0x65487d900dd3e33a"],"When":"2024-1-29"},{"Name":"Maryam BG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYOocnrrI0wz1xy1UzzrfX002uyW86PfiNNhxdXyfBusTbUhlS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Exception food with friendly and fast costumer service!\n\nI ordered the beef curry meal set, and I was very happy with the taste, textures, and quality of food! I will definitely be coming back 🍲😊","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyVdNx0NDO4YvoDnUs3Ym1QXgJ2vbzaXKPPt6E\u0026fid=0x0:0x65487d900dd3e33a"],"When":"2022-10-29"},{"Name":"Glau K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIX2-9VK2_IAqzFQmLS0Pm18s0rAyIGmgBS9g-wTlvV9YSR4Ta0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The staff are friendly. The service was fast. The place looks really nice. I ordered the dynamite roll and Yam tempura roll. I love this two rolls. But today both tasted like plain. The tempura part could be a little bit bigger. Because the shrimp and yam was really small pieces inside. The last piece of my dynamite roll didn't have the shrimp inside and just veggies. And a big piece of lettuce. It was good to try this place anyway.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPaz8EtdxUxd_mwiINSyJGarCO8DXYxnUOyPyz1\u0026fid=0x0:0x65487d900dd3e33a"],"When":"2022-3-1"},{"Name":"Amir Hassanpour","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXIEEr8UJ4VznvZzRZ2-Utty00-tH2O6MV3noFbmj3AVWSYmGk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The restaurant is very clean and there are hand sanitizers at every table! I ordered the vegetable combo and it tasted quite good! The service was a bit slow but it was mainly because there were too many online orders (which I guess is a sign that the place is popular?)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMa4IN46ZUOONiUzTc9N8Pqd_uHVUjgGZP-wfTc\u0026fid=0x0:0x65487d900dd3e33a"],"When":"2022-2-21"},{"Name":"Kalahne Serpanchy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFGEDSbxuRXcDV4BiTngAhOvvEpzmvZq7HRiLNLWnKNG1vmF0uRA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Server was lovely. One of the few places in Vancouver actually open after 10pm. Food was mid, and I was disappointed because of the comparatively high prices. Rice and seaweed were stale, rolls were chewy and flavourless, tea was bitter. I wish there were more places to eat out at night, and this is still a good spot if you find yourself stuck on the west side after dark, but it'd be a last resort for me.","Images":null,"When":""}]

The water tasted a bit weird. Maybe because they didn’t properly wash the cup. Everything else is standard and nothing stands out. I went with a friend and ordered the spicy sushi combo which included "17 pieces of spicy scallop roll, spicy dynamite roll, and spicy tuna roll." The restaurant was cozy with all booth seating, and on one side of the wall, there were shelves for storing belongings. The table we were seated at had the shelves.

The server was nice and offered free green tea, as well as kept our cups refilled throughout our meal. At the end, my total came out to be a bit more than $1 for each piece of sushi. The combo was filling, but the quality was not as good as I would have liked. I thought the sashimi was going to be marinated in a spicy sauce, or that the other ingredients inside the rolls were going to be spicy, but the only element that made it spicy was the sauce they drizzled on top at the very end. I think the taste was decent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORmQBgldaGZfOJoaGKRxtN39xTzvR7bDGoHovm&fid=0x0:0x5c1dc52e12dcd539"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super big portion size and delicious food!! I ordered their Yakisoba (with chicken) and i despite being STARVING, I ended up being super full! I will say the Yakisoba could be even shared between 2 or 3 people!

I am often very picky with the chicken as I liked it to be very well seasoned and it did not disappoint. It’s soft and not overly seasoned but pretty good.
I will say if you’re looking for an affordable tasty and worthy meal, definitely come here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMumqdUBkcBBW1VgSlayNjcOIqz61sSH-HfpPdj&fid=0x0:0x5c1dc52e12dcd539"],"When":"2024-2-6"},{"Name":"Марина Остапчук","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgPEOFf5kc5CtS14aUnBP2XPfjMJh4ZrLbNFbmJYu-1hc6IasS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Got my order and I really have to ask you a question! user_reviews:
[{"Name":"R C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0eD31csNo04JzXmFiGxOw6om-U7XoOcrwih3LN1YIW10DJFxa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is a hidden gem!
Food was amazing , I like the deep fried skewer and the watermelon punch the most.

The watermelon punch was made from fresh watermelon !!

Service was great , they were friendly.

We went there for dinner on a weekday around 7:30pm , only half of the restaurant was full. So no line up and no need reservations at all. Easy to find street parking","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPklUsHCdij4gU0akyUMmTtv_rCFXEJKA4jlctv&fid=0x0:0xcc621ac7fc194781"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"minnie li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRoQOlIxvrw__7xun_s22_XplGfNg8u2NALefXOOF5MWkjHg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This Japanese restaurant has a cozy and small atmosphere, which is reflected in the small tables. The food is quite good, though the portions are on the smaller side. The prices seem reasonable for what you get. However, the worst part of the experience was the condition of the menu. It looked old, dirty, and felt sticky to the touch.  I think the restaurant would benefit from updating or replacing their menus to improve the overall dining experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkX8P-RyR4bH7ya-92MrUIShNkdiH3BdtG-j1l&fid=0x0:0xcc621ac7fc194781"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Alvin Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWe7GNAcDD_olIxPvjJNxL1Hm7Qi7x4Wh-Txa7EiT1fdDm_8c2Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fun little Izakaya style experience that focuses alot of the fried things on a stick experience, though having said that; there is a wild variety of things that are not fried on the menu as well.  Tables are spaced well, but cramped on the surface front, which creates a particular  contrast, while the decor is best described as modernized tradition.   Food was a highlight, as there was a good mix of expected crowd pleasures and known modernized classics.

All in all a fun place to go, drink and eat, but falls a little short of being that exceptional place you'll rave constantly about? Though I will say for what it is, it's priced well with sticks at 2-4 bucks and larger items at 12-20, so the value is here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbY3F_VqnnH8rdHc44_Nqjp3lCBQh5Q5N6Tj6h&fid=0x0:0xcc621ac7fc194781"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"AP M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIaKGpK1qxDPJR9sUK3SPV8F5w7Y9wdWWnd2roa6x4OwjMUrg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fairly small venue with touch of japanese festive decorations.

As for food i had 3 kushi (wagyu menchi, lotus root, and pork) and surprised how filling it was; couldn't finish eating the rest of kushis i'd ordered ...
Yellowtail sashimi was SO good.
I have yet to try more food to better recommend, but as for dessert, try hojicha pudding!

Pineapple punch is a must try!

PS:
JP, what a great server. He had great smile and service from the moment i walked in to the place. And to Mikiya, Rum, Mayu, and Subaru. Thank you ALL for great hospitality. See you all soon 😊🙏","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNW7_lZj1KpNNONBZwJpLM_JSs8xlxoZ93Cgqyc&fid=0x0:0xcc621ac7fc194781"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"Nicholas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3MqXkQTWBnytBqBoopWRG64mTWTekYAfx5KuIzef3l0AjSOM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a wonderful birthday with Rajio with my wife!!!! Kushikatsu is such a great way to eat fried food nice and light not greasy at all. Staff are incredibly nice and welcoming here so that’s a huge win!!! Will be back again soon for sure with friends!!!! Thank you again Rajio!!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMBsBoIWWTPaoIf6hO29xp8wayDMeQYvhKu9J1s&fid=0x0:0xcc621ac7fc194781"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Callie Perdue","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhk03jvEouDz9tR4fVD9P5Wc7UhXK9h25P9uTPlziHjUwnOFHP-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Not only is it a cute & cozy restaurant but they are serving some of the most innovative and tasty udon dishes I've ever had! Their scallop carpaccio was to die for too. Do yourself a favor and check this place out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMP9vAotQPkULc0zdFUTAgv9uJqjxu_jro12Em0&fid=0x0:0xcc621ac7fc194781"],"When":"2024-8-1"},{"Name":"Fernán Oviedo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLMNyrTTiHR4Zfs_4KOSf072KTEBXxk2tD4rnh3ffoznWOycg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Ok food at an affordable price. The kushikatsu sampler is good value. The uni-bonara udon was pretty tasty. The pressed unagi sushi wasn't good. The scallops carpaccio tasted quite fresh.

All the tables are quite small, which makes it very awkward to fit all the food and drinks. Ours was also crooked and sticky. The rustic public house vibe tips over to the point of shabbiness. The menu seems very randomly put together.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOeo0J1acEVBHAewPcha-aNrWBAi-xdNlXbgYTE&fid=0x0:0xcc621ac7fc194781"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Emily Lu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKEvwebxzOOvHfn2UnHwr4i_lsQ_4WBBcdmwEUmGOtZoyfwO9Mg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I really did not care for the sticky table surface. And the whole time we were there, there were flies in the premise.

The food was alright albeit on the pricy side. The eel skewer was really tasty. However, since the texture of the skewers is mostly the same and the sauce is also the same, it gets kinda boring after a while.

The restaurant filled up quickly after they opened at 5:30, so it’s best to make a reservation. Lots of references to Japanese culture icons in the 80s.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfUQnedOZEVXstksj2nrT6F6lEft2FQG3_VePy&fid=0x0:0xcc621ac7fc194781"],"When":"2024-6-29"}]

[{"Name":"Jane Shi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFWHgQId1z1gpOQAZDnSRuOfaVawcViBKqphYyzzEF887Ye7SC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered vanilla iced latte twice and told them explicitly that I don't want any ice, but both times they managed to give me a cup full of ice. I mean did you just choose to ignore my request??? Both times they had to scoop the ice out of the cup which also wastes the coffee. And today they ask with a very bad attitude that if I don't want ice, why did I order iced latte. I mean excuse me??????? Your own product is CALLED iced latte how can I order otherwise?????? god I'm so pissed😡😡😡😡😡

Edit: well, I would like to know what sort of concrete steps you would take to improve your customer service before I spend my time filling out the survey.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP26zNE_DWGnKYuaEfMTSdvzSJV2G8ZG69T3jk-&fid=0x0:0x8e5ba67aeb16884"],"When":"2024-4-18"},{"Name":"Ashton Lobo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-pMUIh55ERT5yoWTx3MLftCNVSaPthJBF-YPWCGfpOoas0Xcd=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered 20 min in advance because I know there is a wait . Showed the girl my order number and she said it’s not ready yet which is fine. Waited another 10 min and asked if my single coffee is done cause other people who ordered after with large orders for their food came and went. She looked at my order number again and said it’s not done. 5 min more and I looked at the numbers myself and my order is sitting there cold when I’ve been waiting 30+ min and when I told her my order is there she just shrugged at me and said I thought you said a different number even though I was also showing her my order number on the phone. Just an excuse and a shrug. Quite infuriating since I made it a point to try and confirm with her twice if it’s already up","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"RandomAlpaca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWc8u0_GgO8i6h2t6topz8d0q7v21fNNwo_yKKNeSkQzcr9qkb8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Excessively crowded which is expected, but they forget items in orders. I got a sandwich, coffee, and donut, and they only gave me the sandwich and donut. Whoever is running Tim’s stores on campus needs to be replaced as they’re really not doing a good job with quality assurance.

EDIT: Tim Hortons reached out and pointed me to a website that was only functional for US locations. Pointing customers to a non-functional website is worse than just not responding to reviews.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPax_SpCgnZMnQbo08sOwzNib2xw2Lt3_YTtma9&fid=0x0:0x8e5ba67aeb16884"],"When":"2024-4-2"},{"Name":"Trevor Bauer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL3kOQXRi6t9ZaWFmWOK1yHhdMbwZakzEgV87anVI5-hmZoWw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered a meal for my girlfriend and they finished making the order without calling out the order to be picked up. My gf patiently waited for her food, until she went up herself to find out it’s been ready. Complete waste of time. Because of that the food went cold and tasted mediocre. I also ordered a donut for her which they never gave her and it was closed already so she couldn’t get the donut that I paid for. Waste of time and money.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Clare Kiernan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWDtgqAHBQP-hdFm7dvkILK-8JWMGyKuC3aAuckHobV4v8UzfI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I got the cilantro chicken wrap. This is my third time from this location and never again! The first time I got one it was excellent, the second time, I waited 40 mins and it was very mediocre. Today despite no lineup, it took 20 mins. The wrap was awful. First off, it was just thrown together. The ingredients in lumps and not at all mixed, and the wrap was not folded up well at all. Worst tho, was the chicken. It was so tough that I couldn’t even bite through it, I had to grip the pieces between my fingers and gnaw on it to het a bite. It was a messy and totally enjoyable experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Miranda Beland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXugd-yJW_ZmR4sLr-haBN83f_URWB7O5JM90puo-gziqIVFEG6=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"At least 60% of the time I come here they get my order wrong or forget something. When I asked a staff member about my missing item, they attempted to convince me I was wrong about the order I literally watched them enter into the till.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alex Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsS-1aq93FxG14MhrycZLyGMNUgtvT517vrkZsmZvuyf-iNtxU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Trivy D's Order: Large Turkey Bacon Club Sandwich. 4 Donuts (1 Apple Fritter, 1 Boston Cream, 1 Sour Cream, 1 Honey Cruller). BELT bagel and Large Iced Coffee 50% Sweet","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Justin Goh Kian Hwee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKaJsTQukvXaUjEPh_Nim_Fr7rjrv34EmxUe97S2H_kljdjGg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Very  rude staff manning the collection station on 18 Nov.. Got shouted at rudely even though there was noone manning the booth and I had to collect my order ASAP. Please follow up on this","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: West Coast Suites at UBC
address: 5961 Student Union Blvd, Vancouver, BC V6T 1K2
descriptions: Polished suites in an upscale campus property with a fitness room & free Wi-Fi, plus kitchens.
about: null
