user_reviews: [{"Name":"Andrew Varley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLjnq84TKWkg-tLqF45oNeQLJbZsKNJSF5Wh6BdqPtFv1Xd1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I love pizza hut pizza... Usually. This is the first time I've gone to this location and unfortunately it's the only one close to where I live now. I ordered and paid online. Once I got to the store, it smelt bad and I couldn't find anyone working there. After several minutes and ringing their service bell, someone came and gave us the pizza. Sadly, when we got home, it wasn't topped well and there was too much crust. It was also kind of small for a large pizza. Overall, it did taste pretty good, but if the topping and service quality isn't better next time, it'll be my last time going to this location.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMtS5iZ_XrjicRCGchGxrddbKFtstFKQVc9rnyj\u0026fid=0x0:0x73dc129c03bbe4ca"],"When":"2024-6-7"},{"Name":"Channery Lin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPCa58XswM9oeJkBlSP7OFCtX4mM1nu7J-ZHpsMvSOGBAjZBIB=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"FOOD SO GOOD! SERVICE SO GOOD! PLACE SO CUTE! YES YES YES! CAME HERE 2 NIGHTS IN A ROW!! HIGHLY RECOMMEND! Thank you Hrmn for the wonderful service and food!! ❤️❤️🙏🏼🍕😚","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXGjghIM0WYKPDjSt2OkgP0Lv0wUjmNErrSMsC\u0026fid=0x0:0x73dc129c03bbe4ca"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Alice zhao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLUfiRk55VShc1QAIWLb_yvaY8ztxoOnHIhfevRzbQAF_htdAo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Two times in a row they burnt the cheese and the crust was so dry it was hard to bite，they used to do a good job，but I would not go back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEvUBL688JiZ6yg5HvddEvE-beUmzm39EVJjAq\u0026fid=0x0:0x73dc129c03bbe4ca"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"Kali Dumbrell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIF-R5nuYoypZBOnP7oKiA2YK0fBoXPazaV5qaF1UwKGlJq4A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"On the weekends I will often take a walk in the woods and then head to the library and grab a personal pizza. It's a perfect treat. Whenever I go there, Love, the manager, is very friendly and attentive. I appreciate this high-quality service and location!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rane Simpson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5oKgLOrxETpWNrlEBRDhwQtiUf_O2ZC6UyFJcnsPvifspJg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If you buy from here, you're rolling the dice. I've ordered from here twice, once was great, pizza was the best I've had in the area. Second time the toppings were extremely sparse, and the sauce was nonexistent. I think they actually put some because I had the BBQ chicken and I could smell it, but I couldn't taste it at all. They maybe put 5% of the normal amount of sauce. Ordered 2 pizzas and they were both the same. Hard to believe it's possible to screw up a pizza so badly. Will be going to Cornwall from now on.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSodhAgEqEZbUMq1UrGxmYAOk1530pYkdNXgk9\u0026fid=0x0:0x73dc129c03bbe4ca"],"When":"2024-2-3"},{"Name":"Jennifer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIRYF6mt7fxAWLB76LLNY5_bJLZcNjJpxSovCkmMwZSdHEN2A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always a great experience at Pizza Hut. My wife is from Brunei, really loved all the options available here, and was even sending pictures to her parents because she liked it so much!
We definitely will go again next time we're in Vancouver 💛","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQbHscqkDBrA78fA_ZuOEfHEviSlOhK0y759wI&fid=0x0:0x43e657669f8110be"],"When":"2024-12-12"},{"Name":"Gordon Cheung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVYpk0cIhtHUvM7XXheJSxz2s3kSGL8HqlDSxLxb-fzNnM7pgBx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good service. This is the most ridiculous thing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Roxanna A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvu7ReYx1jDqEBEihJ1WEpyUOvvS9FNTvugliEo1xCZAMtqxSb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Friendly dude at the checkout on a Friday evening was eager to give advice about the products they carry! Prices better than other liquor stores obviously as it’s a government store.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tiphanie Felix","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5cKFNUmADzWdMw_kQjRZVSQ6EFvmfyvB0IaLH_Xir64zlqaM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The gentleman was kind in letting us know that the store was closing soon. However, young lady at the cash register was less than helpful. For a location that has a lot of customers that are not normally from BC, it would have been helpful to say what “second ID” was acceptable. In today’s day and age where people always carry their credit/debit card (an acceptable second ID), it would have been easy to say we can use that as second ID instead of turning us away. I guess she wanted to go home already 🤷‍♀️","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew Mockett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJh16kXTvjp9voL_usPnY-C1Rs3AMvFSlWh494t5irYIVOYvA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Was buying alcohol for my mother and had my younger brother with me and was asked to leave as he was a minor and therefore it was illegal for him to be in the store? It's a complete zero on the scale. The waiter's attitude was extremely bad, the worst shop assistant I've encountered in a month in Vancouver with the worst service attitude, very impolite and very rude, I'd like to know why you need to check your ID card after checking your passport, do you carry your ID card for domestic use even when you're abroad instead of your passport? Very bad shopping experience, simply the worst shopping experience I've had in Vancouver in a month. I can't forget the arrogance and rudeness of this waitress for the next 10 years. I think the owner should focus on training his staff on service awareness!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shannon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUR5MSTnMQUenhPuSgfv6aUYPpoTBrQLvEE5nOIl_spt2v9Oi4T=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They have a decent variety, but I'd like a wider selection of wines from Spain and Portugal. Haha!

Update: Walked in the other day and spoke with Mario, who was SO helpful. They didn’t have what I was looking for, but listened and tried hard to provide alternative suggestions without judgement. Had a really upbeat vibe, which I appreciated.

Older woman with the glasses whom others have given poor reviews for was there too, I think. She’s definitely unpleasant and I’d avoid her for assistance. I’ve been impressed by everyone else though. [{"Name":"Chantal Beaulne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4iPSaOoxa5N-aIK7WYR6cb4u_gJpd1PU2Smc4K3gtzFxK0ufA4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Danoo has come under new management and it’s a massive improvement. The new owner is a very kind, conversational guy, but he can also make a mean crêpe. He’s very open to suggestions or requests, and will make things to order with no fuss - he even encourages it. I’ve had nothing but perfect meals every time I go there, which is becoming more and more frequently. It’s a pretty quiet place, which is a shame, because the food is great - but until people figure out this is a hidden gem, it also means it’s the place to go to avoid the line ups for coffee and smoothies at the coffee shops down the road. If you want to skip the lines, this place could sure use the business, and it’s also a nicer, quieter start to the day.

And again - such good, good crêpes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORwmNCmYRq22_aiOP3gN4-QX47KkuqBSEPWksP&fid=0x0:0x609c14887d4cda4d"],"When":"2024-10-25"},{"Name":"Sora Al-Hamami","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUufDXjw0049Bx2obDd_iYK0L-bYgOmyPWCsMDtEUPuYn2HkSs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really good food, fabulous taste I couldn’t wait to take a pic had to take a bite before and enjoy while I write this review. Really recommend this place, their service is excellent and a great place very tasty. Egg benedict with bulgogi beef is a must try.

Also the nutella latte super delicious. Bobby is the owner and the chef, he’s s super sweet and i cant wait till I’m back in town to come back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuotvUMuZLyBa26ZsiQ-BqXYP6TYHhUq-X_aee&fid=0x0:0x609c14887d4cda4d"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Patty M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLzYB8hXGPbayx7tpEViMXV_lLAqxSi21QGr_7rvQmRSA0nxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently stumbled upon this hidden gem of a restaurant and had the pleasure of trying their savory crepes, which were some of the best I've ever had. I’m already looking forward to returning to try the sweet crepes next time. The owner is also incredibly friendly. Highly recommend this place!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sisi Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ1XrEfjoHB25JyI9GWmLk55v02rjLSr5ozV1st76zzH4jcJA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went to Danoo cafe this morning .  ordered strawberry banana waffle and pork belly Benedict. It was so tasty. The pork belly  with kimchi is perfect! Big size and fresh. The bubble tea it was fantastic ！The stuff so nice. The place looks great . I’ll repeat !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGla15dWkMdkjE9gYeDyR9YnH-mt2aqewugNAi&fid=0x0:0x609c14887d4cda4d"],"When":"2024-5-16"},{"Name":"Lauren Young","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJszv0xvV6CI-zOUXF-nhKFDvG9-7fmIllym2j0ztH9HQcBiI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The owner and staff are so friendly and accommodating! We came in with a large party and they were so welcoming. The food was great, and my friends and I had such a great time. Thank you so much for the wonderful experience. Definitely check them out!! Prices are also super reasonable!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jade Tsui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI07p4-rPZUOm_gnTxt2eAgnoM7i2sWDKs4vgzQql1WtXuZKnM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"In love with this place - the food is beyond amazing - the crepe and masala fries are so special and delicious. The owner was also so nice to us when we are there - he even gave us a free crepe. Because the owner works alone, the service is not the fastest but that's not a problem at all since he communicated that to us. I appreciate this cafe a lot and will come right back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pratyaksha Awasthi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXb8pZrx3au1RiFFbUjGwbeRctpxFQb6HrhRWGP45hkfSL3vUis=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered the crepes and waffles and loved them. There was a huge portion, and the food was jist delicious!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZnIJRDDGdrS2-g0A0QqqbBRQdbq4bnR-oQ86K&fid=0x0:0x609c14887d4cda4d"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Hannah Mahdavi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKW609cpHMDUeU_kbmbpUWNSK7-McNV11sgKr04S0ay7NDPYg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best local brunch spots you can go to! They have a variety of crepes and they all hit the spot! Flavour is on point, portion size huge and the best thing is that they have really good prices. Overall AMAZING and a must try.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Kimia Hsh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXN85V19Jb4Jk-sTaGGI_PTEUcdLYM1crpnesGDxH3SCTl2Cbfq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered the Panaeng (Prawns and Scallops)with rice and Drunken Noodles (chicken) and they were both amazing. It was the best Thai food I had in Vancouver. Full of flavour and aromatics and a perfect balance of spiciness.

PS: I took the photo of the noodles after we had some of it. It was well presented in the plate before we begin eating 😄🍽️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPH1edK_uwdL3_FiP2wyjN7V1Dx5pye8OkKZQBa&fid=0x0:0x41ff7028aedc1619"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Jenna Matsalla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVebyQDnKZjAM21xV80dRK6LZW7SlO2uZLeEIF6M8iY38Wgu15J=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such a delightful experience! First time eating here, not even a big thai food eater, and was not disappointed :) . I got the Drunken Noodles with tofu and vegetables and it was very delicious! I had the dish at 2 spices for level of heat and it was just the right amount for me. I was also very pleased that, as someone with Celiac's Disease, that there was a lot of gluten-free options and some good vegan/vegetarian options as well. The owner and staff were also very friendly, accommodating, and helpful :) ! Highly recommend this place!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rebecca Fernandes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAdheW-q7abDlFOlSQ-d9b2M7e_o4K6qai9GNwOqFtMj64EA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The owner was so accommodating and kind. He provided us with a complete experience and great recommendations. Some of the best Thai food we’ve ever had! The restaurant was cosy, felt authentic and yet modern. Highly recommend the crying tiger beef and red curry, especially if you’re looking for spicy food, they adjust it to your preference and it was perfection. Best Thai iced tea as well!! This is going to be our regular spot for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAyGbaOmTIGwGMqVgrLEFn-yeKMxkBHcKKFtxt&fid=0x0:0x41ff7028aedc1619"],"When":"2024-3-21"},{"Name":"Sean “Seanwiches”","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVnTzFWGQfJQMbbpjucIHtu1smaGLNpsJGa5YTtcfzP5sTrd0k5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nestled in Vancouver’s West Broadway, Taste of Thai radiates authenticity and familial charm. Run by a delightful trio – daughter, mother, and father – the restaurant exudes warmth and hospitality.

The daughter, a graceful hostess, effortlessly guides diners through a menu bursting with vibrant flavors. In the kitchen, the matriarch works her culinary magic, crafting dishes that transport taste buds to the streets of Bangkok. Meanwhile, the patriarch’s jovial presence infuses the restaurant with laughter and camaraderie, treating guests like cherished family members.

From fiery spice of the curry’s to comforting Pad Thai, each dish is a flavorful masterpiece. Beyond the food, Taste of Thai offers a sanctuary where dining is a celebration of tradition and togetherness. For a taste of Thailand and a heartwarming experience, this family-run gem is a must-visit in Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGsQ29cYfOKkD_zQImJQPW7LAyAZ_oM1fqadlM&fid=0x0:0x41ff7028aedc1619"],"When":"2024-3-8"},{"Name":"Farah Anderson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIOJ6Mt16Mi7gLpSTc7xwKVC963JDml9EgLQ_8zWJYNbZGq_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was our first time visiting and we had such a great time! The food was amazing and the owner made us feel so welcomed. The Thai Iced Tea is a must try! We had the spring rolls, red curry, basil fried rice and cashew chicken and every single dish was so delicious! Many people coming in knew the owner by name and you could tell they have alot of regular customers here. We will definitely come back again. Thank you for a wonderful dinner!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"david sojka","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjVtxF8UsJiiN_zhR78LYRi99JgdQVa4NztGHNLgQeAjPZEOLQyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The drunken noodles were very flavourful with the perfect amount of spice kick.

The red curry was equally flavourful and delicious with a side of coconut rice.

If you like spice, highly recommend the in house made chilli sauce.

Decent wine list with pairing notes at a good price compared to Vancouver prices in general.

Serendipitously, the owner Sam used to at run Wimaan. Which was my favourite up until now. Sam is very gracious and the service from everyone was exceptional.

Our new go to Thai place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMl6qnMVkf8z2Un5zu8RH4NVHZ9zphyuMsmXwpi&fid=0x0:0x41ff7028aedc1619"],"When":"2023-11-23"},{"Name":"Jacqueline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1WO7A8lMFW8fnIep9Jc-P2_SjQNy2h_adEbEPeSH1euFHjxxH=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is our first time here. Taste of Thai is very cozy and the food is fabulous! The 4 of us ordered Tom Yum, pad Thai, satay chicken, and pineapple fried rice. We also ordered mango sticky rice, tapioca pudding with banana, and fried banana with vanilla ice cream for dessert.

The food is authentic and tasty, and I especially love the Tom Yum and fried banana! Thai iced tea is also good, It’s quite sweet but I like it.

The staff are friendly, and they even made two flavours of chicken wings for us :D (because some of us can’t eat too spicy). I will definitely revisit this place again for delicious Thai food✨","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0zBqUOlwNXRUAb3gw2d6XCgO1e-4q8KXWrUEH&fid=0x0:0x41ff7028aedc1619"],"When":"2023-3-17"},{"Name":"Ju","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJr5yufCFlnzWeKURciDGl0Lrd3HqGw1b1F7ct386Kexjc1F34=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Taste of Thai is a taste of flavor and delicious food! The food came out relatively quick and the plating was a beauty. The food was very reasonable priced. And It is clear that the restaurant takes a lot of pride and care with the food they serve. The Drunken Noodles were very flavorful and the spice has a good kick to it. The staff is extremely friendly and my table had a wonderful time here for dinner. Taste of Thai has a very nice and cozy ambiance and I highly recommend coming here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOo5UyDGQOhgxIjNBUDCMp-vKf-FTD7s0OoD66K&fid=0x0:0x41ff7028aedc1619"],"When":"2023-1-9"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"M B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIxiCIy7Ch29LlP7VXHtco7aO8YNkp89Hd11g67GLT8n9AIrZy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"They used to serve lettuce and tomato, in fact I think the menu still lists it with the burgers. Last time (August) I ordered the Pork (pictured), this time the Farm (October) and both came with meat and rice, and a tiny bit of slaw. No salad. I didn't realize how much the lettuce and tomato balanced the meat and rice combo. Now it is too dry yet also sort of greasy (not sauce) to eat. No freshness. Not for me anymore. I always get take out, as inside feels grubby, the floor is sticky when you walk. That kind of things always makes me wonder what the cleanliness behind the scenes where your food is made is like... Without the salad it is a spoon of meat and two spoons of rice with a sprinkle of slaw so very overpriced at $13. It is the size of the palm of your hand for reference. I also eat with my eyes and was disappointed with how the burger looked, and sadly tasted. I used to crave this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYJ5S0DbHsJ0w9h1XuMRlCQCM8C4m_WwGggX4b\u0026fid=0x0:0x25762a4aae318566"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Dennis Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJgBHuKaxB6_AGRs3DyAn5DYWAJVYL8OdZQBLbOlZjEJJMR8F5KA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This restaurant is participating in TooGoodToGo app, this photo shows the surprise bag order, half the price of mini beef bowl, not bad but a little small","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0PIYdSvzNdUvylTulTbOJ5JGQdxLKWUlz6DNc\u0026fid=0x0:0x25762a4aae318566"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"leesa tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWsWaHyhzcw7kKPh9V3HkvTK5TTa81TdmCDp9IylYllx4puXIy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered the beef burger combo and it was really good. However, it was a bad Japanese Izakaya in Vancouver area.
Two stars only for the good services for all staff. All staff were so extremely friendly and ebullient. The food was so expensive among the Izakaya and tasted not well. All the foods were so salty. We ordered chicken skins and it came out but it was so salty…. The udon was so salty too. The miso soups were salty, too. Also, I did not recommend to order the grilled squid because it was hard to chew and it was tasteless. The beers are recommended to order.
Even one of the staff had compensated some treats for us but I don’t think I will come back again…..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQ-T8vC28aj5GscFOYe-fuAmz59yJN-v6zAtLw&fid=0x0:0x24f357af8ee1f4f5"],"When":"2022-7-7"},{"Name":"Han Ling","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkfurfZg45U2uYya7AdAzmcKQGQIYhVdmvpM5S9jlCLR9EBZCG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My favorite restaurant on UBC campus. Especially loved their fish roe fried rice and japanese style chicken wings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTPt1RPQ1-ggQE9RfFMPoNutxIKZEWBuQNl5xs&fid=0x0:0x24f357af8ee1f4f5"],"When":"2022-6-30"},{"Name":"Avery Lau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrABv9x3_bbuaIeUAb6D3b2MGnnjFNfu1lDqc53tSA72_yLBJq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I had a coupon through another app for Meet Night, so I decided to try it out! Unfortunately, I was rather disappointed with the food.

I ordered the Aburi Set, which is only available from 11am-4pm. It comes with 3 aburi sushi (salmon, tuna + shrimp), salmon teriyaki on rice, shrimp tempura ×2, spring roll ×2, vegetable tempura ×3 (I think), salad, and miso soup. A breakdown of taste is as follows:

Aburi sushi: my expectations were highest for this, which is perhaps why I felt so let down. The salmon aburi was okay, but both the tuna and shrimp aburi were overcooked and dry. None of the aburi tasted like they were "melting in your mouth", which was unfortunate. Perhaps a kitchen error where they were flamed for too long.

Salmon teriyaki on rice: the rice was. Rice. The salmon was mid, super average tasting salmon. Nothing to write home about.

The tempura (both shrimp and veggies): I've had better, but I've also had worse- again, average.

Spring rolls: small, average tasting.

The salad: super simple side salad. could benefit from more dressing.

The miso soup: average. Had a good amount of tofu, seaweed, and enoki mushrooms.

Overall comments; I was able to purchase for about $8.50 because of my coupon. The people who passed me my food were nice and polite. The presentation of the food was also nice! However, I likely would not return if i didnt have a coupon. The regular price for the aburi set (at the time of writing) is $16.99. For that price, I'd rather go elsewhere.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eric Sun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ0uoLrdVaAgxy_ima5kN_-EQZRYJwHiQNjcVeSqDwpGfPgQg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"They charge you 5 dollars more for the lunch menu on ramens compared to dinner menu, because you have a very small portioned salad, a dry fish snack and a few bites of watermelon. Flavour below average, fair service, portion below average. And the California roll is worse than a cheap pack you purchase at a random ubc mart, the rice is too hard. Overall, very bad experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Stephanie Vu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFFlg8ZCVJN5df9Ep-W5UtMD81ecLr09njsUdrmB7cjmu3VDsO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The waiters were busy but they seemed very distracted. Cheap & large lunch combos!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOODfRsyiOOI7URwzrTcJZ-5DO4QjJwVXLf7tMk&fid=0x0:0x24f357af8ee1f4f5"],"When":"2023-2-25"}]

[{"Name":"Chris Helgren","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMAlSlQnmQbIkMlcbNUhzxzkQe_i_pBwvNmCrJ1Wm7NdB_9U0R=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I hope this doesn't turn out to be a eulogy in the end, but I walked in for brunch and was told that this was the final day in this location at Jericho Beach. Apparently the landlord didn't want to extend the lease. I hope they find a new space in Vancouver. That said, the service was fantastic and deserving of a good tip. I loved the eggs Benedict with hashbrowns and pork belly, I forget what they called it but the food was memorable. And it's in a perfect location near the marina at Jericho so a great place for a walk to burn off the calories","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO44BS-QhzVwExBGdBt60sVJ7rQI5WrhEEj06X1&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Laurel Windover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnEhLdsjZ16qCFrqZXUCMvuEzXtbI46OBVg6YSX7imdPsfZHYlwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I love the casual patio and the menu is priced right. I asked for the salmon burger as a salad instead of a burger and it was delicious!
The service was a bit slow the day I was there though. It didn’t appear to be too busy but we waited 40 minutes for our food and nobody came to do a quality check after we were served. In fact we didn’t see the server again until quite awhile after we were finished eating. That said, it’s a cute, casual spot in a great location and I would definitely go back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOg4RgddnYKK-Gjr0FDLECUohwzN85d-LhzmZqd&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"Tina Fischer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_PBoE3UhL3iJ077dZx_qOA7mXIKHJuwtODDKop9ishOSiUuMS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Classic breakfast was awesome! Wonderful servers! Very fast and yummy! Even gave me a green onion when I asked for it!! Thanks for making my travel experience a good one. 😃👏✈️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoOAvh2tRDsfrjuEP1ANoDHO4Ncr2jLxqAl9Ga&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Ben Jefferson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBEOMkGOoEkxaChUtJDYIbi9DXvbFJ44f1Vjs7ERmTv1vlDzvJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super friendly staff. We had the salmon burger and vegan burger. Both were delicious - the salmon in particular. A low key local vibe. When we visited there were young kids, students, and old timers like us all enjoying the food. Good amount of seating outdoors and inside.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Silver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJawI80c4qwvuA-pWmht_nhIypwFKNS8vUDHnZIepoqs0gJvft7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I really wanted to like this place but unfortunately we didn't. Affordable prices but the food just let us down. I'm fine with basic but found the DICED burger lacking and the nachos were ruined by the corn chips. The fries, which were pretty good, and the biscuit were the only items I liked.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2IuCEopmqKeJmI6RJiYC1Jx0nJYLnmSgbhl5z&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-3-16"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stumbling upon this establishment was like uncovering Vancouver's best-kept secret. Critics of its operations might miss the bigger picture: this place is not just a restaurant but a cornerstone of the DICED Culinary School, which champions affordable and sponsored culinary training programs. With very reasonable prices, especially for its locale, the ever-changing menu keeps the dining experience fresh and exciting. The patio and the events hosted there add another layer of charm. More than just a meal, dining here supports a noble cause, making it all the more worthwhile to explore and endorse.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNY6bN7P2eB7zct_4A0kOI6o7FgWoR-H3d3oeSf&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-2-25"},{"Name":"Adam Myhre","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLlloGTdin2BEFn5bg_e4KC9zJLJE3T-tVTT7t76H3j3mWQRw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"DICED Discovery Cafe, tucked away near Jericho Beach, surpasses its seaside competitors remarkably. This establishment prides itself on prompt service and observant staff, showcasing an unwavering dedication to guest contentment. In fact, there were staff hovering near the entrance the entire time looking for tables to clear or anyone needing anything.  As a dog lover, the inclusive pet-friendly policy significantly enhanced our dining experience, contributing to the overall laid-back vibe of the place.

The outdoor seating area presented a slight hiccup, as only half the tables benefit from the shade, either natural or via umbrellas. However, after a short wait, we managed to nab a shaded spot for our meal.

A point worth noting is the slightly elusive location of the restrooms, hidden within the upstairs hostel. This required a minor search, but the overall experience outweighed this minor inconvenience.

The charm of DICED lies within its simple but well done menu. The irresistible Cuddle burger has managed to capture the hearts of many, including mine. The unbeatable combination of delectable flavor and affordable pricing make it a standout choice!

A crucial aspect not to be forgotten is the cafe's commendable work within the community. Functioning as a social enterprise, DICED invests in shaping the future of young adults in the culinary field. Every delicious meal served is a testament to their commitment towards empowerment and opportunity.

To top it off, we found free street parking just one block away, saving us the usual parking hassle. DICED Discovery Cafe is a great combination of delicious, wallet-friendly food, comfortable ambience, and admirable community engagement.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSPfi0AwhrYBYvn8ORU8C3XN4mxY8m-1H40jSJ&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2023-7-26"},{"Name":"Joshua Brodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLFib9zhnbuMwdZJxwP44egP7q34gwvfJ-Pyd_QVmgeuHQq0g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place and the concept. Unfortunately 2024 wasn’t as kind to Dice as 3023. Perhaps losing the liquor license for the patio?

However still a great place. And just wonderful people. Great prices.  What more could I want?","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Suzie DC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVP5wVyYCm5VabmCjkYB9zq4l4DSI1gVVvywESUKWnv7VT2U84m_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We decided to try Karma Indian Bistro since the Michelin Guide added Karma to its list in 2023.

Overall, we thought it was okay compared to some of the award-winning South Asian restaurants in the US.

There were way too many items on the menu.  If the Michelin Guide recommends a restaurant, I would expect the restaurant to have a smaller menu.  By offering fewer dishes, chefs can focus on perfecting each recipe.  It isn't easy to achieve this with an extensive menu.

We got two appetizers: the chicken 65 and the onion bhaji.  The chicken 65 was tangy and flavorful; however, it was not spicy.  According to my husband, the chicken 65 is supposed to be spicy (his predilection for South Asian food is strong, and he is very knowledgeable when it comes to the cuisine).  The onion bhaji was delicious!  It was nice and crispy.

The lamb karahi was okay.  It had a slight kick to it, which was nice.  The lamb was cooked well.  The vegetable jalfrezi was also okay.  The flavors were subtle; I was hoping the flavors would be bolder.

My husband thought the mango lassi was decent.  It looked pretty.

I am giving Karma three stars.  It is on the Michelin Guide’s list, and I'm rating this restaurant based on other restaurants I have been to that are on the Michelin Guide’s list.  The food should be more than “okay.”  The restaurant should have a smaller, curated menu showcasing its culinary expertise.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwCNe-9Nz1B-5QkCTOOomaxNwClmQCDj9tlPqm&fid=0x0:0x5caf2e6bd3efdca9"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Kat Porco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkg9-cmgKUxfFRMDXBCMo90jVcp5ygdnK00acmKCZNlny4Eos=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We visited Karma Indian Bistro five months ago while traveling from Montana, and we’ve been dreaming about it ever since! The food was perfectly spiced and full of flavor, the service was attentive and warm, and the zero-proof drinks were a rare and delightful find. The cozy ambiance made the experience unforgettable. We can’t wait to return on our next trip!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFUoHTNiqgdDG3v5JlCLCrk9rstMqD7PYwPmxJ&fid=0x0:0x5caf2e6bd3efdca9"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Michael Moriarity","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNhkYaB9zjlkkl74OBPcplO2QslT6bqh419yvto-fc4bLKxsqAKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were so pleased to return to this very special restaurant on October 25th for a special dinner occasion …such a special treat and experience to be welcomed so warmly and to look forward towards an authentic Indian cuisine…the staff provided an exceptional discussion of the menu and the hospitality was present from the moment we arrived..either traditional or contemporary style of menu options are available…again we totally enjoyed ourselves at this very special Indian Restaurant by exploring the menu again…the BLT Terrace Noble Pinot Noir wine was fabulous and our Chilli Paneer , butter Naan and Mixed Tandoori Platter was amazing…then the dessert- Chocolate Lava Cake with Vanilla ice cream and RAS Malayi  set the perfect dessert to finish our very special meal….","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNw4kIUt3VCJ4d-k4bKLbUvoOp-i5wK1_x2U83M&fid=0x0:0x5caf2e6bd3efdca9"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"Jacek Dziewonski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI3f961m4N5pPc9gtcB5EHR7wL1UZbXfZE0jng2H1nTOV0IsA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The food is comparable to any other decent Indian restaurant in Vancouver. It was a mild spice, less than almost any other Indian place would give you by default. Great to bring your white grandmother to. Good service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniella Bozzetto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWw0O-rwDCSIm-hsTvjqtBXkPFgcTdPNLf0eCXIXN7PVhn4-w88=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has truly won our hearts. Really enjoyed living here!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOp43zP9IOhSye2NcDhebquupPUNEqkc9AAkC_h\u0026fid=0x0:0x125dd8a7e9a1ca46"],"When":"2020-4-7"},{"Name":"Harran Shi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVposYwd6J2dlDeYCSGnh3ME_dZtFZ9u3SjpUExJkrlqu62h0dh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Don’t talk too loud in your room. If you want to talk to your parents hide under your sheets. People will be able to here you from from neighbouring rooms as well as outside. They can hear you when you shower. They can hear you kicking the wall in the middle of your sleep. And you will be able to hear others too.\nAlso they told us our bathroom was not clean two times and they charged us for the third inspection to clean the bathroom. Prior to the third inspection I had to email telling them we could guarantee that the washroom was spot clean and it was causing mistrusts between us and the residence staff. They emailed me saying they will check again and if the washroom is clean they would not charge us. The third time they arrived, the staff came to our washroom was about to “clean it” (I honestly think they are gonna pretend to clean it, because our washroom didn’t have a spot of dust) my Roomate told the worker that we have cleaned our room the previous inspection and they failed us for no reasons. And the staff said yes, our washroom was really clean. Like huh? You came with all your tools and you were about to clean a perfectly clean washroom! If we did not stop them they would have started their pretend cleaning! They seem to simply follow the instructions to “clean the bathroom”...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNX-NgfRi8f5OGt8GrQZwHw9AdBpcfMuOK1UiAu\u0026fid=0x0:0x125dd8a7e9a1ca46"],"When":"2019-10-12"},{"Name":"Kyle Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVq8PjqN4H65UYnaauc5mKLSKtfHCBg1Z0duY3_fDx3LDIwl_vq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"May be an underwhelming place to live at first, but depending on who you get on your floor and building, living here for first year at UBC may be thrilling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFQsYa7hSG51yufGIYNL6aOzt1F3OAddLbjyoN\u0026fid=0x0:0x125dd8a7e9a1ca46"],"When":"2018-5-20"},{"Name":"Mankanwar Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4dvrRfhrzNoDo-0WZhrM82mUHsTvB5pPzwq40MgBajZvPH0Ma=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice if you get hamlesam and other new buildings","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8jIcn0wK_Nqif1Mv_Qf78RtOSchEtKpnciOVW\u0026fid=0x0:0x125dd8a7e9a1ca46"],"When":"2022-1-9"},{"Name":"Dwayne Perry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLq84FDQFxE-oKbgh9KOMr8MPbTX-cr6pA9xedLNZgrofnJCw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an easy,efficient moving day for our daughter into residence here. Great job...beautiful place!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"KW","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLnPVkSl1JhTPa41qapQ9STNT8BI5tVnBfXDRTCZJIqrTOvIM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pretty decent for first year student housing. Rooms are SMALL, but there's enough room to fit what you need. They have different activities and events for the students to join all the time,  so social life seems good. I didn't eat in the dining hall. I hear it's 'ok' most of the time. Campus is huge, and beautiful. Extremely clean.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sergey Honchu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1u7U8eQ8XF64FJ2Xg--GRhjclAQZ3ZQQRWVnofhCYXjaevA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Parts of Totem Park are great and I'd definitely recommend it out of the residence options. However, if you bring a bike, you'll have to keep it in your room. Bikes are constantly stolen completely or have parts such as gear shifters removed, and UBC and Totem Park management will not take action to prevent it (no cameras etc.) They will however happily, for a few of course, allow you to rent an actually secure bike locker. It's unfortunate but the staff have shown they do not have student property safety in mind, just profits. Moreover, the food is ludicrously over priced and awful for you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Wallace Zhao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-n7VaHSj2xEvhI7YeFd2FQMicO5ZPpO6OQvHBWesoU_c4JuMk9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Liveable, but only just.\nRooms are about 2m by 3m, twin XL bed, rather long desk, plenty of storage space for whatever stuff you may bring. Aesthetics are rather lacking, brick walls and white paint similar to commercial or prison buildings. Communal washroom has five taps, four toilets, three showers. Also no wifi, you’ll need a router or wealthy friends.","Images":null,"When":""}]
